title: shrimp mold
directions: Prepare shrimp, celery and onions.
Heat soup and cream cheese until smooth.
Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add shrimp, onions, celery and mayonnaise to cooled soup mixture; mix well.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until well set.
Serve with Waverly Wafers.

title: curried almonds
directions: In saucepan, combine butter, curry and garlic.
Cook over low heat, stirring.
Add nuts; toss.
Arrange in shallow baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inch).
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes; stir often. Cool.
Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add milk, oil and beaten egg. Beat well and pour into greased pan. Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift 2 cups flour over nuts and raisins.
Dredge until all flour has been absorbed.
Dissolve soda in applesauce.
Mix spices with other 2 cups flour.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs. Add flour with spices alternately with applesauce.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour in greased tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar with a wooden spoon.
Add vanilla. Alternately add flour and chopped nuts.
Roll out dough by patting it with hands to about 1/4-inch thick on floured waxed paper.
Cut with biscuit cutter into crescent shape by overlapping cutter. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes on ungreased baking sheet.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: james andress' venison or beef roast
directions: Put roast in large Shake 'n Bake plastic bag.
Marinate 24 hours and then roast in the marinade about 3 1/2 hours at 350°. Delicious!!!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice until done.
Set aside.
Cook onion, water and broccoli until onion is tender.
Set aside.
Reserve 2 to 3 tablespoons margarine.
Combine milk, celery soup, margarine and cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Add to rice and broccoli mixture.
Add reserved 2 to 3 tablespoons margarine to bread crumbs.
Put 1/2 of crumbs into bottom of baking dish (large, round or square).
Pour rice, broccoli, cheese mixture on top of bread crumbs.
Put remaining bread crumbs on top.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: fig preserves
directions: Bring to boil in large saucepan over medium heat.
Boil for
3 minutes (all ingredients), stirring constantly.
Pour quickly into jars and seal.

title: rice cake s'mores
directions: If desired, spread peanut butter on rice cake.
Top rice cake with 1/2 of 1 candy bar, do this 6 times.
Then top with approximately 8 to 10 marshmallows.
Place on microwave-safe plate (one at a time).
Microwave for 15 to 20 seconds on High.
Cool for 1 minute.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and lemon flavoring.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Roll into 1-inch balls and dip in sugar.
Place balls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press each cookie lightly with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Mix egg and water well with a fork.
Combine flour with salt and pepper on a paper towel or piece of waxed paper.
Pour crumbs on another piece of paper.
Flour fish fillets, then dip in egg wash, then in crumbs.
When all are breaded, fry 2 at a time in 1 cup cooking oil heated to about 300° to 350° in a 12-inch skillet.

title: orange salad a la mrs. schmidt
directions: Oil, vinegar and sugar may be used "to taste".

title: cherry cream pie
directions: In small bowl, put milk.
Microwave on High 2 minutes or until hot.
To this, add cornstarch and sugar.
Heat on High 2 minutes or until thick (microwaves differ).
Add egg yolks, slightly beaten to mixture.
Microwave 1 minute on High.
Add butter and vanilla and let cool.
Mix cherries packed in water; drain and add sugar.
Mix well and let sit.
When filling is cool, drain cherry mixture and fold into pie filling.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.
Add Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate squares
directions: Mix Crisco, margarine, water
and cocoa all together in a saucepan; bring to a
boil.
Remove from heat and add sugar, plain flour,
buttermilk,
soda
and
beaten
eggs.
Bake
30 minutes only at 350° in sheet pan.

title: hamburger-cheese stuff
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; add garlic.
Simmer 3 minutes. Add rice and cheese.
Cover and simmer until cheese is completely melted.
Serve with a fresh salad.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Continue beating while slowly adding honey, then vanilla, butter, salt and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 20 minutes, then reduce heat to 250° and bake for 10 minutes or until firm.

title: shrimp spread(finger food for party)
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Serve on bread.
Yield: 1 1/2 cups.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat shortening until soft and smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar; continue beating until mixture is soft and fluffy.
Add egg; beat well.
Sift together the flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Add flour mixture alternately with the bananas.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch pan.
Pour in batter; bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon and baking soda together. Add eggs, salad oil, strawberries and nuts.
Mix well.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In a blender, beat up the onion. Add the vinegar to the onion. Then add the sugar,	salt and powdered mustard. Slowly add the oil, then the poppy seed.

title: helen's favorite chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in large crock-pot.
Also add vegetables.
Season with 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon pepper.
Add water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour . Remove chicken and vegetables from stock.
Discard onion and bay leaf.
Pull meat from carcass and cut into bite-size pieces.
Place stock in refrigerator overnight.
Also store chicken along with vegetables in refrigerator.
Next day, skim fat that has risen to top of stock. Combine flour with shortening until pea-size crumbs form.
Stir egg with fork.
Add enough cold water to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Stir egg mixture, salt and pepper into dough.
Roll out dough the thickness of a pie crust.
Cut dough into 1/2-inch wide strips.
Boil stock. Add strips.
Cover; turn heat to simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir twice.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box and bake.
After baking, punch holes in the cake with a fork.
Bring sugar and pineapple to a boil.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Pour over the hot cake.
Let cool.
Mix pudding as directed.
When it thickens, spread on the cake, then spread Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut and then nuts.
Refrigerate until eaten.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening, butter and eggs together in large bowl.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Blend well. Shape dough in round balls.
Roll in a mixture of 3 tablespoons sugar and 3 tablespoons cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: pear crumble pizza pie
directions: Prepare pastry for 1 crust pie.
Roll larger to fit pizza pan. Cover crust with pears that have been mixed with the sugar and spices.
Top with Crumble Topping.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Spread thin layer of cake mixture in greased pan.
Spread brown sugar mixture, then add rest of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° until done.
Mix powdered sugar, vanilla and evaporated milk.
Mix well.
Poke holes in cake.
Pour over cake while hot.

title: christmas champagne punch
directions: Mix together first four ingredients and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, remove and add ginger ale and champagne.
Serve immediately.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Add salt, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Add chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on foil-lined cookie sheets.
Put in oven and turn off oven.
Forget for 4 hours.

title: sausage lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, cook pork sausage over medium heat, stirring to break apart.
Pour off excess drippings.
Add onions; cook and stir 3 minutes or until tender.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Layer sauce and noodles. Put in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: yoo-hoo chocolate drink
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a blender for about 30 seconds. Refrigerate until cool.
Makes 2 drinks.

title: deluxe banana pudding
directions: Prepare Dream Whip by directions (or 2 cups Cool Whip).
Set aside.

title: tea strawberries
directions: Mix together (reserve small amount jello).
Let mixture stand in refrigerator 2 days.
Shape into strawberries.
Roll in jello; dry on waxed paper rack.
Use green icing for stems.
Great for weddings or anniversary parties.

title: sock-it-to-me-cake
directions: Beat together the first 6 ingredients.
Add the chopped pecans.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Pour half of the batter in the pan.
Mix the brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter in the pan.
Pour remainder of batter in pan and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: penna dutch corn pie
directions: Line pie plate with 1 crust.
Drain corn and reserve liquid. Add corn to crust.
Slice egg on top of corn.
Add a few dabs of butter or oleo.
Salt and pepper to taste.
If oysters are used, arrange on top (drain off liquid and save).
Put second crust on top and crimp edges.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: devil's delight salad
directions: Mix pie filling and Eagle Brand milk.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip and sprinkle nuts on top.
Freeze and defrost 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: yon mozette casserole
directions: Brown 1st four ingredients, drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients except grated cheese.
Mix and pour in baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese on top.
Bake 25 or 30 minutes, until heated well at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.
Good with salad.

title: potato leek soup
directions: Clean and cut leek into 1/2-inch pieces. In stock pot, bring leeks, water, potatoes and grated onion to boil.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add Parmesan cheese and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Puree soup in blender until completely blended.
Return to pot and cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: date cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with sour cream to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Spread teaspoon of dough on greased cookie sheet to form the cookie.
Flatten 1/2 of date and put on dough. Cover with another small bit of dough.
Spread to cover.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cover with frosting.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar and juice from pineapple plus water to make 3 cups.
Cook over medium heat until cranberries are done. Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup water.
Add to cranberry mixture.
Cool. Add pineapple, grapes and walnuts.
Refrigerate until set.

title: german chocolate chip cake
directions: Slightly beat cake mix, pudding, oil and milk with electric mixer. Gradually add eggs and
mix well, about 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in chocolate chips and grated German chocolate.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan and bake.
Cool 1 hour in pan, upright. Turn out and sprinkle top with sifted powdered sugar. Stays moist and keeps a few days.
Cooking temperature:
350°. Cooking time:
55 to 60 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: fudgy chocolate pie
directions: In a saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in sugar, cocoa and flour.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, then vanilla.
Pour into well-greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes (center may be soft).
Let Serve warm or chilled.

title: mountain bread
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan and bake in preheated 300° oven for 1 hour or until bread starts to pull away from sides of pan.
Cut in squares and let stand uncovered overnight to dry a little.
Seal in plastic bag or wrap.

title: country apple coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch round cake pan with 1 tablespoon butter.
Spread 1 cup apples in pan.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces and arrange pointed side up.
Top with remaining apples.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat the egg yolks and add 2 cups of milk.
Add to the sugar and flour.
Cook over medium/low heat and stir until as thick as desired, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
In a bowl, put a layer of vanilla wafers and layer of sliced bananas; pour cooled sauce over that.
Repeat layers again; last layer should be wafers.

title: chocolate top caramel bars
directions: Cream the margarine and sugars slightly.
Beat in the egg yolks and mix thoroughly.
Add flour and oats.
Mix well.
Spread on greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes and spread with chocolate that has been melted with margarine over hot (not boiling) water.
Sprinkle with the nuts.
Cut into squares or bars when cool.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: In a large bowl, stir ingredients together in order listed. Cover and refrigerate dough at least 12 hours.
Place dough on lightly floured board and cut out.
Place on cookie sheet and let rise 2 hours before baking.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.
Will keep in refrigerator about 8 days.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Blend in soup and milk.
Add chicken, pimento and pepper.
Heat slowly and stir often.
Serve on toast.

title: zucchini crescent pie
directions: In saucepan, melt butter. Stir in zucchini and onions and cook for 10 minutes at medium heat. Add parsley and other seasonings. In separate bowl, mix eggs and cheese. Remove zucchini from stove

and stir in cheese mixture. Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles and place in ungreased 10-inch pie dish. Press to form full crust. Pour mixture into crust and bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Let set for 5 minutes.

title: purple lady salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add blueberries and pineapple.
Chill until partially set.
Whip the cream and fold into jello mixture along with banana and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: chocolate lover's cookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together flour, sugar and cocoa. Cut in margarine until mix resembles crumbs.
Press firmly on bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Glass, nonstick works best.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix cocoa into sugar.
Pour into evaporated milk and cook over medium heat until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped into a glass of cold water.
Beat in peanut butter (more than indicated, if desired) and pour into greased platter.
Let cool completely and cut into squares.

title: cinnamon swirl bread
directions: Soften dry yeast in warm water (110°).
Combine hot milk, sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 2 cups flour; beat well. Add softened yeast; mix.
Add enough remaining flour to make moderately stiff dough. Turn out on lightly floured surface.
Knead about 5 minutes. Shape in ball and place in lightly greased bowl, turning once. Cover and let rise in warm place (about 1 1/4 hours).
Punch down.

title: bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon; drain fat.
Add water and bring to a boil.
While bacon is frying, beat eggs well.
Add cornstarch, vinegar and sugar.
Mix egg mixture well.
Slowly add egg mixture to boiling liquid.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Pour over cleaned lettuce.
Serve warm.
Garnish with hard-boiled egg slices, if desired.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add
salt,
pepper, paprika and sugar. Beat until light and
foamy; add milk.
Pour corn into greased one quart baking dish.
Pour
egg
mixture over corn.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Yields 6 servings.

title: seasoned scallops
directions: Heat oil and butter in small baking dish.
Add lemon juice, bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add scallops; toss to coat with mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Has about 250 calories per serving.

title: fruited jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water until no longer grainy. While hot, stir in chunks of Philly cream cheese until melted. Refrigerate until it starts to congeal, then fold in 2 cups Cool Whip and 1 small can well drained, crushed pineapple.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and melted margarine until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk, chopped chives or onion, green pepper or pimento.
Separate crescent dinner rolls into 4 rectangles; seal perforations.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture into center of rolls.
Pull 4 corners to center and seal. Brush tops with melted butter; dip into 3/4 cup crushed seasoned croutons or Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend in the butter and beaten egg.
Shape the dough and place over fruit. Use any kind of fruit (fresh, frozen or canned) and add sugar according to your taste.
Bake in 8-inch greased pan in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: cheese chowder
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, over high heat, heat to boiling first 6 ingredients and 2 cups water.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Do not drain.

title: taco salad
directions: *May substitute Kraft Catalina dressing (12 ounces) for these ingredients.

title: divinity pastels
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and water; bring to a boil over low heat, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Continue boiling, stirring occasionally, until a little syrup forms a hard ball in cold water (252°) about 15 minutes.

title: smoked sausage and 5 bean casserole
directions: Put all in casserole dish; mix together.
Bake at 350° for 90 minutes.

title: easy chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken and cool, reserving broth.
Melt butter and add to dressing mix.
Put half of dressing mixture in bottom of baking dish.
Save the other half for the top.
Mix soup together with 1/2 cup of broth.
Dice chicken in bite size pieces and put on the dressing.
Pour soup over chicken and top with remaining dressing. Spoon some broth over the top to keep it from being dry.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: low-fat submarine sandwich
directions: Cut bread horizontally into halves.
Spread mustard on bottom half of loaf.
Layer cheese, turkey, ham, lettuce, tomatoes, onion and green pepper on bottom half of loaf.
Drizzle Italian dressing on top.
Cover with remaining bread half.
Secure loaf with toothpicks.
Makes 6 servings.

title: red clam sauce
directions: Fry garlic in oil.
When browned, add spices and rest of ingredients plus 1 cup clam liquid (not clams).
Cook for 1 hour. Taste for flavor.
Add more spices, if needed.
Add clams; cook for 10 minutes more.
Serve over a thin pasta.

title: "cabbage casserole"
directions: Mix and place in lightly oiled medium casserole dish, cabbage and onion.
Mix soup, egg, mayonnaise and butter.
Pour over cabbage.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to package directions.
When Jell-O is partly set, add rest of ingredients and chill.

title: star appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blot cooked sausage dry, then combine with cheeses, dressing, olives and red pepper.
Lightly grease muffin tins and press 1 (or 1 cut egg roll wrapper) wrapper, in each cup.
Brush with vegetable oil.
Bake 5 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from tins; place on baking sheet.
Fill with sausage mixture.
Bake 5 minutes until bubbly.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen appetizers.

title: frozen citrus pie
directions: Place concentrate in a large mixing bowl and beat about 30 seconds.
Gradually spoon in ice cream and blend.
Fold in Cool Whip and whip until smooth (by hand).
Spoon into pie crust. Freeze at least 4 hours.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie or 6 individual pies.

title: oriental salad
directions: Combine in a large bowl and pour dressing over.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: emerald surprise
directions: Mix together peas, onion, celery and sour cream.
Add bacon and peanuts at last minute before serving.

title: egg nog
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks.
Stir sugar into yolks.
Beat in rum, brandy and whiskey.
Heat mixture well.
Stir in cream and milk.
Beat mixture.
Add in well beaten egg whites.

title: date nut bread
directions: Combine dates and boiling water.
Let stand 15 minutes. Grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix with fork, flour, nuts, brown sugar, soda and salt.
Stir in egg, oil and date mixture just until flour is moistened.
Spoon evenly into a loaf pan.
Bake 65 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Makes a 2 pound loaf.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.

title: slow cooked hot crab dip
directions: In a 1-3 quart slow cooker, combine the first 5 ingredients. Mix well with a fork. Add sherry or apple juice, green onion and crab, mix lightly. Cover and cook 1 1/2 - 2 1/2 hours. Serve with crackers or veggies.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs until lemon flavored.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add oil.
Add flour which has been sifted with cinnamon and soda.
Add vanilla; stir in dates, coconut, pecans and apples.
Pour onto well-greased pan.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour, maybe 20 minutes longer.

title: chicken salad
directions: Coarsely chop celery ribs and half the grapes.
In a large bowl, combine chicken, celery, grapes, coconut and almonds. Toss, mixing well.
Blend whipped cream with mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Fold into chicken mixture.

title: grandma's noodle pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then add to cooked and drained noodles.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle optional Rice Krispies on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° oven.

title: ham, broccoli and pasta casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli and macaroni according to package directions. Set aside.
Melt margarine over low heat.
Add flour and onion, stirring well.
Add milk gradually, stirring until mixture is thickened.
Add cheese spread, pimiento, mustard, salt and pepper. Stir well until cheese melts.
Remove from heat and fold in ham, broccoli and macaroni.

title: chili beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook, covered, at 350° for approximately one hour, or until thickens.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: Cream together softened butter and brown sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, salt and baking soda.
Stir in oats; mix well.
Spread 2/3 of mixture on a 15 x 10 x 1-inch lightly greased jelly roll pan.
Melt together chocolate chips, sweetened condensed milk, butter and salt, stirring constantly over low heat.
Blend in vanilla.
Add nuts.
Spread over mixture in pan; dot with remaining dough.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Don't overbake!

title: smothered pork chops and rice
directions: Lightly brown both sides of pork chops.
In a small bowl, mix soup and milk together and set aside.
In an oblong baking dish, spoon cooked rice into dish.
Lay pork chops on top of rice. Sprinkle onion on top of pork chops.
Pour soup and milk mixture over pork chops.
Sprinkle with cheese, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (covered).
Serves 3 to 4.

title: tamale pie
directions: Remove paper from around tamale.
Layer into pan.
Cover with chili, onions and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oil, in blender.
Cover and blend at high speed for 30 seconds.
With blender on medium speed, slowly add oil.
When it bubbles, it is done.

title: rhubarb treat
directions: Place half of mixture in a buttered baking pan.
Next put 4 cups diced rhubarb over mixture and sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar. Put remaining mixture over rhubarb.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until rhubarb is tender.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Heat buttermilk (do not boil).
Stir in sugar, salt and oleo; cool to lukewarm.
Add beaten egg.
Measure 1/4 cup of the very warm water.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar; put in mixing bowl.
Stir to dissolve.
Add the buttermilk mixture to bowl and mix.
Add flour; mix well.
Melt 1 stick oleo.
Roll dough into a rectangle; brush on melted oleo.
Sprinkle on the brown sugar and cinnamon (may add raisins and/or pecans).
Form into a roll and slice into 1 1/2-inch circles.
Place on oiled cookie sheets; let rise until double in size (about 1 hour).
Bake for 25 minutes, or until light brown, in a 350° oven.
Ice with Powdered Sugar Icing.

title: sweet potatoes with ham(servings: 6.  preparation time: 1 hour.)
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until they can just be pierced with a fork; cool slightly.
When cool enough to handle, peel and slice lengthwise into 1/2-inch slices.
Slice ham into 1/2-inch slices about as large as sweet potato slices.

title: bacon chive rice
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Add rice, chives and seasonings. Blend well and heat thoroughly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9-inch crust. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Center should be a bit shaky when you take the custard out.
Put on rack to cool.
The center will set as it cools.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: italian stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut 4 peppers in half lengthwise, discard seeds and chop remaining pepper (reserve).
In a 10-inch skillet in 3/4-inch of boiling water, place the pepper halves, cut side down.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and drain peppers on a paper towel.
Drain skillet and dry.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cookie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs with mixer until foamy.
Add flour and sugars, beating until blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Add chocolate chips and walnuts; mix.
Pour mixture into pie crust; bake for 1 hour.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Combine carrots and water in medium saucepan. Bring to boil; cover and reduce heat. Simmer for 8 minutes or until crisp and tender. Drain and return to pan. Add honey and remaining ingredients. Cook over low heat, stirring gently, until butter and sugar melt.

title: portuguese rice pudding
directions: Boil 3 cups of water.
Add 5 cups of rice; stir once.
When water evaporates add 2 cups of milk.
When rice begins to thicken, add the sugar.
(The sugar will dissolve.)
Stir until rice thickens.
Let sit for 10 minutes.
Add eggs and stir rapidly. Pour into a plate or small cups.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: cabbage dinner
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and form into small meatballs. Brown on all sides.
Drain.
In a 6-quart saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Add the remainder of ingredients except the water. Arrange meatballs on top of vegetables.
Add water, cover and steam for 30 minutes.
Do not stir.

title: tomato cheese souffle
directions: Cook tomato juice and tapioca one minute, stirring constantly. Add cheese, seasonings and butter; stir until cheese is melted. Cool slightly.
Stir in well beaten egg yolks and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Turn into greased casserole and place in pan of hot water.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, depending on depth of casserole.
A long shallow one will have a brown crusty top and requires less time.
Serve with green salad and French bread for lunch.

title: aunt ann's butter cookies
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Make a depression in the center.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.
Put a dollop of powdered sugar frosting in the center after cooking.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add egg last. Put in large pie pan. Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
Test with wooden pick.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.
Can be frozen and reheated to serve.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add flavoring.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Spoon batter into greased 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or until cake tests done.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Steam and drain broccoli.
Add in cans of soup.
Cut Velveeta into chunks and add to mixture.
Pour in milk; then add steamed broccoli.

title: black & white cupcakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients first.
Add the wet and boiling water last.
Can also be used for cake.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place fruit in baking dish (8 x 8 inches, or larger). Cut crust from bread and cut each slice into five strips. Place strips over peaches. Mix sugar, flour, egg, and margarine.
Blend well, pour over bread strips. Bake 35 to 45 min. or until golden brown.

title: roasted brussel sprouts
directions: You will need a large baking pan.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients until 1 mark below soft ball stage. Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream and peanut butter. Beat with mixer and pour into 9 x 13 pan.

title: grape-nut pudding-custard
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and vanilla in mixer or blender.
Pour milk over egg mixture.
Add cinnamon and raisins.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Put custard in pan of hot water in oven.
Use middle rack.

title: pasta salad with peas
directions: Cook pasta
"al
dente." Put frozen peas into bottom of colander and drain pasta over peas.
Cool pasta and peas, then mix well
with
the
remaining
ingredients,
adding
salt and pepper to taste.

title: hungry jack biscuit barbecups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in sauce, onion and sugar.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Press biscuits in bottom and up the sides of muffin tin, forming 1/4-inch rim.
Spoon 1/4 cup of meat into each muffin cup.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute.
If the barbecue sauce you use is a sweet one, omit the brown sugar.

title: frito casserole
directions: Brown beef in a large skillet; salt and pepper to taste and drain off any excess fat.
Then stir in beans and chili; simmer 5 minutes or longer.
Put 1/2 of meat mixture in a casserole dish. Sprinkle chopped onion and grated cheese all over.
Pour in the rest of meat mixture and cover with rest of onion and cheese. Crush Fritos (in your hands) and completely cover the top.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 35 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix and store.
Use 3 tablespoons per cup of hot water.

title: joe's creamed baked chicken
directions: Combine onion, pepper and soups and pour into a baking dish with chicken breasts.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 375° to 400°. Remove chicken and add noodles to soup; cook until noodles are done.
Debone chicken and cut into bite sized pieces; return to soup mixture.

title: duff's bread pudding
directions: Combine Coffee-mate and water.
Mix until free of lumps.
Add melted butter and beat 30 seconds.
Add eggs, beat 1 minute.
Add sugar, vanilla, peaches (which have been cut up).
Beat on high speed for 1 to 2 minutes.
In a non-greased dish, place 3 cups mixture in dish.
Sprinkle with raisins.
Add bread slices which have been cut into cubes (1-inch).
Lightly toss.
Pour remaining mixture over bread.
Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 or 45 minutes.
Cool slightly and top with nutmeg sauce.

title: baked beans
directions: Place 4 cans of beans, catsup, mustard, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce in saucepan and mix well.
Add frankfurters. Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons brown sugar.
Bake, uncovered, approximately 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: pork and potatoes
directions: Mix the dry ingredients.
Dip chops and brown in hot shortening.
Put into a greased casserole dish on top of potatoes. Mix soup, mustard and milk; pour over chops and potatoes.
Bake for 75 minutes in a 350° oven.
Uncover the last 1/2 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour into 8 x 8 inch baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, sugar, soda and salt.
Make 3 holes in mixture and add oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour 2 cups water over mixture and stir well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Chop and saute in 1 stick oleo the 2 ribs celery, 3 carrots and onion.
Add 3 cans Swanson chicken broth and simmer 20 minutes.
Add 3 cans cream of potato soup, 1 lb Velveeta cheese (cubed), 1 can cheese soup and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add 1 (8 oz) carton sour cream.
Whisk to make creamy.
Serves 8 - 10.

title: three bean salad
directions: Melt sugar in vinegar on stove.
Cool mixture.
Add oil and salt.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Shake well in a jar and let stand for one hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain, then cook rice and drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Reserve cup of grated cheese for topping. Combine all ingredients together and pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Add grated cheese, then bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fireman's chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Wash chicken (legs, thighs or breasts).
Place on outdoor grill and baste with mixture, turning chicken and basting every few minutes.
Grill until chicken is done.
Chicken will have a black crispy look because of the poultry seasoning.

title: ham roll
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on thin ham slices; roll up. Chill, then cut in small rolled pieces.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Put rind in cold water and bring to boil (all green and red having been cut from the rind and the rind cut into small pieces). Drain and repeat two to three times in all.

title: brown rice
directions: Pour soup in Corning dish.
Add rice. Cut butter in small pieces and put on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blender coconut pie
directions: Place all ingredients except coconut in blender. Cover and blend 10
seconds. Scrape sides if necessary. Blend 10 more seconds. Pour into a greased 10 in pie plate. Bake at 350° or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean. Serve warm or cold. 6 to 8 servings.

title: meal-in-a-muffin
directions: Beat together egg, milk, oil and brown sugar.
Stir in cottage cheese, carrots, raisins and nuts.
Combine dry ingredients and stir in just until flour is moistened.
Batter will be lumpy. Spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: banana salad
directions: Cook sugar, eggs and vinegar over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cool.
Layer bananas and peanuts. Pour dressing over top and serve.
Serves 8.

title: rice and mushrooms
directions: Brown butter lightly.
Add rice, soup and mushrooms.
Cook until rice is done.
Keep adding a little water until done.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: Brown onion and hamburg until cooked.
Add 2 cans chili beans. Mix.
Stir.
Let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add chili powder to taste if you'd like it spicier.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Mix brownie mix as directed on box.
Spread 2/3 brownie mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and spread cheese mix in pan.
Add rest of brownie mix on top.
After you have two mixtures in pan, use knife to marble the two together. Bake at 350° (as directed on box).
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: family style chicken pie
directions: Melt shortening in large kettle and saute carrots, celery and onions until soft.
Add chicken, bay leaves and pepper.
Cover with cold water; bring to boil over medium heat and cover.
Simmer until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken and cut meat from bones and set aside.
Strain both into large saucepan.
Knead butter and flour together until it resembles coarse meal.
Bring broth to boil and add bits of flour mixture stirring constantly until broth has thickened to desired consistency.
Add reserved chicken, carrots and peas.
Put in casserole or deep pie dish.
Top with pastry, pricking crust with fork.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: lemon sponge pies
directions: Mix sugar and butter well, until light and fluffy.
Beat in 8 egg yolks and salt, again mixing very well.
Add lemon juice and rind, beating well.
Add flour and, lastly, the milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form and hold, but not dry.
Fold egg white mixture into lemon mixture with wire whisk, rolling it over and over until whites are blended but not deflated.
Pour mixture into 4 unbaked 8-inch pie shells.
Fill as full as possible. Place cookie sheet on bottom shelf of oven.
Preheat oven to 425°. Place pies on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 50 minutes.
If getting too brown, place another cookie sheet on top shelf.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and put in casserole. Put a little grated cheese and a few potato chips (crushed) on top.
Can be stored in refrigerator one or two nights.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 hour until well heated through.

title: fruit chef salad
directions: Line bowl with romaine leaves.
Place mixed greens in center of bowl.
Arrange apple slices around bowl.
Sprinkle coconut.
Add raisins, almonds and carrots in circle on top of lettuce.
Cover and chill.

title: stew beef
directions: Brown beef or venison; add Polish sausage.
Add potatoes, onions and carrots.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally.
When meat is tender and vegetables are done, thicken stew with flour or cornstarch.
Add pastry, if desired.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and layer with vanilla wafers and bananas.
Delicious!

title: dutch pea soup
directions: Soak peas overnight completely covered with cold water; drain. (If pig hock or shoulder pork is used, cook meat, peas and water for 2 hours.
If metworst or beef sausage ring is used, you can cook all the ingredients at once.
The metworst and beef sausage require no advance cooking.) Just put all ingredients in large kettle and cook until thick, rich and smooth consistency.
(My mom cooked this soup all day with tender loving care and lots of stirring.)
When nearly done, drop the small prefried hamburger balls into the soup and enjoy!

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine melted butter and cracker crumbs and pack in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set until firm.

title: egg pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, and margarine with hands.
Add warm milk and vanilla.
Beat eggs until white and add last.
Bake in two 9-inch pans at 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: corn meal batter rolls
directions: In large bowl, combine 3/4 cup flour. corn meal, yeast and baking powder.
Stir together milk, shortening, sugar and salt until shortening almost melts.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add egg. Beat on low 1/2 minute.
Beat 3 minutes on high.
At low beat in remaining flour 2 minutes.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
About 1 1/2 hours before serving, time out of refrigerator.
Stir down.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Drop batter into greased muffin pans.
Fill half full.
Cover and let rise 1 hour. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: Saute meat in butter.
Mix soy sauce, water, ginger and garlic to make a sauce mixture
and
serve
over
hot
rice or noodles.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: Mix butter, flour and nuts until crumbly.
Press into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake crust at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden.
Cool.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix raisins, milk and bran together; let soak for 15 minutes to soften.
Combine rest of liquids and add to bran mixture.
Mix all dry ingredients, fruit and nuts; add to bran mixture.
Do not overmix.
Fill greased muffin cups or muffin papers to top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add other ingredients; pour into buttered casserole dish and top with 3/4 cup grated cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: lamb stew with plum jam(heritage:  australia)
directions: Roll the lamb in seasoned flour.
In a large casserole, melt the butter.
Add the oil.
Heat.
Add lamb cubes, a few at a time, and brown quickly.
Remove and set aside.
Add the onions, carrots, potatoes, celery and apples.
Fry, stirring until lightly browned. Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in 1/2 tablespoon seasoned flour.
Add stock and stir.
Return meat to pan.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat to low and simmer for 1 hour or until lamb is tender.
Stir in the jam.
Taste and adjust seasoning.

title: lasagne
directions: In large pan, brown beef and onion.
Drain. Add chopped tomatoes, paste, water, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic powder, pepper and oregano.
Simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally, 30 minutes.

title: burnt-sugar cake
directions: Gently brown sugar in iron skillet.
Add boiling water.

title: candy pudding
directions: Bring the sugar and water to a boil; cook well until sugar dissolves.
Add the whipping cream; cook to soft ball stage (238° on candy thermometer).
Cool and beat until mixture starts to cream.
Add the nuts, coconut and cherries.
Mix and pour into mold lined with Reynolds Wrap.

title: pizza pan cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugars, cream cheese and vanilla. Add eggs, flour, soda and salt. Stir in chips and nuts.
Pour in two 12-inch greased pizza pans and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: green chili dip
directions: Combine vegetables and seasonings in a medium bowl.
Pour salad dressing over all.
Let stand 2 hours or longer in refrigerator.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: terrye's baked rice
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in small covered baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: velma's tea cakes
directions: Put cooking oil in measuring cup.
Add Crisco until oil rises to the top ring.
Add sugar and eggs; beat.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Roll into tiny balls and press with solid bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375°.
I bake on cookie sheets that do not require greasing.

title: pumpkin corn muffins
directions: Combine the flour, cornmeal, salt, baking powder and soda. Sift together in a bowl. In another bowl, beat the egg slightly. Then beat in the honey or molasses, pumpkin, buttermilk and melted butter until well blended.
Add the liquid ingredients, all at once, to the flour mixture and stir just until blended.
Spoon into greased medium-sized muffin pans, about 2/3 full.
Bake in a 425° oven until nicely brown on top, about 15 minutes.
Makes about 18 muffins.
Serve hot with plenty of butter.
Extra good with baked beans or meat dishes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Make into 1 large loaf or 2 small ones.
Pour tomato juice over top to 1/2 up on loaf and bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: walnut frosties cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add the rest of the ingredients.

title: holiday salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Drain well.

title: quail and hazelnut sauce
directions: Grind hazelnuts in blender.
In processor, blend molasses and butter.
Chill for 1 hour.
Season and tie quail to hold in shape. Saute quail in 2 ounces of butter.
Start with breast side down, turning to brown all sides.
Finish in oven for 5 minutes at 450°. Remove quail; drain and add hazelnut butter to thicken.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: sirloin tips and gravy over rice
directions: Trim all fat from sirloin and cut into pieces approximately 1 to 1 1/2-inch square.
Brown well in 1 tablespoon of butter. Remove from heat.
Start rice as directed on package.
Add 1 1/4 cups of water to meat; scrape bottom of pan with fork to incorporate all meat drippings.
Blend 3/4 cup hot water with flour, salt and pepper, stirring flour vigorously to prevent lumps.
Stir flour mixture into sirloin and water.
Prepare Hunter's Sauce as directed on package but do not thicken.
Add Hunter's Sauce to meat.
Return to heat and stir constantly until gravy is thickened.
Continue to cook about 5
minutes.
Serve over rice.
Egg noodles can be used instead of rice, if preferred. Serves 5 to 6.

title: angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix together.
Bake in 9 X 13 prepared pan for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: veal or chicken parmigiana
directions: Dip veal or chicken in beaten egg, then roll in seasoned bread crumbs.
Saute in oil until browned on both sides.
Place in a shallow baking dish and cover with spaghetti sauce.
Top each piece of meat with a thin slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until cheese is melted and browns.
Serve with tossed salad, bread and spaghetti.

title: edible play dough
directions: Blend all ingredients except sugar; add sugar.
Knead to desired consistency.
Store in Ziploc bags or plastic containers.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Stir in oats and chocolate morsels; mix well.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies, or 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Makes about 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: yellow cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add enough milk to make a batter.
Bake in 350° oven until top is starting to brown.
Let cool, then ice with buttercream icing.

title: hamburger cookies
directions: Ice a vanilla wafer 1/2 red, 1/2 yellow.
Place a mint cookie on top.
Ice one wafer green, dip in coconut and put on mint that has a dap of green icing to hold top of cookie to Burger.
Bag in lollipop bags.
You will need more green icing than the others. Keebler grasshoppers have 40-42 in 1 package.
Use 2 wafers per burger.
Wilton cake decorating colors best for icing.
Deeper and better colors.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown the ingredients and use lots of salt and pepper.
Boil 2 cups of chicken broth, add to the ingredients, cover and cook, over medium heat, for 15 minutes and do not peek.
After 15 minutes, look and cook 5 minutes more.
Mix well.
Serve with the chicken and broccoli.

title: 3 kinds baked beans
directions: Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or you can put in crock-pot for a day on low.

title: meat balls for spaghetti
directions: Mix well with hands. Form into balls. In a frying pan with small amount of oil, brown on all sides. Drop in boiling spaghetti sauce.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange peel together.
Chop balance of orange.
Add to cranberries.
Chop celery and add.
Add sugar and nuts to jello.
Serve chilled.

title: lila's dessert
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with pie crust and bake.
Whip the soft cream cheeses with vanilla.
Add confectioners sugar, and mix. Add whipped cream.
Put in pie crust.
Top with pineapple pie filling.
Refrigerate overnight.
May be served with creme de menthe.

title: monster cookies
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole(bonnie's)
directions: Season chops and fry.
Mix potatoes, cheese, 1/2 onion rings, sour cream, 1/2 cup milk and soup.
Place in bottom of pan.
Place chops on top and cover with the remainder of ingredients. Top with cheese and onion rings after baking for 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: deep dish antipasto
directions: Marinate artichoke hearts and mushrooms for 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place triangles in ungreased pie pan.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cut salami into strips; sprinkle over bottom of crust.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese.
Drain artichokes and mushrooms from marinade. Sprinkle over cheese.
Top with green onion, Parmesan cheese, parsley, olives and pimentos.
Bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: apricot cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together except walnuts.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped walnuts.
Freezes well.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Beat shortening until creamy.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Mix in 1/4 of flour mixture.
Repeat until all flour is added.
Roll into small balls. Roll in sugar.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: In a large bowl, beat the eggs and milk. Add spaghetti. Toss to coat. Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with beef, spaghetti sauce, pepperoni, mushrooms and onion. Sprinkle with garlic salt. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with cheeses. Bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese is melted. Let stand 15 minutes before cutting. Yield: 8 servings.

title: macaroon kiss cookies
directions: Beat butter, cream cheese and sugar in a large bowl until well blended. Add egg yolk, almond extract and orange juice. Beat well. Stir together flour, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to butter mixture, beating until well blended. Stir in 3 cups coconut. Cover. Refrigerate 1 hour (or until firm enough to handle). Remove wrappers from the chocolate Kisses.

title: cherry salad
directions: Stir contents of Danish dessert into 1 3/4 cups cold water. Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Chill.
Fold in all fruit and refrigerate.

title: margie's potato dumplings
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Put in 2-quart bowl.
Cool slightly. Drop egg into potatoes, beat well and add next 4 ingredients, which have been sifted together.
Beat thoroughly.

title: chocolate orange freeze
directions: Combine crumbs and butter and press onto the bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine sherbet, orange juice and 1 cup whipped topping.
Pour over crust and freeze.
Heat fudge topping and milk over low heat.
Cool slightly and add remaining Cool Whip.
Pour over sherbet and freeze until firm.

title: bon ton salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl except olive oil; whip until thoroughly mixed.
Pour olive oil in slowly while whipping vigorously.
Yields approximately 3 cups or 1 1/2 pints.

title: scallop kabobs
directions: Parboil green peppers for 2 minutes.
Alternately thread first 3 ingredients on skewers.
Combine next five ingredients.
Brush kabobs with wine/oil/lemon mixture.
Place on grill (or under broiler).
Grill 15 minutes, turning and basting frequently. Yield:
4 servings of 6 oz. kabob.

title: chocolate nut toffee bars
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Reserve 2 tablespoons butter. In a large mixing bowl, beat remaining butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour and cocoa; mix well.
Grease a 13 x 9
x 2-inch
baking pan; press into pan with floured hands. Bake 15 minutes.

title: carrot raisin cookies
directions: In medium bowl mix together dry ingredients.
In large bowl beat together oil, egg whites and honey.
Mix in carrots.
Fold in flour mixture then add raisins and nuts.
Drop by tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart on nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: spice cookies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Mix in a bowl, flour, soda, baking powder, salt and spices.
Add to creamed mixture.
Drop by spoonful on sheet. Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Very good.

title: texas beef squares
directions: Brown onion, pepper and hamburger.
Add tomatoes, rice, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Cook 10 minutes and stir.
Put in 8-inch square pan.
Grate 1/4 pound cheese and put over top of meat. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, green pepper, mushrooms and garlic salt.
Pour off fat.
When beef mixture is browned, add rice and cook for 1 minute, stirring to keep rice from burning. Add tomatoes and pimento; salt and pepper, if desired.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake 1 hour at 350° or until rice is tender.

title: broccoli casserole 2
directions: Mix all ingredients except broccoli and stuffing. Stir in broccoli.
Put in buttered casserole dish. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with herbed stuffing mix. Dot with butter and bake for 15 more minutes.

title: beef spinach hot dish
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown meat and garlic. Drain.
In small skillet, brown onions in butter with basil and oregano.
Combine remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese with butter in oblong baking dish; mix well.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese and dot with butter.
Bake about 40 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 375° in 9 x 13-inch dish about 40 minutes or until done.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar. Add eggs, mixing well. Blend in flour. Shape by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls. Blend cinnamon and sugar; roll balls in mixture. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Immediately remove from sheet to cool. Can use colored sugar for different holidays. Makes 6 dozen.

title: cherry jubilee dessert
directions: Mix ingredients and chill or heat and serve immediately.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together before baking cake and set aside.

title: frozen banana split pie
directions: Prepare pie filling with milk as directed on package.
Pour in 2 cups whipped topping.
Arrange banana slices on the bottom of crust.
Pour mix over bananas; sprinkle nuts over.
Freeze at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: pineapple jello dessert
directions: Dissolve jello. Add marshmallows. Add to whipped milk. Add 1/2 cup sugar and 1 can pineapple. Line pan with graham crackers and butter mixture. Pour in jello mixture and put into refrigerator until set.

title: louis abate's pesto
directions: In a blender or food processor, combine the garlic, salt and oil and process until smooth.
Add the basil and the nuts and process until smooth.
Transfer the mixture into a bowl and mix in the cheese.
Serve room temperature pesto over hot spaghetti or pasta.

title: chinese lo mein
directions: Preparation of Noodles:
Bring water to a boil and place noodles in water and boil 5 to 8 minutes stirring occasionally.
Do not overcook.
Remove from stove and drain into colander under cold water for a few minutes; let drain.

title: "cowless" cow patties
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugars.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and baking soda, mixing well. Add nuts, coconut, chocolate chips and corn flakes.
Mix and drop by large spoonfuls on a cookie sheet.
Spread each one lightly with back of spoon.
Bake 15 or more minutes in 350° oven.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Use a greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Combine croutons and cheese and spread on bottom of greased dish.
Beat the eggs slightly and add milk, salt, mustard, onion salt and dash of pepper.
Mix and pour over the croutons and cheese.
Prepare and refrigerate overnight.
May be topped with cooked crumbled bacon (8 slices) or bacon bits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and sour cream or buttermilk well. Stir in nuts. Spoon half of batter in well greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Add the brown sugar and cinnamon to remaining batter and mix. Spoon over batter in baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Mix well and cook on medium heat until thickens.
Cool.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Top with meringue.

title: sweet potato-pineapple bake
directions: In a large bowl, mash the potatoes.
Stir in the pineapple, pecans, brown sugar and butter.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until marshmallows are lightly browned.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Cook rice in 1 cup of the broth in covered saucepan until almost tender, about 30 minutes.
Cook spaghetti in butter over low heat until golden brown, about 2 minutes.
Stir frequently. Watch carefully.
Add browned spaghetti, onions, green pepper, garlic, thyme, salt, pepper and remaining 1/2 cup broth to rice. Bring to boil; reduce heat and cover.
Cook over medium heat until liquid is absorbed, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; let stand 2 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheesy cabbage and apple slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, celery and green onions in large bowl; mix well.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice, salt, white pepper and fennel seed in small bowl.
Add to cabbage mixture; mix well. Chill, covered, for 2 to 3 hours.
Add apples and cheese cubes; toss to mix.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: boston brown bread
directions: In a large bowl
mix
raisins, baking soda, water, eggs and margarine; gradually
add
flour, sugar, vanilla, salt and nuts. Bake in 3 greased
and
floured
1 pound coffee cans or tube pan. Fill coffee cans half full.
Use all batter in tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Slice Twinkies lengthwise and place in pan, cream side up. Spread pineapple on top of Twinkies.
Spread sliced bananas on top of pineapple.
Mix up pudding and spread on top of bananas. Spread Cool Whip on pudding and refrigerate.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar together.
Blend in egg.
Add flour, salt
and baking powder that has been sifted together. Add vanilla.
Roll
out
on floured surface to about 1/8 inch thickness.
Cut
with floured cookie cutter to desired shapes. Transfer
to
cold
cookie
sheet
with a thin bladed spatula. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: baked beans with hamburger
directions: Saute bacon and chopped onion.
Add and brown ground beef. Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: custard rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and salt slightly, then add everything else. Pour into 1-quart baking dish and set in pan of water 1-inch deep. Bake at 350° for 50 or 60 minutes.

title: chess cheese squares
directions: Beat egg and margarine and gradually add cake mix.
Beat until smooth.
Spread in 8 x 12 x 2-inch greased pan.

title: orange delight "jello salad"
directions: Step 1:
Mix jello according to directions on box.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch rectangular pan.
Allow to almost congeal.
Add crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over jello and return to refrigerator to completely congeal.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix 3 1/2 cups flour with baking powder and add alternately with orange juice to butter.
Combine candied cherries and candied pineapple.
Sift remaining 1/2 cup flour over fruit that has been cut in large pieces.
Add vanilla, 3 or 4 cups pecans and fruit to batter.
Put in tube pan with greased paper bottom.
Bake 2 hours in slow oven. Yield:
5 pound cake.

title: kay's chicken pot pie
directions: Pour ingredients into an unbaked pie crust.
Top with second crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Saute onions, garlic and celery in oil, then add hamburger and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Drizzle butter over top. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy potato bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix potatoes, sour cream, cheese, soup and onion.
Spoon into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Toss crumbs and butter, then sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: mother's nut pie
directions: Mix together in large bowl flour, sugar and salt.
Add Karo, water, butter and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Pour into 10-inch pie crust.
Top with pecan halves (or nut pieces).
Bake at 325° for about an hour until silver knife inserted in center comes out clean.
I usually make two at a time.
One is gone in no time.

title: holiday salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place layers of thinly sliced potatoes, green pepper and onions in buttered baking dish; season each layer with salt and pepper.
Mix soup and milk; pour over potatoes and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: hot taco cheese dip
directions: Layer cream cheese, chili, cheese and olives in Pyrex pie pan. Microwave on High for 10 minutes or 30 minutes in a 350° oven. Sprinkle green onions on top.
Use paper towel to soak up excess grease.

title: chicken divine
directions: Cook the broccoli; place in bottom of greased casserole. Layer chicken over broccoli.
Combine soup with mayonnaise; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sauerkraut and spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving size portions.
Pack into pot and cover with water.
Add salt; cook until tender, about 1 hour.
Add kraut, pushing down meat stock.
Cook 30 minutes longer or until most of liquid is evaporated.
Makes 5 servings.

title: asparagus loaf
directions: Chop asparagus.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole or loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: frozen pistachio dessert
directions: Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Pat in an 8 x 12-inch pan and freeze for 1/2 hour.

title: cottage cheese custard pie
directions: Mix together cottage cheese, salt, sugar, flour, egg yolks and cream. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and pour into pie shell. Bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour. Delicious served with maple syrup.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Wash oysters in cold water.
Add cracker crumbs to melted butter; mix well.
Cover the bottom of a baking dish with a thin layer of crumbs.
Add a layer of oysters.
Season with salt and pepper; add 1/2 the milk.
Repeat and cover top with remaining crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: killer dessert
directions: Bake according to directions, but do not overbake.
Cool. Frost with chocolate icing.
Cut into squares.

title: deluxe cocoa brownies(microwave)
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla in medium bowl at medium speed about 1 minute.
Add melted butter and continue beating until well blended.
Mix in flour and cocoa on low speed.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Spread evenly in greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Cook 3 minutes.
Give dish a quarter-turn then continue to cook 4 to 6 minutes until top springs back when lightly touched. Cut into squares.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together. Fold in potatoes. Turn mixture into a greased 9 x 12 casserole dish. Toss corn flakes with 1 tablespoon butter. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until casserole is golden brown and the potatoes are tender.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Dredge in flour, salt and pepper.
Pound to tenderize.
Brown on all sides in oil. Arrange in layers with onion in baking dish.
Add water and Worcestershire.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until the meat is very tender.
Remove to platter and keep warm, reserving pan juices.
Serve over noodles or potatoes with gravy.

title: chocolate potato cake(ft.  daivs, al)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add cold potatoes and eggs and blend well.
Stir in chocolate or cocoa mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in angel food cake pan or 45 minutes in 2 small loaf pans.
Ice when cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and milk; beat.
Stir in corn and vanilla.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: fried rice with peanuts
directions: Prepare rice.
Cut up vegetables.
Saute onions in oil.
Add remaining ingredients and stir-fry 15 minutes.
Serve with Chinese noodles.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain vegetables.
Mix water, sugar, oil, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetable mixture. Refrigerate overnight in covered bowl.

title: bran muffins
directions: In medium bowl, pour 1 cup boiling water over 1 1/2 cups cereal.
Cool; set aside.
Blend sugar, oil, eggs and buttermilk. Stir in rest of dry cereal and warm cereal.
Bake in baking cups at 375° for 35 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: best ever spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Place ground beef in a large pot with other ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: tuna-cheese bake sandwiches
directions: Slice bread into 8 slices.
Generously butter each slice. Lightly sprinkle garlic powder on each slice.
Place drained tuna in a bowl.
Add chopped onion and 2 to 3 tablespoons of mayonnaise (enough to moisten tuna, but not as much as when you make regular tuna sandwich).
Mix well.
Spoon tuna on each slice of bread.
Top with 1/2 slice of cheese.
Place on broiler pan.
Broil until cheese melts and very slightly browns.
Serve hot.

title: cornbread muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients, beat vigorously 30 seconds. Pour into greased or lined with paper baking cups in muffin pan. Fill to 7\8 full.
Bake at 450° for 20 min.

title: three day old refrigerator slaw
directions: Toss first 3 ingredients in a large bowl. Bring to boil the rest of the ingredients. Pour over cabbage mixture. Toss during cooling. Cover and store in refrigerator. Will keep several weeks.

title: black bean and lime dip
directions: In a blender, combine the black beans, broth, cumin, black pepper, lime juice and zest. Pulse until just mixed. Pour into a serving bowl and add chilies, bell pepper and cilantro. Mix well and serve with tortilla chips. Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend all ingredients and cook according to pudding directions.
Pour over baked pie crust.
Refrigerate.
Top with whipped topping before serving.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Cream together and chill thoroughly.
Slice apples.
Sprinkle with lemon juice (prevents them from turning brown).
Dip into Taffy Apple Dip.

title: green salad with apples and raisins
directions: Slice apple into salad bowl. Coat and toss with lemon juice. Add greens, scallions, raisins and walnut pieces.
Toss with oil dressing.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil noodles until tender.
Boil chicken and then remove off bone.
Saute onion and bell pepper.
Pour chicken, noodles, seasonings, Ro-Tel tomatoes, corn or peas and celery soup into pan. Mix well.
Add Velveeta cheese in chunks.
Bake, covered with foil, for 35 minutes.
About 15 minutes after being baked, stir and mix in melted cheese.

title: spinach squares
directions: Mix together butter, eggs and milk.
Set aside.
Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well and mix with grated cheese and onion.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to butter mixture and stir.
Add spinach mixture. Pour into a 12 x 8 pan sprayed with PAM.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35
minutes.

title: sesame seed green beans(international:  france)
directions: Heat beans through.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Toss and serve.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Dissolve box of Jell-O in container of 1 1/2 cups of boiling water.
Empty can of pie filling and pineapple in 9 x 9-inch dish (do not drain pineapple).

title: easy rhubarb cake
directions: Start with rhubarb in 12 x 8-inch pan.
Then just layer everything in above order on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix together all ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake 8-10 minutes.

title: dekuyper peachtree fuzzy navel cake
directions: Since this is a rich dessert, cut it into thin wedges for serving.

title: creamy clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; remove to paper towel to drain. Discard all but 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Saute onion in drippings for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add clam juice and potatoes.
Cover and cook over low heat until tender for 15 minutes.
Add bacon, minced clams, cream of celery soup, milk and pepper; cook over low heat until heated through.
Garnish with bacon you reserved (2 or 3 pieces).
Serve with oyster crackers, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains 262 calories per serving.

title: cottage cheese delight
directions: Mix pineapple with vanilla pudding.
Add other ingredients. Chill and serve.
Good for Weight Watchers.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Flour dates and orange slices; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add buttermilk with soda. Gradually add dates and orange slices to creamed mixture; makes very stiff dough.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Lay chicken on top of mixture.
Sprinkle onion soup on top of chicken.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Roll and pat into a ball.
Then press remaining nuts onto cheese ball.
Serve with veggies.

title: cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Mix
1 1/2 cups yellow cake mix, 1 egg and oil; press into oblong pan 9 x 13-inches.

title: crabmeat puffs
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on English muffin.
Cut in quarters.
Stick under broiler for 2 minutes.

title: quick and easy haddock(in the microwave)
directions: Will need a microwave-safe dish (big enough to lay fish in).

title: cranberry bread
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Mixture will be lumpy.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until lightly browned on top.

title: creole baked beans
directions: Stir well and place in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco hors d'oeuvre
directions: Mix together sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning. Chill overnight. Spread on jar of taco sauce. Pile on shredded lettuce, peppers, tomatoes, onions and sharp cheese. Dip with Tostitos and/or Doritos.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash and halve green peppers.
Lightly mix beef, rice, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Spoon into peppers. Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over peppers. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover; top each pepper with cheese.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla until thick.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir in zucchini mixture.
Add raisins and nuts and blend well.
Pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let set 10 minutes before removing.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until clear and thick.
Add gelatin and cook until completely dissolved.
Put strawberries into baked pie shell.
Pour syrup over strawberries and chill. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: mom's french salad dressing
directions: Shake well before serving.

title: melody honey
directions: Beat sugar and syrup together; fold in whipped cream.
Cook in double boiler until smooth.
Serve hot over waffles or pancakes.

title: grilled sweet potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Place each half in center of a piece of aluminum foil.
Dot evenly with butter.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle evenly over potatoes.
Wrap well and place on food rack.
Cook over hot coals for 25 to 30 minutes, without grill lid on.
Turn foil packets once during cooking time.

title: summer shrimp (or tuna) mold salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water (1/2 cup).
Heat soup and add cheese.
Beat until smooth and add gelatin, stirring until smooth and dissolved.
Stir in mayonnaise and chill until partially set. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 5 1/2-cup mold that has been sprayed with nonstick vegetable oil spray and chill until firm.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Heat a large Dutch oven and brown salt pork - leave fat in the pan.
Salt and pepper roast and brown in fat - both sides (do not puncture meat).
Add 2 cups of water, bay leaf, garlic, thyme and parsley.
Cover - simmer slowly 2 hours - Keep at least 1 cup of water.
Add carrots, onion and turnip.
Cover and cook 1/2 hr. Then add potatoes and cook until potatoes are done.
Watch water (don't let pan get dry).
Take out meat and vegetables.
Add small amount of water if needed.
For roux melt butter, add flour in the pan and mix to desired thickness for gravy.

title: taco popcorn
directions: Pop popcorn.
Melt and pour butter over popcorn.
Sprinkle and mix taco seasoning into popcorn.

title: cheese custard
directions: Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish or oblong pan with graham crackers.
Mix all other ingredients together, Cool Whip, softened cream cheese, vanilla instant pudding and add milk.
Mix until it is smooth to put on top of crackers.
Put any kind of pie filling on top and spread.
Put in the refrigerator to settle.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix together until smooth, except chocolate chips.
Add the chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Double recipe for 2 pies.

title: pork chops italiano
directions: Combine Italian dressing, mustard and pepper.
Brush chops with sauce and place on rack in broiler pan (or on a grill). Broil at low to moderate heat for 15 minutes per side.
Brush often with sauce to keep from drying out.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine uncooked rice, water, undrained corn, carrot, onion and thyme. Bring to boiling.
Stir in soup. Transfer mixture to a 2-quart rectangular baking dish. Trim excess fat from chops. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Arrange on rice mixture. Cover with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes. Stir together bread crumbs and paprika.
Add oleo. Toss gently to mix.
Remove foil from chops. Sprinkle paprika mixture atop. Bake, uncovered, about 15 minutes more or until rice is tender and pork is slightly pink near the bone.

title: green christmas salad
directions: Mix together Jell-O, hot water and cold water.
Cool until thick.
Whip cream until thick.
Mix all together.
Put into refrigerator to set.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix Cool Whip, vanilla pudding and milk.
Put to the side. Mix cocoa, milk, salt and sugar.
Bring to a boil and then add margarine and vanilla flavoring.
Let cool.
Butter a 9 x 12-inch dish.

title: beef and cheese italian bake
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add 1 jar Ragu sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: trifle
directions: Thaw strawberries.
Slice bananas.
Layer in trifle or deep sided bowl the cake, strawberries and bananas.
To top, dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add lemon juice.
Cool.
Pour over layers.
Mix vanilla pudding as directed.
Pour on top.
Chill several hours.
Top with Cool Whip.
Serve.
Yummy.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Add warm water and oil to flour, salt and baking powder.
Dough should be soft but not sticky.
Knead until smooth, not too much and don't use rolling pin.
Tear off pieces about the size of a lemon.
Pat and stretch until thin, about 1/4 to 1/2-inch.
Poke hole in center with finger.
Fry in hot deep fat (can use electric skillet).
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towel.

title: creamy cheese salmon
directions: Rinse salmon; pat dry.
Arrange (skin side down for fillets) in a single layer in an oiled baking dish; season to taste with salt and pepper.
Mix onion with sour cream (option; add dill weed also) and spread evenly over fish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes per inch of thickness or until flesh turns from translucent to opaque and flakes easily with a fork.

title: settler's beans
directions: Brown the ground chuck and onion; drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 6 hours or medium-low on top of stove for 1 hour.
Serve with corn bread, corn chips or crackers.

title: no miss yeast rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water.
Add eggs, sugar, shortening and salt.
Stir with a fork.
Add 1 cup of flour at a time, stirring with a fork.
When dough becomes too thick for the fork, knead with your hands, until right texture.
Cover; let rise in warm place for 30 minutes (or store in bottom of refrigerator covered with a damp cloth for 2 days).
Knead the dough down and with oil or greased hands, work into small rolls.
Place in pan. Let rise second time again about 30 minutes.
Bake in greased pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Put boiling water and oatmeal together and cover while hot. Combine remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Place chicken breasts in bottom of a baking dish.
Spread can of cream of celery soup over breasts.
Sprinkle uncooked Stove Top stuffing mixture over top of celery soup.
On top spread can of cream of chicken soup.
Add 1/2 can water.
Bake 45 minutes or until breasts are done at 350°.

title: horns-of-plenty
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and butter together like a pie crust. Mix yeast, dissolved in water with beaten egg yolks, then mix first mixture with second mixture lightly with a fork.
Form dough into a ball.
Divide ball into 4 equal parts.
Roll one part at a time on a well floured surface to form a 9-inch circle.
Spread with 1/4 of the filling.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nuts.
Cut into 8 pie-shaped wedges.
Roll as for butterhorns, starting at the wide end.
Repeat with other 3 parts of dough.
Bake on greased cookie sheets at 375° for about 15 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: roast potato cake
directions: Peel and thinly slice potatoes.
Toss with olive oil and 2 cloves minced garlic.
Layer potatoes in an 8 or 9-inch ovenproof skillet.
Sprinkle each layer lightly with salt and ground pepper. Sprinkle top layer lightly with 1 tablespoon grated Parmesan or Romano cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes until potatoes are brown on top.
Cut into wedges and serve!

title: broccoli cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Steam broccoli until partially cooked.
Beat eggs well in large bowl. Add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Stir in cheese, broccoli and onion.
Bake until set, 30 minutes.

title: hot beef sandwiches
directions: Put roast, water, bouillon cubes and onion soup mix in crock-pot and cook on high for 4 hours.
After 4 hours, take out meat and shred it, removing fat pieces.
Put back into crock-pot and add beefy mushroom soup.
Cook for another hour and serve. Freezes well.

title: graham cracker nut loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and quickly.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: mississippi barbecue sauce(taken from mississippi agricultural extension service)
directions: You may vary the recipe to suit individual taste.
Try salting the chicken 1 to 2 hours before barbecuing.
After salting real good, place in the refrigerator.
