If you salt before barbecuing, do not add salt to the sauce.
Amount given is for 8 to 10 halves.

title: macaroons
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Drop onto well-greased baking sheet.
Decorate with cut-up cherries.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until slightly brown.
Remove with moistened spatula. Enjoy!

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into the casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until the top starts to brown.

title: four star congealed salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and let jell in an oblong casserole dish.
Then add topping.

title: chocolate chip cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix cake as directed; fill cupcake cups 1/2 full.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and egg.
Beat mixture together with electric mixer until smooth, then add chocolate chips.
Put 1 teaspoon of this mixture on top of chocolate cupcake and bake.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain all liquids from your peas, corn, etc.
Combine those ingredients in a large plastic container.
Pour sugar, vinegar and oil into bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Cover container and store overnight in refrigerator.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in a skillet.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Lightly mix together croutons, chopped onions, butter, water and poultry seasoning.
Place a mound on top of each pork chop.
Blend soup and water; pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until tender.
Serves 4.

title: minna's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, margarine and eggs.
Add combined baking powder, salt, flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla and lemon.
Place in a cake pan into cool oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: chicken potato curry
directions: In
a casserole dish or a nonstick 9-inch square baking pan, arrange
in
layers
as
follows:
1 cup potatoes, eggs, chicken and remaining 1 cup potatoes.
In a small bowl, blend flour, milk,
salt,
pepper
and curry powder (using a shaker bottle with lid is easier).
Pour mixture over casserole.
Dot butter
over the top of all (by 1/2 tablespoon or whatever is easiest).	Bake, uncovered,	at
for
hour, or until potatoes are tender.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix ingredients in descending order.
Put in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve warm.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: four season pizza(4 pizzas)
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add salt, olive oil and half the flour.
Beat well.
Add remaining flour.
Turn dough out on floured surface and knead until smooth and satiny (about 5 minutes).
Let rise until doubled (about 1 hour).
Punch dough down.
Divide into 4 parts.
Knead and roll each into a circle.
Stretch with hands, if necessary, making dough thicker at edges.
Place 4 dough circles on greased and floured baking sheet.

title: swedish tarts
directions: Cream the butter and cheese; add flour and mix well.
Chill for easier handling.
Pinch in balls and press in molds, being careful not to leave any hanging over edge.
Bake 11 minutes at 425°.
Fill shells with strawberry or cherry pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip. Makes a pretty tray for a party.
Makes 32 tarts.

title: green peppercorn steak
directions: Tips:
Look for green peppercorns in cans or jars in stores featuring imported French food specialities.
They are the immature peppers that ripen into black peppers, preserved in brine while soft textured.

title: chiffon pumpkin pie
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Cook together all ingredients except egg whites.
Add gelatin while still hot.
Beat the egg whites and add 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold into the cooled pumpkin mixture and pour into baked pie shell (9-inch).
Refrigerate.
Top with whipped cream.

title: mom's strawberry salad
directions: Melt jello in hot water.
Add all ingredients to jello, except sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in bowl and refrigerate until set.
Spread sour cream over set mixture and then pour the rest of jello mixture on top.
Refrigerate again until set.

title: ohio buckeye candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and form into small balls. Place balls on a cookie sheet and put into freezer for an hour or so. Melt dipping chocolate in double boiler, being sure no water gets into the chocolate. Remove balls from freezer. Using a toothpick, dip balls into chocolate until almost covered, leaving some of the peanut butter mixture exposed on top to resemble a buckeye.

title: white bread(2 loaves)
directions: Combine salt, honey and shortening; add 1 cup boiling water; dissolve.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Add yeast; dissolve.
Mix in 2 cups flour, then add 2 more cups flour.
Knead until soft.
Put in hot greased bowl and cover for 30 minutes.
Put in bread pans (greased).
Let rise 30 minutes or until well risen.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out and butter tops.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Pour boiling water over chipped beef; let stand 3 minutes. Wrap each breast with a slice of bacon.
Arrange beef on bottom of 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Lay on chicken breasts.
Mix soup and sour cream; add seasoning.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Baste occasionally. Serve over rice, if desired.

title: poppy seed nut bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
Beat well.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt and beat.
Add 1/2 of milk, poppy seed and nuts.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: glarum's potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: patio potato salad
directions: In medium saucepan, combine milk, sugar, vinegar, egg, margarine, cornstarch, salt, celery seed and dry mustard.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened.
Remove from heat; blend in onion and mayo.
Cool.
Combine with cooked eggs and potatoes. Chill.
Just before serving, sprinkle with paprika.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Blend together and store in airtight container.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup.

title: foil steak supper
directions: Place steak in center of foil.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix. Cover with potatoes, carrots, celery, green pepper and onion.
Dot with margarine; salt and pepper to taste.
Fold foil over, leaving a small space for steam.
Bake in 450° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Pour in greased loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over chicken.

title: fruit filled jewel cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter.
Add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and vanilla; beat at medium speed until fluffy.
Add flour; mix well.
Gather dough into ball; flatten into a disk.
Wrap tightly and refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll dough into 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut 2-inch round cookies.
Drop jam or filling onto cookie, then top with another cookie.
Using the tines of a fork, seal edges.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine over medium heat for about 10 minutes.
Add flour, salt and pepper; stir constantly for 2 minutes.
Add broth slowly.
Add broccoli.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Cover and simmer until broccoli is tender. Puree in blender.
Return to pan; add milk and let simmer.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: date-nut loaf
directions: Put soda, dates and boiling water together and let soak while mixing other ingredients together.
Baked in a greased and floured tube pan in a slow oven (300°) until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: "aunt betty's" pound cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Mix together next 4 ingredients. Beat all on #3 for 2 minutes.
Add eggs; beat an additional 2 minutes.
(Gradually increase speeds.)

title: potato cheese bake
directions: Thaw potatoes 45 minutes.
Reserve enough grated cheese to sprinkle on top of casserole.
Mix all ingredients together well. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kasha varnitchkes
directions: Cook noodles to package directions; drain.
In a large skillet, heat oil and cook mushrooms and onions until tender.
Add kasha and salt.
Add hot bow ties and toss well.

title: banana split salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and condensed milk together.
Add cherry pie filling, pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Mix well and chill.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach thoroughly. Combine all ingredients and shape into balls about 1 teaspoon each.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Remove from cookie sheet at once and drain on paper towel.
Serve hot.
May be frozen after baking. To reheat, place in oven for about 5 minutes at 400°.

title: beef bologna
directions: Mix by hand and form into 2 rolls.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
On cookie sheet, bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Mix all ingredients well; bring to boil.
Cook on moderate heat for 10 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour over 8 pork chops in deep bowl and cool.
Can stand overnight.
Arrange chops in shallow baking pan and add sauce.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Baste occasionally.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water. Cook until hard ball forms in water. Add beaten egg whites. Beat until stiff. Add nuts and drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper. Cool.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Combine
all ingredients, except Parmesan, and put into greased
casserole	dish.
Top
with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken hurry
directions: Remove skin from the chicken parts.
Arrange the chicken in casserole. Mix together the ketchup, water, sugar and soup mix. Spoon over the chicken parts. Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for at least 1 hour (until tender).
This is delicious served with rice.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Heat 5 cups milk.
Mix remaining ingredients until smooth and add to hot milk.
Stir until it starts to thicken.
Remove from heat.
Beat 3 egg yolks; add a small amount of pudding to eggs and mix.
Then put all together and heat to boiling.
Remove from heat and add 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla and lump of butter.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in tomato paste, 1 tablespoon of Parmesan cheese, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer while preparing crust.

title: raspberry fluff
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water, then add 1 cup cold water.
Chill until starts to jell.
Beat with electric mixer while adding whipping cream and continue to beat until mixture is fluffy.
Add nuts, pineapple and marshmallows.
Return to refrigerator until firm.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine (completely thawed) potatoes, 1/4 cup margarine, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Stir well.
Spoon into greased (9 x 13-inch casserole.
Crush cereal and mix in remaining margarine. Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pork 'n bean bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, mix sugar, oil, eggs and beans, beating until smooth.

title: peanut butter tandy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into greased and floured cookie sheet (15 x 12-inch, a little bigger than normal; one about size you'd use for Texas Sheet Cake).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Take from oven.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes. While still hot, drop in dabs of peanut butter and spread as soon as it starts to soften.
Then put 4 to 5 Hershey chocolate bars over top of peanut butter.
Spread when softened.

title: mimi's hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add the next 9 ingredients (all except macaroni and cheese).
Simmer 10 minutes, then add macaroni and stir well.
Turn into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Remove cover and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Serve hot with garlic bread and tossed salad.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly. Add flour, which has been mixed with sugar, then add other ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: country chicken and barley soup
directions: Place all ingredients, except parsley, in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer for 1 1/4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove chicken thighs; cool slightly. Remove meat and cut into bite-size pieces.
Return meat to soup. Simmer for an additional 15 minutes; stir in the parsley and serve.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat a pan with a small amount corn oil until hot. Drop into the heated oil by a teaspoon and cook until golden brown.

title: kraut cake(kraut tastes like coconut)
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cocoa. Cream butter, sugar and vanilla; thoroughly beat in eggs, one at a time; stir in flour mixture in several additions, alternating with water, until smooth each time.
Stir in kraut.
Turn into 2 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean, 30 minutes. Cool on wire racks for 10 minutes; turn out on racks; cool completely.
Use Mocha Cream to sandwich cakes together and frost top and sides.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Cook over medium heat until thickened. Pour in baked pie shell.

title: beef roast casserole
directions: Place
roast
in baking dish with water, salt and onion soup mix;
sprinkle over roast.	Place lid on baking dish and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Bring spinach and water to a boil in a covered saucepan.
Cook 1 minute.
Drain and cool.
Add scallops and shrimp.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add diced fish and cooled spinach.
Drain off any liquid.
Mix eggs with cream, salt and pepper, beating well. Spoon fish and spinach into pie shell.
Pour cream mixture over seafood.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop onions and dried beef.
Combine with cream cheese and mix thoroughly.
Form into ball and roll in more dried beef.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook zucchini, onion and oleo for 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley, salt, pepper, garlic, basil and oregano.
Combine eggs and grated cheese.
Stir in zucchini mixture.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 10-inch pie pan. Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Spread crust with 2 teaspoons of yellow mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture into crust. Bake in 375° oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until center is set.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Heat and brown flour and oil in iron skillet as usual for making gravy.
Salt and pepper flour.
Add crushed tomatoes and stir.
Add water to finish gravy to desired thickness.

title: hot clam dip
directions: In a saucepan combine clams and lemon juice.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Melt butter.
Saute onion, green pepper, garlic, oregano, parsley flakes and pepper in butter.
To this add bread crumbs.
Mix in the clams.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until brown.

title: lemon party chicken
directions: Coat chicken with mayo.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Heat oil (just a little) in frypan.
Fry chicken (as many as the pot can hold at a time).
Meanwhile in a saucepan make chicken broth 1/2 the strength.
(Use 1/2 the water for every cup that the recipes says).
Remove from stove.
Fry chicken until brown on both sides. Ladle two scoops of broth and put into pot with cooked chicken. Squeeze 4 lemon slices into the pan with the chicken.
Leave on flame for 1 minute.
Dump in roaster pan.
Keep going until all your chicken is cooked, then cover tray with foil and bake in a 350° oven for about 40 minutes, no more.
Enjoy!

title: frozen daiquiri
directions: Mix, stir and freeze for 3 days.

title: frosted grapes
directions: Beat cream cheese, margarine, powdered sugar, and vanilla until creamy. Add grapes and walnuts; stir until well coated. Chill and enjoy.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: In big pot, brown hamburger; drain.
Add all the ingredients, except cabbage, green beans and macaroni; cook 20 minutes.
Add cabbage, beans and macaroni and simmer until all vegetables are tender.
You may add additional water for a thinner soup. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: bacon dip
directions: Soften cheese and margarine; mix together and add bacon, onion, olives and garlic salt.
Cool, then roll in pecans.

title: venison stew
directions: Coat venison with flour; brown in bacon drippings in a large Dutch oven.
Cover meat with water; add catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add carrots and potatoes; cover and simmer about 45 minutes.
Add garbanzo beans and pimiento; cook an additional 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: lite chicken teriyaki and stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken in strips and marinate in teriyaki sauce in refrigerator overnight.
Cook in microwave on bake until tender (about 7 minutes).
Cook rice according to package directions. Add water chestnuts, cooked broccoli and teriyaki sauce.
Stir until moist.
In small amount of peanut oil, cook bell pepper, onion and mushrooms; drain and add to rice mixture.
Top with chicken.

title: baked kapusta sauerkraut
directions: Wash the sauerkraut.
Add the cabbage, onion, salt, pepper and bacon or kielbasa; mix well.
Bake in ungreased dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham and cheese bites
directions: Butter the bread.
Place a slice of cheese and a slice of ham on three pieces of bread.
Cover with remaining three pieces. Press together firmly.
Fry gently in butter until golden brown on both sides.
Cut each sandwich into diagonal quarters.
Serve hot.

title: spaghetti cheese
directions: Boil spaghetti or macaroni until done.
Drain.
Pour in baking dish.
Add grated cheese to spaghetti or macaroni.
Add stick of margarine and Cheddar cheese soup.
Mix milk and 2 eggs in a bowl. Beat with fork.
Add to spaghetti and cheese.
Stir with spoon. Mix well.
Salt to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: monkey biscuits
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 to 6 pieces. Combine cinnamon and granulated sugar.
Roll each piece of biscuit in mixture and place into greased Bundt pan.
Melt butter and brown sugar together and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: jordan marsh blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and mix until blended.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Mash 1/2 cup of berries and stir in by hand.
Add rest of blueberries, whole, and stir in by hand.
Grease muffin cups well; grease top surface as well.
Pile high in each muffin cup.
Sprinkle sugar over tops.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool in muffin pan at least 30 minutes.

title: festive syrian rice
directions: Soak apricots and raisins in water for 1/2 hour.
Cook rice according to directions.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a baking dish.
In a skillet, melt the margarine and saute the onion, green pepper and curry, until the vegetables are soft but not browned. Add the almonds to the skillet.
Drain and chop the apricots.
Mix the rice, apricots and raisins with the sauteed vegetables.
Place the mixture in the greased baking dish and bake in oven for 30 minutes.

title: potato yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water; let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Cream shortening with sugar.
Beat well after each addition.
Add eggs. Beat until fluffy.
Mix mashed potatoes, salt and milk together; add to cream mixture.
Beat.
Beat in 1 cup flour.
Stir in softened yeast and beat in potatoes.
Beat in enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn dough onto floured surface and knead.
Form in ball and turn into greased bowl.

title: spam casserole
directions: Stir the cooked macaroni and the mushroom soup together.
In a 2-quart baking dish, put half of butter, then a layer of the sliced potatoes, a layer of the diced Spam and a layer of the macaroni and soup mixture.
Sprinkle half the grated cheese, then the rest of the potatoes, rest of the macaroni mixture, rest of the Spam and rest of the butter.
Cover with bread crumbs. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: best ever brownies
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add the chocolate and flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter easter eggs
directions: Combine all ingredients into a bowl.
Blend well.
Divide into 6 parts and shape into a bowl.
Blend well.
Divide into 6 parts and shape into ovals.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: In a bowl, combine the shrimp, oil, garlic, rosemary, oregano and bay leaves. Cover and refrigerate for 2-4 hours.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix and serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 8.

title: jello pie
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and let cool one hour. Combine all remaining ingredients and beat until very light and fluffy.
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: easy chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix together and pour into freezer.

title: broccoli fondue
directions: Saute mushrooms and chopped celery in skillet with butter. Melt 1 roll garlic cheese in double boiler.
Cook 1 pkg. frozen broccoli, as directed on pkg.
Combine all together and keep warm in fondue pot.

title: onion soup
directions: You will need 6 (2-cup) baking bowls.

title: lemon chicken(one-skillet meal)
directions: Dip chicken in flour.
In a large skillet, heat oil and margarine over medium-high heat.
Add chicken; cook 5 minutes on each side.
Remove from skillet; set aside.

title: new year's eve dip
directions: Blend the cream cheese and ketchup in mixer.
Start with cream cheese at room temperature and add ketchup until mixture is a peachy-pink shade.
Add dashes at a time to taste of the spices (about 2 to 3 dashes).
Blend thoroughly.
Taste.
Adjust with listed spices, or add salt, pepper, garlic powder, again to taste. Chill for 1 plus hours.
Re-taste and re-spice, if necessary. Serve with potato chips.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: tiger butter
directions: Combine white chocolate and peanut butter in top of a double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook, stirring constantly, until chocolate melts.
Spread mixture into a wax paper-lined 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix well.
Sprinkle grated cheese or crumble croutons or potato chips on top.
Let set several hours.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
If casserole is cold allow more time (50 minutes) until hot and bubbly.
tags: amount of chicken broth or mushroom liquid

title: candy strawberries
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and roll.
Shape into strawberries. Roll in red colored sugar.
Refrigerate.
Makes about 2 dozen. You may use green icing to make the stems or purchase stems from bakery supply store.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix ingredients all together and cover.
Refrigerate for 24 hours. (When draining spinach, try to get as much water out as possible because dip will be too runny otherwise.)

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add the eggs.
Gradually add the milk and mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Chill.

title: baked noodles
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Combine noodles with the remaining ingredients, except paprika and cheese.
Bake in buttered casserole dish at 350° until hot (about 30 minutes). Sprinkle with paprika and Parmesan cheese.

title: doris' yeast rolls
directions: Mix 1 cup hot water with butter, sugar and eggs.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water; add to butter and sugar mixture.
Add flour and cover; let rise at least 2 hours.
Punch down, knead and roll out like biscuits. Put in greased
cake
pans and let rise another 1 to 2 hours. Bake at 425°
for 12 to 15 minutes.
This recipe will last in the refrigerator for 7 to 10 days.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl and beat until smooth.
Spread on unrolled cake and then reroll.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: scalloped meatballs
directions: Parboil potatoes, carrots, onion and 1 teaspoon salt for 10 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Mix ground beef, egg, bread crumbs, milk, thyme and 1 teaspoon salt.
Shape into balls.
Brown meatballs in margarine.
Remove meatballs from frying pan and pour off all drippings.
In same frying pan stir soup and sour cream; heat just until hot.
Layer half of vegetables, meatballs and soup mixture in a baking dish.
Repeat the layers and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: country style vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in vanilla and half and half.
Mix well. Freeze in freezer.
Any fruit flavor can be made by adding 3 cups fresh or frozen fruit sweetened with sugar.
Puree the fruit and add to vanilla mixture.
Then freeze.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and 1 1/4 cups of water in saucepan.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Stir in mixture of flour and milk, stirring constantly.
Add cheese.
Cook until cheese melts, stirring constantly.

title: ralph's bread pudding
directions: Blend eggs, salt and sugar with wire whip.
Add vanilla and milk.
Break bread into medium-sized pieces in a bowl.
Pour the melted butter over bread and toss to coat.
Then arrange bread in a Pyrex baking dish and pour the egg mixture over it.
Place the dish in a larger pan of water with at least an inch of water in the pan.
(Water should be well up around the dish.)
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve with lemon sauce or whiskey sauce (below).

title: jam cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves together. Mix remaining ingredients together in separate bowl. Slowly add flour mixture. Bake in three 9-inch round cake pans at 350° until done. Ice with Caramel Icing.

title: never fail frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients for 15 minutes on medium speed of mixer. Enough for 1 large cake.

title: curried tuna casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In skillet brown butter and curry powder. Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased casserole dish. Bake uncovered for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage; crumble.
In casserole dish, place cubed bread on bottom.
Sprinkle sausage and cheese on top.
Beat eggs; add milk and mix.
Pour on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
If you choose, you may refrigerate overnight and bake in the morning.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add a little milk if necessary.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: ham casserole
directions: In saucepan melt butter; saute onion and green pepper.
Remove from heat and stir in mushroom soup and sour cream.
In a 2-quart buttered casserole dish, mix layers of noodles, ham and cheese. Cover top with crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream sandwich dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan:

title: green rice casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine 1 cup white flour, wheat flour, yeast and salt; mix well.
In saucepan, heat milk, water, honey, molasses and shortening until warm.
Add to flour mixture.
Add egg.
Mix well (about 3 minutes).
Gradually add remaining white flour.
Let rise until doubled.

title: squash cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugars.
Beat in the eggs and squash.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Remove broccoli tops (flowerets) and break them into pieces. Rinse, drain and put in medium size salad bowl.
Add chopped onions, raisins and crumbled bacon.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar. Pour over salad mixture and toss.
Serves 6.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Mix fried hamburger, spaghetti and spaghetti sauce all together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then top with cream cheese (might want to add a little milk to cream cheese to make runny). Then top with French fried onions.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Makes about 10 to 12 servings.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Cook in boiling water until soft (not too soft).
Put in ovenware bowl; add milk, butter, cheese, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in casserole dish.
Thin soup with milk; heat and pour over broccoli.
Melt margarine and add cracker crumbs. Sprinkle on top of broccoli and cheese mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all other ingredients and pour in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Let cool at least 15 minutes before cutting.

title: wy's chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Heat broth and add chicken and seasonings (and vegetables, if desired).
Roll out pastry to fit 9-inch square pan.
Pour chicken mixture into crust.
Top with another crust.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours until light golden brown. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese, peanut butter and sugar until well blended.
Stir in 1/2 the container of Cool Whip and vanilla. Pour in pie crust.
May freeze or put in refrigerator several hours to set.
Top with rest of Cool Whip before serving.
This pie freezes and can be kept frozen about a month.

title: chicken italian
directions: Saute onions, pepper and garlic in oil.
Add other ingredients and simmer.
Boil chicken.
Use broth to cook noodles in.
Chop the chicken.
Add noodles to onion mixture,
then add chicken. Grate cheese
over top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: jambalaya
directions: Mix rice, water and margarine together; cook 20 minutes.
Brown sausage, onion and green pepper; drain fat.
Add can of tomato sauce and kidney beans (drained).
When rice is cooked, add sausage mixture together, then add salsa.
Mix all together.
This is spicy.
You can use regular sausage if you don't like real spicy food.
Serve with a green salad.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cooking applesauce
directions: Put liquid and 4 or 5 pieces of apple in blender container. Cover and process until smooth.
Push blend and add remaining apples a few at a time.
Add sugar and cinnamon.
Yields about 2 cups.

title: seasoned snack crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pan.
Place in glass dish and heat in microwave for 3 to 4 minutes or heat in oven at 300° for 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: navy bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: cream cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes about 8 sandwiches.

title: crispy baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Pat fillets dry with paper towels; brush with dressing.
Coat with crumb mixture, pressing crumbs into the fish.
Place fish on a lightly greased baking sheet (or spray with Pam).
Bake until the fish is just cooked and the crumbs are golden, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: uncle louie's crab treats
directions: Place English muffins, open faced, on broiler pan.
Layer avocado slices and crab meat on each muffin half.
Pour Hollandaise Sauce over each.
Sprinkle with paprika.
(Dab on Tabasco sauce, if desired.)
Broil for 3 to 5 minutes (or until bubbling and golden).
Serves 2 to 4 people.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13 inch pyrex dish.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix cream cheese, parsley, chives, garlic powder, Mrs.
Dash and Tabasco sauce.
Spread in a dish, then cover with cocktail sauce.
Drain and rinse shrimp; pat dry.
Place over cocktail sauce.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, Jell-O, flour, eggs, water, oil and 1 cup strawberries together.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans at 350° according to cake mix directions.
Mix margarine, confectioners sugar, vanilla and 1/2 cup strawberries together to make frosting.
Ice cooled cake.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Chop fruits in food processor.
Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: meltaways (cookies)
directions: Press together and shape into balls.
Press down a little. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. When baked, roll into powdered sugar while still warm and again when cold.

title: spritz cookies(light, tasty cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Beat butter and sugar until creamy. Add egg and vanilla, continuing to beat. Add flour 1 cup at a time. Dough will be soft. Do not refrigerate. Sprinkle colored sugar or sprinkles on dough. Fill cookie press and place cookies on cookie sheet about 1-inch apart. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown around edges. Cool 2 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.

title: cheese and spinach puffs
directions: In saucepan, combine spinach and onion; cook according to spinach package directions.
Drain well, pressing out excess liquid.
Combine eggs, cheeses, salt dressing, butter and garlic powder.
Add spinach mixture and muffin mix; mix well.
Cover and chill.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Cover and chill until serving time (or place in freezer).

title: zesty meatballs
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Cook meatballs in hot oil until they are lightly browned; drain.
Place meatballs in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: sweet potato croquettes
directions: Mix sweet potatoes with fat, salt, pepper, sugar and 1 well beaten egg.
Beat well.
If mixture is too stiff, add a little hot milk.
Shape into croquettes.
Roll in crumbs; dip in beaten egg, diluted with water, and roll again in crumbs.
Fry in deep fat at 375° until golden brown and drain on unglazed paper.
Serves 6.

title: yellow squash pickles
directions: Combine vinegar, salt, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed. Bring to boil.
Let set 1 hour.
Use small squash (cut in thin slices).
Dice green pepper and pimentos.
Pack in jar.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over squash and seal.

title: tandy cakes
directions: Mix together eggs, vanilla, sugar and oil.
Beat well. Add flour, milk and baking powder to rest of ingredients and mix well. Pour into jellyroll pan (well-greased) and bake for 25 minutes at 300° to 350°.
While still hot, spread peanut butter on top. Cool in refrigerator.
Melt Hershey bar with 2 tablespoons oil.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: artichoke, tomato and avocado salad
directions: Combine vegetables and season heavily with salt and pepper. Pour dressing over and marinate at least 2 hours.
The longer the better.
Drain and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry rice in oil until brown, then add water and boil until soft.
Drain.
Saute the onions in a little oil; mix with tomatoes and chopped peppers and add to the rice.
Add seasonings and place in a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: reuben sandwich mix
directions: Mix all together and bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serve on cocktail rye or Reuben rye bread.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and eggs.
Mix in remaining ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Butter bottom of 10-inch glass pie pan.
Sprinkle coconut over bottom of pan.
Place all other ingredients in blender and blend well on high speed.
Carefully pour over coconut.
Be sure coconut is moistened.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Surprise - it forms its own crust.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes and chop coarsely. Chop celery, onions and peppers finely and add to tomatoes in a large saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients, mix and simmer slowly, stirring occasionally until desired thickness (about 1 1/2 to 2 hours). Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Place on bottom of 13-inch round glass platter.
Spread chili sauce on top. Sprinkle crab on top. Sprinkle parsley over mixture.
Let sit in refrigerator for a few hours, then serve with crackers.

title: clam stew
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Eat with fat-free crackers.

title: creamy apple squares
directions: Combine cake mix and butter; mix until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup for topping.
To that topping portion, add brown sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
Press the remaining mixture onto bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange apple slices over crust. Blend the sour cream and egg together; pour over apples evenly. Sprinkle on the topping mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: veg casserole
directions: Mix well and put in oblong casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle over top.
Drizzle melted butter over crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Cook cabbage, celery and onions until yellow.
Cover with 2 cups of water and simmer 20 minutes.
Put into a large pot and add tomatoes, beans, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Simmer until ready to serve.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Boil eggplant until tender in salt water and drain.
Mix all ingredients but cheese and put in greased baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This is good with 1/2 pound browned and drained sausage added.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches.
Rinse broccoli under running cold water to thaw.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups of Cheddar cheese and onions in plate.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Add onion and 1/2 cup raisins.
Let sit 2 hours.
Then mix in another 1/2 cup raisins and sunflower seeds.
Add 12 pieces bacon, fried crisp and crumbled and 2 large bunches of fresh broccoli blossoms.
Chill, serve and enjoy.

title: chicken 'n stuffing
directions: Boil chicken for 15 minutes.
While chicken is cooking, make Stove Top stuffing according to package directions.
Slice mushrooms.
Mix the soup and evaporated milk together.
Cut up chicken into bite size pieces.
Place into bottom of casserole dish.
Put sliced mushrooms on top of chicken.
Next, pour soup and milk mixture onto the chicken and mushrooms.
Spread stuffing mix on top.
Pour on onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered, then uncover for 15 minutes longer to crisp.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Slice tomatoes and onions thin.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup salt over and let stand overnight.
Drain well.
Add seasonings except 1 pod of red pepper.
Add to the hot vinegar and sugar mixture.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Pack in hot jars.
Use 2 red peppers to garnish.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, blending thoroughly.
Add bananas and process until thoroughly mashed and blended.
Beat in egg and yogurt.
Mix the remaining ingredients together thoroughly and then add the wet mixture to them, stirring to mix until all the flour is moistened.

title: peas and asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and peas.
In a 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole, layer the asparagus, pepper and peas on asparagus.
Spread sliced, boiled eggs on peas.
Salt and pepper.
Then spread undiluted cream of mushroom soup on top.
Cook in 350° oven, uncovered, about 1 hour.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Place all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour dressing over all and toss.
Allow to sit at least 6 hours before serving.
It is best made one day ahead.

title: mrs. honeck's bean salad
directions: Drain beans well.
Add chopped onion and green pepper.
Mix oil, vinegar and sugar well to dissolve sugar.
Pour over beans. Marinate overnight.

title: swiss steak
directions: Stir together flour, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the flour mixture onto meat.
Pound into meat.
Turn meat over and pound remainder of flour mixture into that side.
Cut meat into 6 pieces.
Melt shortening in large skillet.
Brown meat over medium heat about 15 minutes.
Cover tightly and simmer 1 hour.
Add a little water if needed.
Mix tomato, onion and green pepper with salt and pepper.
Pour over meat and cover tightly.
Let simmer 30 minutes or until tender.

title: english toffee
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan. Add sugar, syrup and water. Cook, stirring often, to hard crack stage (300°). Remove from heat; stir in
almonds.
Quickly turn into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread evenly onto pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Melt 1 bar chocolate over hot water.
Spread on one side of toffee.
Sprinkle with half of the pecans.
Let harden (chill in refrigerator). Turn over and repeat with remaining melted chocolate and nuts.
Let harden. Break into pieces.
Store in airtight container in cool place.

title: german sausage and kraut
directions: In small skillet, cook bacon and reserve drippings; set aside.

title: pepper relish
directions: Finely chop peppers and onions.
Add 3 tablespoons salt.
Pack in a bowl and cover with boiling water.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Drain and add vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil until thick.
Put in jars and seal.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Makes 2 cups. (Even better the second day.)

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and milk alternately. Fold in nuts.

title: amish oven fried chicken
directions: Place
oil and butter in shallow cooking pan and put in 375° oven to melt butter.
Set aside.
In large sack, combine flour and
seasonings.
Roll the chicken pieces (3 at a time) in the melted oil/butter mixture, then drop them into the sack and
shake to
cover.
Place on a dish or waxed paper.
Place chicken in the pan, skin side down. Bake for 45 minutes.
Turn over and
bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Serve hot or cold, but texture
of crust is better if not refrigerated before eating. Serves 4 to 5.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Have butter at room temperature.
Mix cornstarch, flour and sugar in a bowl.
After completely mixing, knead in butter thoroughly.
Spread mixture evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan; flatten evenly with hands and spatula.
Prick entire surface with a fork (many times).
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Score into pieces with sharp knife after taken out of oven.
Should be cool before eating.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar when slightly cool.

title: beef taco filling
directions: Brown meat in shortening.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Makes enough to fill 12 taco shells.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix sugar and syrup.
Heat.
Add peanut butter.
Mix.
Add mixture to cornflakes.
Mix well to coat all flakes.
Press into an 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16 servings.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, Jell-O and marshmallows.
Add boiling water; let cool.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Put in refrigerator until jelled.

title: chocolate oreo cake
directions: Crush
Oreos
in
processor, reserving 1/2 cup for garnish. Mix
melted
margarine
and
cookies
and
press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate
for 15 minutes.	Mix 1 1/2 cups of Cool	Whip, 2
packages
cream	cheese	(softened) and 2 cups confectioners sugar.
Beat
thoroughly and spread over cookie crust. Refrigerate
minutes.
Prepare pudding as directed on package and spread.
Refrigerate.
Cover with Cool Whip and garnish with crumbs.
Make at least 1 day ahead.

title: split personality cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix together in a bowl the cake mix, margarine and 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam and pour mixture in. Spread evenly. Bake for 5 minutes. Melt caramels in 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Remove cake from oven. Spread chocolate chips and pecans evenly over cake mixture. Finally, pour melted caramels evenly over all. Return to oven; bake for 20 minutes more. Great warm topped with ice cream.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Stud the 3 oranges with whole cloves, about 1/2 inch apart. Bake in a baking pan with a little water added, at 325° for 30 minutes.
Heat cider and cinnamon sticks in large saucepan.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Simmer covered for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients (nutmeg, honey, lemon juice, orange rind, lemon rind, and pineapple juice) and simmer uncovered for 5 more minutes.
Remove cinnamon sticks that are left.
Pour into large punch bowl and float spiced oranges (above) on top.
Yields:
40 punch cup servings.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix the ingredients and form into a loaf.

title: lime muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin pan cups.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into large bowl. Mix milk, eggs, oil, lime rind and juice in 2-cup measure.
Add all at once to flour mixture; stir lightly with fork just until moist.
(Batter will be lumpy.)
Spoon into prepared cups, filling each 3/4 full.
Bake for 20 minutes or until golden.
Remove muffins from cups to wire rack.

title: company potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in covered saucepan in small amount of boiling salt water over low heat until tender.
Drain and cut in 1/4-inch thick slices.
Combine sour cream, soup and spices.
Place in 2-quart casserole in alternate layers, in order given, using 1/3 of quantity for each layer; the sliced potatoes, sliced eggs, and cream mixture.
Combine bread crumbs and Cheddar cheese and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken dijonnaise(makes 2 to 4 portions)
directions: Coat the chicken with mustard and set in a bowl to marinate at room temperature for 2 hours. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: mini pecan muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray miniature muffin tins with cooking spray.
Fill 3/4 full and bake in a 350 degree oven for 12-15 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix and cook cornbread according to package directions. (May also
use
own
cornbread
or leftover, if desired.) Chop vegetables while
bread
is
baking
and
sausage is browning. (Drain sausage very well.
Also run cold water over sausage to get rid of
all
fat.)
If using bacon, be sure to drain also. When bread
is
done,
break into small pieces and add vegetables, mayonnaise, pickles and juice.
Serve cool.

title: victorian fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Chill for several hours before serving.
Maraschino cherry halves may be added for extra color, and chopped pecans if you like.

title: gingerbread people
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Blend in molasses, water, flour, salt, soda, ginger, nutmeg and allspice.
Chill 2 to 3 hours. Heat oven to 350°.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut with gingerbread people cutters.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press raisins into dough for eyes, nose and buttons.
Use other items to trim as you choose.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove to wire rack.
Trim with decorators icing. Yield: 14.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Cook
berries
until soft;
strain through sifter.
Add seasoning and sugar.
Mix well and heat 5 minutes on low heat. Put into baking dish and drop dough like dumplings into juice. Cover top with dough and dot with butter.

title: easy chicken stir-fry
directions: Pour oil in a wok or skillet, coating bottom and sides; heat to medium-high for about 2 minutes.
Add chicken and almonds; stir-fry about 2 minutes.
Add vegetables; cover and cook 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: out of this world pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine pie filling with sugar, pineapple and juice, cornstarch and food color.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Allow to cool.
Add sliced bananas and pecans after cool.
Pour into 2 pie shells and top with whipped topping. Keep refrigerated.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine 1 cup meat loaf fixings with eggs.
Add next 8 ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Add ground chuck and thoroughly combine.
Shape half of meat loaf in shallow pan.
Fold cheese slices in half; place on top of meat loaf.
Add rest of meat mixture.
Make sure meat is sealed around cheese.
Cut bacon in half and lay on top of meat loaf.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Drain off grease.
Mix remaining tomato sauce with the brown sugar and seasonings to make topping.
Pour over meat loaf.
Return to oven and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: wassail
directions: In crock-pot, combine first six ingredients.
Simmer.
Float orange and lemon slices in wassail after simmering.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs
and
oil together.
Add sugar, flour and dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Roll and cut out. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: In large pot, cook until meat comes from bone easily.
Discard skin.
Strain broth and cool.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Place juice in saucepan.
Add sugar, flour vinegar and egg.
Heat and stir until thick.
Add pineapple. Refrigerate.
Can leave until next day.
Add Cool Whip, apples and peanuts.
Marshmallows may be added, if desired.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Mix well and press into 9-inch pan and save some to sprinkle on top.

title: funnel cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Add egg and milk, beating until smooth.
Heat 1/4-inch oil to 375° in skillet.
Cover bottom opening of a funnel with your finger. Pour 1/4 cup batter into funnel.
Hold funnel over center of skillet.
Release batter in a slow circular motion into hot oil.
Fry 2 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.
Drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Eat this way or with syrup.

title: date or fig filled cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and brown sugar.
Cream well.
Blend in unbeaten eggs, vanilla and almond extract.
Add dry ingredients gradually.
Mix well.
Chill about 2 hours.
Prepare filling.

title: turtle cookies
directions: Blend cocoa, butter and eggs.
Add sugar, flour and vanilla. Drop by teaspoonful onto hot waffle iron.
Close cover and cook for 1 minute.
Frost with chocolate frosting when cool.

title: biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift flour.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and stir.
Roll out on floured sheet.
Knead 5 to 6 times. Roll with rolling pin until it's 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out biscuits and brush tops with butter.
Bake for 6 to 7 minutes.
Makes approximately 20 biscuits.

title: spinach burritos(vegetarian)
directions: In a skillet, saute the onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
Add the spinach and pepper; cook for 2-3 minutes or until heated through.
Place about 3 Tbsp. of mixture on each tortilla; top with 1 Tbsp. of picante sauce and 2 Tbsp. of cheese.
Place seam side down in a 13x9x2 inch baking dish that has been coated with cooking spray.
Top with remaining picante sauce and cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20-25 minutes or until sauce is bubbly and cheese is melted.
(Yield: 6 servings.)

title: sharon's pecan pie squares
directions: Grease 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Beat all ingredients together.
Mixture will be dry.
Press firmly in pan.
Bake until light golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Prepare filling (recipe follows).
Pour over baked layer.
Spread evenly.
Bake until filling is set, approximately 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add egg, pumpkin and cream. Sift together the flour, salt, cinnamon, soda and baking powder. Add to mixture.
Add raisins.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Grind pepper and chop finely.
Mix vinegar and sugar.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Add Certo and food coloring. Mix well.
Pour in jar and seal.

title: escarole and white bean soup
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in medium bowl.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Set aside.
Heat broth in large saucepan over medium heat. Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add meatballs and cook until firm to touch, about 30 minutes.
Serve immediately, adding Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken piquante
directions: Mix salt, pepper, rosemary, marjoram and oregano together; sprinkle over chicken.
Saute until brown in olive oil.
Add lemon juice and chicken broth or white wine.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 6.

title: corn bread stuffing
directions: Place celery, onion and butter in a 1 1/2-quart ovenware casserole dish.
Cook celery and onions 7 minutes or until soft, stirring well twice.
Stir in chili powder.
Continue cooking for 1 minute.
Stir in stuffing mix and olives.
Beat egg slightly with water in a small bowl.
Pour over stuffing mixture.
Toss lightly until evenly moist.
Cover casserole.
Continue cooking 3 minutes.
Total cooking time: 11 minutes.
Recipe yields 6 cups or enough to stuff 8 to 10 pound turkey.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Prepare 2 cups of strong tea and set aside.
In a large bowl (freezer safe), combine the water, bourbon, sugar, lemonade and orange juice.
Mix well.
Stir in tea.
Place in freezer overnight.
It can be served with 7-Up.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Toss lightly.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Sprinkle chips and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until heated through and browned.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: dump cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan dump pineapple and cherries; mix.
Add dry cake mix; sprinkle coconut on next.
Drizzle melted butter or margarine all over the top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.
Also good cold.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Place half in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine Cool Whip, cream cheese, powdered sugar and butter.
Next combine pudding, milk and vanilla.
Pour layers on top of cookies and put remaining cookies on top.
Cool at least 2 to 3 hours.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Combine first four ingredients in large bowl.
Blend in shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 375°. I use 2 loaf pans.

title: cheese cake
directions: Blend powdered sugar, vanilla and cream cheese until smooth, then fold in Dream Whip until mixture is all one texture.
Put mixture into pie crust right away (hardens quickly).

title: sweet-n-sour cabbage soup
directions: Combine ingredients in large soup kettle.
Place over high heat and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for about 1 hour or until vegetables are tender and flavors meld.
Remove bay leaves after first 30 minutes of cooking time.
Makes 2 to 3 quarts, 8 to 10 servings.

title: easy chop suey
directions: Brown sliced beef well, adding onion and celery near the end of browning.
Brown onion and celery slightly with beef.
Sprinkle with soy sauce while cooking.
Mix rest of ingredients in a large casserole.
Add browned meat to soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper.
Add beef, parsley, and Italian seasoning.	Cook until brown.
Add tomatoes and sauce.
Simmer 15-20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Mix egg and cottage cheese. Add to meat mixture.
Stir in parmesan cheese.	Place cooked noodles in a 2 quart baking dish.
Add sauce.
Add more Parmesan and cover with grated cheddar.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes until cheese melts and casserole is bubbly.

title: cracklin corn bread
directions: Mix with water to pouring consistency.
Pour in iron skillet that's preheated with lard in it (about 1 tablespoonful).
Bake in preheated oven at 425° until golden brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Dump pineapple over entire bottom.
Put cherry filling over the pineapple. Shake dry cake mix evenly over fruits.
Slice margarine over the entire top. Cover with chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve warm with whipped topping.

title: peach pickle
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and spices and let come to a boil. Peel peaches and add to syrup, letting them boil 4 minutes or until easily pierced with a toothpick.
Remove peaches and place in jars.
Let vinegar boil 5 minutes more, then pour over peaches and seal.

title: pop's vegetable soup
directions: Cut vegetables in pieces.
Add vegetables, fresh or frozen, to boiling water.
Add hamburger meat, tomato soup, salt and pepper. Put ingredients in the amount you desire.
If too thick, add more water.
Cook over medium heat for 2 hours.
If you wish, make a large amount of soup.
Let cool and freeze for later use.

title: beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
May be served hot or cold. Great with crackers or vegetables.

title: cajun beans and rice
directions: Chop onion and pepper into 1/2-inch size pieces.
Saute in oil.
Add beans.
Drain 1 can only.
Add seasoning.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer on low 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve over white cooked rice.
Add Tabasco sauce for taste.
Ouch!
Serves 4.

title: nachos
directions: Arrange the chips in a circle around the edge of a microwave-safe dinner plate.
Spoon a little salsa on each chip, then sprinkle with cheese.
Cook on High for 30 to 45 seconds until the cheese melts.
Makes 1 serving.

title: sour cream rum pound cake and icing
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flavoring and salt.
Alternate mixing flour and sour cream ending with flour. Bake at 325° for 1 hour 10 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.
Ice with Rum Butter Icing.

title: browned rice
directions: Brown
rice
and
place
in
baking dish.
Add water and stir. Bake,
covered,
for 30 minutes or until rice is tender. Meanwhile,
saute
onion
and mushrooms in butter.
Remove from heat and stir in peas and soy sauce.
Blend into rice and bake, uncovered, an additional 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, then pumpkin, seasonings and flour.
Beat until smooth; add nuts and raisins and lemon juice.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit soup
directions: Cover fruit with water and cook 20 minutes (simmer).
Add sugar to taste.
Stir in 3 to 4 tablespoons Minute tapioca until it starts to thicken (will thicken more when cool) Add 1 or 2 tablespoons lemon juice.

title: szechwan chicken and shrimp with rice
directions: My favorite 15 minute dish.
Place oil in skillet with garlic, chives and shrimp.
Toss for a few minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons soy, 1 tablespoon oyster sauce and hot oil, a little sugar to thicken.
Add cut up chicken and toss until cooked.
Add rice. Cook until tender.

title: saucy pork casserole
directions: Brown meat, celery, onion and garlic; drain.
Stir in corn and 1 cup salsa.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix biscuit mix, cornmeal and pepper; stir in milk.
Spoon biscuit mix over meat on diagonals.
Pour leftover salsa on top.
Bake for about 20 to 25 minutes in a 400° oven.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage until it gets a little soft.
Mix all ingredients together except V-8 and sauerkraut
and roll in cabbage leaves.
Pour V-8 juice on top of the sauerkraut and cook until done.

title: pineapple nut pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice slowly.
Fold in Cool Whip, pineapple and chopped nuts.
Put in graham cracker crust. Makes 3 (8-inch) or 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan, combine chips and butter.
Stir over low heat until chips are melted and smooth. Add milk and mix well.
Lightly spoon flour into cup.
Combine flour, nuts, vanilla and chocolate mixture; mix well.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip cream cheese and marshmallow together.
Use as dip for any kind of fruit.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Warm the sour cream; stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool. Pour warm water in large bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast.
Stir.
Blend in sour cream mixture and eggs which have been slightly beaten. Blend in flour and knead.
Cover bowl and refrigerate overnight or several hours.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Boil sugar, salt, margarine, Karo and vanilla for 5 minutes. Watch carefully.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Stir quickly. Pour over corn and peanuts, mixing well.
Put onto large cookie sheets and bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring several times.
Store in tightly closed container when cool.

title: mandarin orange pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Bake at 350° in three layers for 25-30 minutes.
Cool completely before icing.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Combine ingredients, except for cheese and chips.
Fill individual baking dish or pan.
Sprinkle with cheese and chips.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until hot.

title: chili
directions: Cook ground meat, stirring until no longer pink. Drain and add onion, garlic and cumin. Cook, stirring 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and cook, covered, over low heat for 45 minutes.

title: 1-2-3 cup chocolate pie
directions: Cook pie crust as directed.
Combine flour, sugar, milk and egg yolks in large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave for 1 to 2 minutes at a time, stirring after each cycle, until thick.
(It may take as long as 10 minutes.)
After filling starts to thicken, add vanilla, butter and salt; stir well.
Continue to microwave until done.
Add cocoa and mix until well combined.
Pour into pie crusts.

title: frosted carrot cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Combine brown sugar and next 7 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; stir in dry ingredients and beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until well blended.
Pour batter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake completely in pan on wire rack.
Spread Orange Cream Cheese Frosting over top of cake.
Cover and chill.
Yield:
18 servings (205 calories per serving).

title: 9-inch apple pie
directions: Prepare pastry.
Stir together sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt; mix with apples.
Turn into pastry-lined pie pan; dot with butter.
Cover with top crust which has slits cut in; seal and flute.
Cover edge with 2 (3-inch) strips of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning.
Remove foil last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes or until crust is brown and juice begins to bubble through slits in crust.

title: italian stuffed meat loaf (braciuola)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, bread crumbs, tomato sauce, parsley, garlic, salt, pepper, basil and ground round in large bowl.
Mix well.
Divide into 2 equal portions.
Cut two 12 x 12-inch squares of foil.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Pat out each half of meat mixture on foil to 9 x 12-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham slices on top.
Sprinkle Mozzarella on top.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, basil, parsley, salt and pepper.
Using foil as aid, roll up jelly roll fashion.
Starting from long side, seal edges and ends.
Place on greased jelly roll pan.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: whipped cream cheese spread
directions: In food processor or electric mixer, combine first five ingredients.
Blend well.
Stir in pimiento.
Cover and chill.

title: lasagna wells style
directions: Boil noodles until soft.
Brown meat.
Drain.
Add in sauce & seasonings.
Heat until warm.
Lightly spray 13x9-inch pan with Pam cooking spray.
Lay 3 noodles longwise in the pan.
Spoon sauce mixture over noodles until covered.
Spread 3 more noodles in pan covering with sauce.
Continue alternating noodles & sauce two more times.
Cover with shredded cheese on top.
Bake in preheated oven at 425 degrees for 5 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: turkey salad
directions: Fold together whipping cream and mayonnaise.
Combine all ingredients.
Add the mayonnaise and whipping cream mixture to this.
Let mixture sit overnight or several hours before serving.

title: south of the border meatballs
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except salsa; blend well. Form into 1-inch balls.
In large skillet, brown meatballs on all sides; drain fat.
Add salsa to skillet.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: burrito bake
directions: Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inch.
Mix Bisquick, water and refried beans.
Spread in pie plate.
Mix salsa and beef.
Spread over bean mixture.
Spread cheese over beef.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Serve with lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream.

title: couch-potato munch
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Whisk together dressing mix, water and chili powder in a large bowl until blended.
Add remaining ingredients and toss until coated with seasonings.
Spread evenly in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until lightly toasted, stirring twice.
Cool completely in pan before packing into jars or containers.
Makes 7 cups.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil ingredients briskly for about 15 minutes or until caramel colored.
Remove from heat and stir in 2 teaspoons soda.
Pour onto 2 large well-buttered cookie sheets.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together.
Chill overnight, if you can wait that long.

title: date nut bars
directions: Sift
together	flour,	baking	powder and salt.
Cream butter and
sugar; add eggs one at a time and beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Gradually blend in dry ingredients, beating well
after
each	addition.
Fold in dates and nuts. Spread evenly
in a greased pan (7 x 11 x 1 1/2-inches).
Bake in	a moderate
oven
minutes.	When cool, cut into squares. (Can sprinkle top with 10x sugar.)

title: southern red rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Combine with rice, tomatoes, pepper, onions and margarine.
Place in casserole dish, cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spread pie filling in bottom of greased oblong pan. Sprinkle with lemon juice. Combine dry cake mix with nuts and melted butter. Sprinkle mixture over pie filling in pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, until golden brown. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: ragu easy pasta twist casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine cooked pasta with sauce.
Layer half the pasta mixture in 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Evenly spoon Ricotta or cottage cheese over pasta.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and spoon remaining pasta mixture over cheeses.
Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes or until heated. Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place apples in 9 x 13 glass pan. Add orange juice. Mix in medium bowl the flour, oats, sugar and cinnamon; mix well.
Mix in butter to make dry crumbly mix. Sprinkle over apples and bake 45 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Trim fat from meat.
Rub both sides of meat with flour mixture.
Pound both sides of meat with garlic.
Cut meat in strips about 1 1/2 x 1-inch.
Melt margarine, butter or Wesson oil in skillet or Dutch oven.
Lightly brown onion, then remove onion.
Place strips of meat in Dutch oven or skillet; brown well, turning fairly often.
Remove meat as it browns.
Add water; stir to dissolve brown particles in bottom of skillet.
This will form gravy.
Return onions, butter and meat to skillet or Dutch oven.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes; add mushroom soup.
Cover and let mixture simmer until mixture thickens and meat is tender.
Add a little water during cooking of meat if mixture gets too thick.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream.
tags: condensed undiluted cream of chicken soup

title: white mountain fudge
directions: Place milk, corn syrup, sugar and salt in a deep saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly, to a soft ball (238°).
Add margarine and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
With the back of a wooden spoon, work the hot fudge up the sides of the pan until mixture thickens. Add nuts.
Pour into well-greased pan.

title: cocoa cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar, cocoa and 1 teaspoon vanilla until light and fluffy. Add eggs. Blend well. Pour into crust. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven. Cool 15 minutes.

title: caramel apple spread
directions: Mix all ingredients with the mixer until softened.
Cut up fresh apples and use the caramel spread as a dip.

title: bambinos
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spread tomato paste on crackers; add a slice of pepperoni.
Top with piece of cheese.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until cheese is melted, 3 to 5 minutes.

title: no-cook divinity
directions: In a small bowl, mix the first four ingredients.
Beat on high speed with mixer until it peaks.
Put in a large bowl.
On slow speed, slowly add sugar.
Stir in nuts. Drop onto waxed paper by teaspoonful.
Leave until outside feels firm.
Turn over.
Let dry for 12 hours.
Store in airtight container.
tags: Betty Crocker fluffy white frosting mix

title: elegant company chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Pepper chicken.
Wrap slice of bacon around each breast.
Place a layer of dried beef in bottom of baking dish.
Arrange bacon-wrapped chicken on beef slices.
Cover with mixture of undiluted soup, sour cream and cream cheese. Cover dish tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Remove foil and bake additional 1/2 hour until lightly browned. Serve on hot rice.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Fry hamburger.
When done, mix in taco seasoning and beans. Cook until done.

title: squirrel cakes
directions: Boil squirrel in salt water, remove all good meat.
Grind bits of meat and blend with the bread crumbs, adding onions, ketchup and mashed potatoes.
Shape into small flat cakes.
Fry in hot oil.

title: crunchy chicken-cheese bake
directions: Place chicken in baking dish; top with cheese.
Stir soup and spread over cheese; top with tomato.
Combine margarine and stuffing.
Sprinkle over tomato.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes until chicken is done.
Serve over rice.
Garnish with fresh oregano.
Serves 8.
Prep time: 10 minutes.
Cook time: 25 minutes.

title: broccoli-cauliflower-carrot medley
directions: Steam or boil until tender; drain water.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place beans on bottom of casserole dish.
Crumble saltines over beans. Add mushrooms, onions and bell pepper. Cover with tomato sauce mixed with seasoning and top with cheese.
Cook in a 400° oven until bubbling, approximately 20 minutes.
A good weight watcher dish.

title: minestrone(vegetable soup)
directions: Soak the beans overnight in cold water.
Cut carrots, leek and celery root in small pieces.
Halve onion and slice in fine strips.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all except stuffing.
In a large buttered casserole dish, put 1/2 of stuffing, then squash mixture.
Place rest of stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 45 minutes to 1 hour according to oven.

title: rigatoni
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain.
Mix 3 cheeses together with egg.
Brown meat.
Add to sauce.
Put sauce in bottom of Pyrex dish.
Layer noodles, sauce and cheeses to top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Cook ground beef in a nonstick skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble; drain.
Stir meat into vegetable mixture. Reduce heat.
Add smoked sausage and simmer 20 minutes.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: mexican salad
directions: Prepare lettuce for salad.
Drain, wash and chill beans.
Add beans, tomatoes, onion, cheese and dressing to lettuce.
Chill 1 hour.
Just before serving, add chips and toss.
Serves 12.

title: better than sex cake
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, combine pineapple, sugar, pudding and coconut.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Using a wooden spoon handle, poke holes in warm cake.
Slowly pour pineapple mixture over cake, spreading evenly. Cool.
Spread topping evenly over cake and sprinkle with pecans.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients.
Spread loosely in 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir with spoon.
Press mixture against bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan; cool.

title: spicy horseradish sauce
directions: Thoroughly mix together the horseradish, salt, pepper, cayenne pepper and white vinegar.
Fold mixture into the whipped cream. Serve sauce with hot or cold roast beef and other meats.
Makes approximately 1 cup.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook ground chuck and onion in a Dutch oven, stirring until meat crumbles and is no longer pink.
Drain meat mixture; return to Dutch oven.
Stir in soup, diced tomato and green chilies and beans.
Layer half of tortillas evenly into 2 lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dishes.
Top each with 1/4 of meat mixture and 1/4 of cheese cubes.
Repeat layers with remaining tortillas, meat mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat the egg yolk and whites separately.
Combine egg yolks, milk, and fat.
Mix with dry ingredients, stirring only until the batter is smooth.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in a hot waffle baker.
Yield:
4 waffles.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Wipe okra with a damp towel.
Do not wash it, or it will make the okra too moist.
Cut off the stems and discard.
Slice the okra into thin rounds.
Meanwhile, cook three slices of bacon in a large pot to render the fat.
Remove the bacon and reserve for another use.
Add the okra rounds to the fat and cover.
Cook on a low fire for about 1 1/2 hours, stirring frequently.
Add tomato, onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Cook, covered, stirring frequently, for about 30 minutes, until vegetables have wilted and the okra has lost its slime.
Add stock and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer about two hours.

title: coca-cola roast
directions: Place roast in deep baking dish.
Cover with ketchup and pour Coke on top.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours until done.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat the egg, then add the salt and enough of the flour to make a very stiff dough.
Knead on a floured board for 3 or 4 minutes.
Then roll out in a thin sheet.
Cover with a towel and let stand about 20 minutes.
Then roll up as you would a jelly roll, cut into thin strips.
Unroll and lay out to dry thoroughly. Store until needed.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Add to pumpkin mixture and mix thoroughly.
Spread in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: quick "biscuit" muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix well (ingredients will be lumpy) approximately 25 strokes.
Place in muffin tins, 1/2 full.
Bake at 425° for approximately 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: branson potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, sour cream, cheese, onions, salt and pepper.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Top this mixture with corn flakes and melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add cheese over top of corn flakes and let stay in oven long enough to melt the cheese.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Put zucchini, butter and seasonings in skillet.
Cover; cook slowly 5 minutes.
Uncover; cook, turning slices until barely tender, about 5 minutes more.
Sprinkle with cheese; toss.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spicy franks
directions: Combine the currant jelly and prepared mustard in 4-cup glass measure cup.
Microwave on High for about 3 minutes or until jelly melts.
Beat well with rotary beater.
Cut each frank crosswise into 6 pieces.
Stir jelly mixture and continue cooking on High 4 to 5 minutes or until franks are hot.
Serve in chafing dish with toothpicks.

title: divinity
directions: Going to the outdoor theatre in Kernville.
We sat on bleachers.
It was wonderful; the cool night air, the bright stars, etc.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients together first, then add next five. Bake in Bundt pan at 350° until done.
Let cool.

title: melba delight
directions: Mix together & bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Let cool.

title: round steak casserole
directions: Slice round steak into serving sizes.
Layer sliced steak, sliced onion and sliced steak to top of casserole.
Add salt and pepper to each layer.
Add about 1/2 cup water.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° until tender.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix together.
Slowly add milk, stirring to mix.
Heat and stir until thickened, 1 to 2 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla. Pour into jar and refrigerate.
Reheat warm to serve.
Serve over ice cream or cake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Pour into a big casserole dish; sprinkle in 1 cup uncooked rice.
Lay cut up chicken on top.
Mix soups and water together.
Pour on top of chicken and rice.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Lightly brown the onions and celery in butter; then add the soups
and
cheese.
Stir
until
all is mixed and melted. Add the broccoli and 1 cup rice and stir well.
Line casserole (2 quart size) with the two remaining cups of rice.
Then pour broccoli mixture in the
middle.
Heat
for 20 minutes at 350° or until bubbling.
This
also freezes well for use at a later date.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix beef, onion, salt, milk, cracker crumbs, egg and ginger together and form into small balls and brown in 1 tablespoon shortening.
Mix cornstarch, sugar and pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook until mixture boils.
Pour over meatballs; add pineapple and green pepper.
Heat and serve.

title: homemade bailey's
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add 1 teaspoon instant coffee to 1/4 cup of mixed ingredients and warm.
Enjoy!

title: cabbage rolls(golabki)
directions: Remove core from whole head of cabbage with a sharp knife. Scald the cabbage in boiling water. Remove
a few leaves at a time as they wilt.
Cool before using.

title: babe ruth bars
directions: Mix oatmeal, syrup and brown sugar. Melt butter and pour over oatmeal. Mix well. Add the 1/4 cup chunky peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well and pat into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 12 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: congealed strawberry sour cream salad
directions: In large mixing bowl, dissolve Jell-O into the boiling water. Add crushed pineapple, strawberries, bananas and nuts.
In a large dish, pour 1/2 of the mixture and place in refrigerator to congeal.
When this is congealed, spread sour cream over top and add remaining 1/2 mixture.
Congeal.
Makes 8 cups.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Slice the kielbasa; brown in pan.
Drain pineapple (reserving juice).
Place juice in with the kielbasa.
Cut pineapple chunks in half.
Add sugar to first mixture; bring to a boil.
Add cranberry sauce; mix well, then add cornstarch to thicken (you may need more cornstarch).
Add vinegar to taste.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Tastes better if made the day before.

title: yummy chicken casserole
