directions: In saucepan, combine soups, sour cream, cheese and milk.
Heat over medium heat until cheese melts and sauce is smooth and creamy.
Place noodles, chicken and peas in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour sauce over noodles and mix lightly.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: 4 step pudding cake
directions: Mix well and spread over second layer.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice pretty thin.
Chop onions and bell peppers into cucumbers.
Put 1/2 cup salt into this.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Drain off water after 3 hours.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices in large preserving kettle and bring to a boil. Add drained cucumbers and heat through.
(Do not boil them.)
Pack while hot into hot jars and seal at once.

title: creamy chicken 'n noodles
directions: In Dutch oven on stove, combine chicken broth and diced onion to boil.
Add frozen noodles; cook on medium heat for 10 minutes. Add the cream of chicken soup; stir if needed.
Add water to your consistency desired.
Cook for 1 hour on low heat.
Eat with mashed potatoes or over rice; garnish with parsley flakes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Place pumpkin on large cookie sheet or in roaster.
Bake 2 hours or more at 350°.
Scoop out and freeze or can.
If stringy, run through food mill.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except corn flakes.
Pour into a 9x13 inch casserole dish and top with crushed corn flakes.
Pour margarine over top.
Bake uncovered at 300 degrees for 1 hour.
A few dashes of tabasco sauce gives it some spice.

title: bavarian brownies
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, milk, margarine and egg.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. (Batter will be very thick.)
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: date cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and let stand.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with fried onions and bake for 5 minutes longer.

title: salad dressing for green salad
directions: Blend together well.
Chill.
Shake before pouring over salad greens.

title: irish cream
directions: Mix in order given. Refrigerate. Keeps up to 4 weeks.

title: steak and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In broiler pan, place 1/2 the butter on bottom and add 1/2 of the Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 the A.1. sauce.
Sprinkle 1/2 the garlic powder and place steak in the center of the pan.
Slice potatoes around the steak.
Pour the other half of the remaining ingredients over steak and potatoes. Cover with aluminum foil; bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: crock pot roast
directions: Place half of the onion in bottom of roast.
Rub the roast with the soup mix.
Place roast in pot and top with remaining onion.
Cover and cook on low heat for at least 12 hours.
You may add carrots or potatoes to bottom of roast if desired so they will absorb the juices.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in large amount of boiling water until tender; drain and rinse.
Add remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese, and beat until well mixed.
Layer half the noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; spread with half Ricotta filling.
Add half the Mozzarella cheese and half the meat sauce.
Repeat.
Bake at 370° about 30 minutes (or assemble early and refrigerate, then bake 45 minutes).
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: pineapple 7-up cake
directions: Mix in large bowl cake mix, pudding mix and 7-Up; beat, then add eggs and Wesson oil.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Bake at 325° for 22 or 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not bake yet.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: In blender, place cottage cheese and 1/2 cup berries.
Blend until smooth.
Make jello according to package.
Pour half the jello in a small pan.
Arrange strawberries in jello and refrigerate in freezer until jello sets.
To the cheese in the blender, add the rest of the jello and the sweetener.
Blend. When the jello in the pan has set, spoon the cheese mixture over and smooth.
Refrigerate until set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine ingredients, place in buttered baking dish. Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Bring oleo to room temperature.
Add all ingredients.
Roll out in small balls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: uncle john's peanut brittle
directions: Premeasure soda and peanuts; set aside for use.
Mix sugar, syrup and water together in saucepan.
Stir and cook continuously until mixture threads, or reaches hard crack on a candy thermometer.
Add peanuts 1/2 cup at a time; stir 20 to 30 seconds. Add next portion of peanuts.
Cook slowly until mixture turns light brown and peanuts smell done.
Do not overcook.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and butter.
Stir.
Add salt and soda.
Stir quickly and thoroughly.
Mixture will foam.
Pour onto a cookie sheet and don't touch for 30 minutes.
Use hot pads whenever necessary.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Break bread into pieces and put into dish; sprinkle the cheese, sausage and dry
mustard over bread.
Mix the eggs and milk and pour over mixture.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: little pizzas
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Melt cheese in a saucepan with tomato sauce.
Add cooked sausage to melted cheese and mix.
Spoon mixture onto rye bread.
Bake on a cookie sheet for 5 to 7 minutes at 350°.

title: salad
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar and water to a boil.
Let cool.
Add onion, tomato, bell pepper, little sugar and kraut.

title: cherry torte
directions: Mix flour and 2 tablespoons sugar; cut in margarine.
Press into a 9 x 6-inch pan; bake in hot (400°) oven until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Make pudding as directed on package.
When cool, but not set, spread on crust.
Heat cherries.
Add sugar mixed with cornstarch; stir constantly until thickened.
Cool slightly; spread on top of pudding.
Top with whipped cream. Serves 8.

title: sweet onion pie
directions: Saute sweet onions in oleo until tender.
Arrange in pastry shell.
Beat eggs slightly, add cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over onions.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes, or until knife comes out clean and pie is well-browned.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: egg salad
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator.
Use for sandwiches or on crackers.

title: sausage bread
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter. Slice top off bread long ways. Take out middle and make crumbs. Cook sausage; drain. Mix sausage and next 4 ingredients real good. Put 1/2 cheese in bottom of bread, then sausage mixture, topping with rest of cheese. Put top back on bread; wrap in foil. Bake 30 minutes in 315° oven.

title: broccoli two cheese casserole(a country thanksgiving at the lamars)
directions: To prepare:
Cook broccoli according to package directions, reducing cooking time by 3 minutes; drain and spread evenly in two greased 1-1/2 quart casserole dishes.
In a large skillet, add flour slowly to butter, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth.
Add remaining ingredients except bread crumbs, stirring constantly until smooth.
Pour mixture over broccoli, sprinkle bread crumbs over top and bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until sauce is bubbly and crumbs are browned.

title: corn souffle
directions: Cook your vegetable in saucepan on slow boil until tender. Drain and place in casserole dish. Dot with butter or margarine. Place sandwich cheese over top of vegetable to cover.
Place in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: good raisin pie
directions: Pour boiling water over the raisins. Cover 5 minutes, then drain.
Cook the pudding and milk until thick; cool. Add the Cool Whip, raisins and lemon juice.
Pour into baked pie shell. Top with Cool Whip to serve.

title: wendy's rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water. Mix milk, sugar, salt, eggs, half of flour and yeast in a bowl. Add shortening and beat on high for 5 minutes. Add remaining flour and stir with a spoon until mixed. Put dough into a greased bowl and place in the refrigerator overnight.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat 1/2 cup chocolate chips and butter until melted.
Mix baking mix, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Bake 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows, nuts and remaining chips. Bake until brown.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: sylvia's eclair cake
directions: Heat water and margarine to a boil.
Turn heat down.
Stir in flour while it is still boiling.
Stir until mixed.
Remove from heat and add eggs one at a time.
Beat until smooth, will be sticky.
Using a knife evenly spread mixture into a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Press down air bubbles in center, leaving "crust" around edge.

title: wyatt's cafeteria baked eggplant
directions: Cut peeled eggplant into 1-inch cubes and soak in salt water in refrigerator overnight.
Drain and place in a saucepan.
Cover with water and simmer until tender.
Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Saute onions, green peppers and celery in melted butter for about 15 minutes.
Combine vegetables and bread crumbs.
Add eggs, pimiento and seasonings.
Blend well.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar with an electric mixer.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Mix baking powder with flour; add 1 cup at a time, mixing after each addition.
The dough will be very stiff; blend last.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients.
Turn mixture on counter or cutting board and knead by hand for 5 minutes or until smooth.
Roll on floured surface and cut with favorite cutters.
Remove and cool.
Make faces with markers or paint with acrylic paints.
Store in a cool dry place.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Warm cocoa and sugar in saucepan until it feels like warm sand.
Cut in butter.
Add milk and bring to boil; cook about 3 to 5 minutes.
Will keep in fridge for about 3 weeks.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Blend dry ingredients in bowl, add shortening, water and applesauce.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed over 300 strokes by hand.
Add 2 eggs, beat 2 more minutes. Stir in nuts and add raisins.
Pour into pan. Bake until done, about 1 hour.
Cool and frost with favorite maple frosting if desired.

title: oven stew
directions: Put stew meat, potatoes, onion, celery and carrots in a large pan with lid or Dutch oven.
Mix salt, sugar, tapioca, tomato juice and beef bouillon.
Pour this mixture over stew and bake covered for 4 hours at 250°.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Add tomatoes, beans and corn.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine ingredients in boiler. Cook on low heat. Stir constantly until thick. Pour into baked pie shell. Add Meringue to pie.

title: banana bread
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan and assemble ingredients. Mix shortening, sugar and bananas.
Add egg and beat well. Combine dry ingredients to banana mixture.
Add vanilla and buttermilk. Turn batter into loaf pan and bake 1 hour.

title: tomato dumplins
directions: Place biscuits in a 10 inch round baking pan. Put tomatoes in a bowl, add sugar and stir well. Pour tomatoes and sugar mixture over biscuits. Bake in oven at 400 degrees for 20-25 minutes.

title: brigadeiros
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Over a low flame, stir until mixture thickens and leaves the bottom of pan.
Cool slightly. Roll into small balls, then roll in chocolate confetti.
Put into individual candy paper cups.

title: dessert graham torte
directions: REMOVE PAPER FROM CAN. Cover can completely with water in charge saucepan. Boil gently for 3 hours, always keeping can covered with water. Cool can and open; the milk turns into caramel. Unwrap crackers from inner paper and spread caramel between each layer of crackers. There should be 3 blocks of crackers as they come from box. Refrigerate after rewrapping. Slice and serve.

title: new orleans spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Add paprika, pepper, salt, tomato soup and mushroom soup.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add cheese and cook 15 minutes.
Add mushrooms and spaghetti.
Makes a lot.

title: pineapple-cheese casserole
directions: Cover with crushed Ritz crackers after mixing all ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish.
Spoon 1/2 stick melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together, then place in pie shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix cream cheese with a mixer until smooth.
Drain the liquid from the salsa but reserve.
Add the salsa to the cream cheese and mix.
If consistency is not right, add some of the remaining liquid.
Mound the mixture on a serving plate.
Top with lettuce, tomato, cheese and olives.
Serve with taco chips.

title: brown hamburger stew
directions: Mix hamburger meat with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in fat, stirring as needed.
Drain off fat.
Add water and carrots.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add other vegetables and simmer until crisp-tender, about 10 minutes.
Add tomato juice; heat through and serve.
Makes 6 servings of 1 1/2 cups each.

title: doc's barbecue sauce
directions: Boil for 1 minute the first 5 ingredients.
Mix beans, onion and pimento in dish.
Pour liquid over beans.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put thinly sliced cucumber, onion and pepper in bowl.
Heat vinegar, sugar and salt to boiling point and cool.
Add celery and mustard seed to vinegar while lukewarm.
Pour over the cucumbers, peppers and onions.
Mix well.
Keep in refrigerator for 6 days, mixing well every day.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin ice cream
directions: Can use pumpkin pie spice.

title: pecan crisp cookies
directions: Sift flour.
Add baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream margarine.
Add sugar and well beaten eggs.
Combine dry ingredients.
Blend well. Shape in a 3 inch roll.
Wrap in wax paper; chill one hour.
Cut the roll into thin slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a hot 350° oven for 5 to 8 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Stir with wire whisk to remove lumps.
Add oil and next 3 ingredients.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Bake in greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes on wire rack.
Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pea casserole
directions: Bake
at
375° until bubbly, then put one can of French fried onion rings on top.
Place back in oven until rings are brown.

title: low-fat potato skins
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Scrub potatoes well; cut lengthwise into 6 wedges and dry on paper towel.
In a large bowl, toss potato spears with olive oil until well covered.
Spread potatoes on a baking sheet; dust with paprika and bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until fork-tender.
Scrumptious eating; so good 2 people can eat in no time.

title: upside-down pear gingerbread cake
directions: Melt butter in an 8-inch square baking dish; stir in sugar. Sprinkle cherries over butter and sugar.
Dip pear slices in juice to prevent darkening.
Arrange pear slices in rows over cherries; set aside.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, saute onion, celery and broccoli in butter or margarine for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in soup, milk and cheese spread until smooth.
Pour rice in a greased casserole dish and pour cheese mixture over rice but do not stir. Bake uncovered at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: powder puffs
directions: Combine flour, cream of tartar and baking soda.
In separate bowl, blend powdered sugar, shortening, egg, vanilla and nuts. Blend with flour mixture.
Drop on cookie sheet and press with fork (like peanut butter cookies).
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes until set.
Do not brown.
Dust with powdered sugar when cooled.

title: spuds 'ala elegant
directions: Blend cream cheese into mashed potatoes.
Add egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Bake in 1-quart casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine onion, broccoli, eggs, margarine, cottage cheese and salt in bowl; mix well.
Stir in muffin mix just until moistened. Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish, well-greased.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown (check to make sure the bread is done).
May take longer than 20 minutes.
Cool; turn from pan and slice.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Layer in order ingredients, breaking up lumps in cake mix. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until browned.

title: baked apples
directions: Core out each apple, trying not to cut through bottom, and peel just around top (around 1/2-inch).
Add to each apple a teaspoon of butter, a teaspoon of brown sugar and a shake each of nutmeg and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour (maybe more, until soft).
Serve in bowls.

title: hamburger rolls with tomatoes
directions: Mix meat with salt, pepper and water.
Form into barrel shaped rolls.
Dip into egg which has been beaten with the 1 tablespoon milk.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Heat shortening in heavy skillet and brown rolls on all sides.
Rub tomatoes through sieve and pour over rolls.
Add onion; cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes, turning occasionally.
Serve hot with the tomato sauce poured over the rolls.
Makes 5 servings.

title: frances' delicious turkey
directions: Put turkey into deep pot with a lid.
Mix together cream of mushroom soup and chicken soup; spread over chicken parts.
Cover; cook at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, depending on amount of turkey. Maybe 2 hours.
Serve hot.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in unbaked pastry shell 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced tea *
directions: Place cloves, cinnamon and lemon juice in water.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Add tea bags and brew for 15 minutes.
Sweeten to taste. Add pineapple juice and orange juice.
When serving, heat just to boil.
Add ginger ale.
Serve immediately.

title: grandma hicks' tea cakes
directions: Mix as biscuit dough.
Roll out on floured board and cut with small cutter.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350°.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Stir all ingredients together until smooth.
Drop heaping tablespoons onto greased pan.
Bake in 450° oven until brown, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cherry blinks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix margarine, sugar and egg.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Blend dry ingredients together; stir in.
Mix in dates and nuts.
Drop dough by teaspoon into cornflakes.
Roll gently so dough is completely covered in cornflakes.
Place about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Top with a piece of cherry.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until no imprint remains when touched.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: cookie pie crust and filling
directions: Mix flour and confectioners sugar well by hand. Add the butter and use pastry blender or fork and mix until mixture resembles cornmeal. Chill 30 minutes, then turn into 9-inch tart or pie pan, pressing firmly. Bake in preheated 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly golden. Cool.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover well with aluminum foil.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Stir once or twice during the last hour.
Serve with noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tea cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening with sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well; combine with dry ingredients. Roll out on floured surface.
Roll to 1/8.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar (colored if desired).
Bake approximately 8 minutes at 425°.
Do not overbake.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Fully cook roast and tear into small pieces, removing fat and bone.
Place in large skillet.
Add garlic salt, vinegar, ketchup and hot sauce.
Place on stove and simmer about 15 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Freezes well for later use.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook in iron skillet, then put in crock-pot to keep it warm.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix together well.
Roll out on floured board.
Knead 10 times.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 450° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 26 biscuits.

title: butterscotch cream cheese bars
directions: Melt morsels and butter in medium heavy saucepan over lowest possible heat, stirring constantly, until smooth. Stir in crumbs and walnuts. Reserve 2 cups crumb mixture for topping. Press remaining mixture into ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 12 minutes.

title: hungarian stuffed cabbage
directions: Remove core from cabbage.
Separate the leaves and boil them uncovered for 5 minutes or until soft enough to roll.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Combine in a bowl the hamburger, onion, rice, salt and pepper.
Shape into medium-sized balls.
Place in center of cabbage leaf.
Roll to enclose meat.
Shred remainder of cabbage mix with sauerkraut and sliced onion.
Place a layer of shredded cabbage sauerkraut in the bottom of large pot.
Place rolled stuffed cabbage in a layer.
Cover with shredded cabbage sauerkraut.
Place remaining rolled stuffed cabbage and cover with remaining cabbage sauerkraut.
Combine tomato paste, liquid reserved from cabbage and sugar.
Pour over layered rolls and, if necessary, add enough water to just cover cabbage.
Cover.
Bring to a boil and lower flame to simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until well done.

title: mexican cheese ball
directions: Combine water and dip mix in a small bowl; stir well and set aside.
Combine cheese, chilies and pimiento; stir well.
Add mayonnaise, butter, red pepper and dip mix; stir well.
Chill and shape into a ball; sprinkle with additional red pepper.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Yield: 4 cups.

title: nachos
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan combine soup and salsa.
Heat through over low heat, stirring often.
Pour over chips.
Top with tomato, green onions, olives and peppers.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Break spaghetti into boiling chicken broth and cook until tender.
Add onions and celery and cook with spaghetti the last minutes to soften.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to spaghetti. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, covered.
For a topping use some cheese.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix last 6 ingredients until sugar is completely dissolved. Pour over bean mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Drain before serving.

title: quick casserole
directions: Fry enough sausage to cover bottom of baking dish.
Drain grease off of sausage.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over the sausage.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: taco platter
directions: Mix the bean dip, sour cream, mayonnaise and seasoning mix together.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and spread over bean mix.
Layer as listed on a platter.
Serve with tortillas.

title: mother's relish mold
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve syrup and add water to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Dissolve gelatin and sugar in the hot water.
Add pineapple syrup and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Add fruits, celery and nuts.
Chill in 5-cup ring mold or a pretty glass bowl overnight.
Of course, you won't need to unmold the relish from the glass bowl.
Individual molds are good if you prefer.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.
Excellent served with cornmeal dressing instead of cranberry sauce.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Crumble one layer of cake and put in large glass bowl. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup Kahlua.
Spread one container of Cool Whip over cake.
Sprinkle with half of crushed Heath bars.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes; boil until tender.
Mash potatoes, adding a little milk for a creamy consistency.
Add butter, cream cheese, sour cream, onion, salt, and pepper.
Mix until smooth. Pour into a buttered 9 x 13 inch baking dish; sprinkle with parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350 degrees until hot.

title: reese's cup cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat until creamy.
Stir in dry ingredients until blended.
Roll dough in balls.
Press into mini muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately press one peanut butter cup into each hot cookie.
Cool slightly and remove from tins.

title: strawberries with vanilla pudding dip
directions: Whisk together vanilla pudding mix and milk until well blended. Stir in next 3 ingredients, chill 2 hours. Garnish if desired. Serve with strawberries as a dip.

title: honey oat bran bars
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, toss together cereal, nuts and raisins; set aside.
In 2-quart saucepan, combine margarine, honey and brown sugar.
Stirring constantly, bring to a full boil over medium heat and boil 5 minutes.
Pour over cereal mixture; toss to coat well.
Press evenly into prepared pan.
Let stand 1 hour.
Cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 24.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and butter in top of double boiler. Cream sugar and eggs. Mix with candy and butter mixture (after it has cooled). Cream well. Add dry ingredients and milk, vanilla and pecans. Beat until well mixed. Pour into floured and greased Bundt pan. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: old fashioned minestrone
directions: In an 8-quart Dutch oven over medium heat, in hot salad oil, cook onions, carrots, celery, potatoes, and green beans about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add water, cabbage, spinach, tomatoes (cut up) and liquid, zucchini, bouillon and salt.
Stir well and bring just to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in white and red kidney beans; cook 15 minutes longer or until soup is slightly thickened.
Parmesan cheese can be sprinkled on individual servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare rotini according to the package directions; drain. In a large bowl, combine rotini, tuna, cucumber, tomato, celery, green pepper and onions.
In a small bowl, blend together Italian dressing, mayonnaise, mustard and seasonings.
Add to salad mixture.
Toss to coat.
Cover and chill.
Toss gently before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli almond angel hair pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain and rinse with cool water.
Combine oil, vinegar, sesame oil and garlic in a jar and mix well.
Toss pasta and dressing.
Add bacon, almonds, onions and cheese.
Chill overnight.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Place beans in sieve and rinse with cold water; drain. Combine beans, celery, green pepper, onion, pineapple, mayonnaise, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Mix until blended.
Pile into lettuce-lined bowl or platter.
Garnish top with olives, eggs and tomato.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Roast pork in a 325° oven until done.
Cool and cut into 2-inch pieces.
Cover hen in water; stew for 2 hours (reserve broth). Cool and cut chicken into 2-inch pieces.
Grind by hand or with processor the pork and chicken coarsely.
Combine ground pork and chicken, tomatoes, tomato sauce, onion, green pepper, vinegar and sugar in large Dutch oven.
Simmer one hour.
Combine water and flour, stirring until dissolved.
Stir into meat mixture.
Stir in salt, pepper and hot sauce.
Cook over medium heat for 30 minutes. Add water as needed.
Add corn.
Cook an additional 10 minutes. Serves 14 to 16.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles, drain and place in casserole dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix in drained tuna, cheese, soup and milk with noodles.
Mix until at a creamy texture (add more milk if needed). Add crushed crackers to the top and cover.
Cook for 45 minutes or until hot in the center.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: broccoli with cheese sauce
directions: Cook cheese and milk in double boiler or microwave until smooth.
Add vinegar and seasoning.
Cook broccoli until tender. Drain.
Serve with cheese sauce.

title: garlic smashed potatoes with bacon
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes until soft enough to hand mash.
While potatoes boil, fry bacon and crumble loosely.
Drain potatoes and put in large bowl to mash.
Add butter and pressed garlic.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mash with hand masher to preferred consistency.
Fold in crumbled bacon.
Serve!

title: quick chicken and mushrooms
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Take 2 tablespoons melted margarine with the brown sugar, nuts and water and place in the bottom of 10-inch Bundt pan.
Mix white sugar and cinnamon together.
Dip each biscuit lightly in rest of melted butter, then into sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Place each biscuit on end in Bundt pan; pinch tips or sides of biscuit together slightly.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
After baking turn biscuit ring out onto plate.
Serve immediately (or cool and reheat later).
Makes 10 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange together.
Add nuts, celery, fruit and sugar.
Make jello and add mixture after the jello has cooled.
Mold. Good served with turkey or Christmas morning brunch.

title: cracker crumb chicken
directions: Cut chicken in small 2 x 2-inch pieces.
Dip in butter; roll in cracker crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet lined with foil.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes, turning once.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Bring margarine, water and cocoa to boil.
Combine eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla. Add boiled mixture to egg mixture.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 12 x 18-inch pan.
I use electric beaters on low speed to blend in all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: corn bubble bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, blend 2 cups flour, sugar, salt, cornmeal and yeast.
Combine water, milk and shortening.
Heat to lukewarm.
Pour into dry ingredients and blend.
Continue adding flour until dough is moderately stiff.
Turn onto floured surface. Knead dough until smooth and elastic, about 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl to rise until double.
Punch down.
Divide the dough into 32 small pieces.
(The easiest way is to divide it with a knife successively into 2-4-8-16-32 pieces.)
Roll the pieces into balls.
Place half the balls in the bottom of a well-greased tube cake pan (angel food cake pan).
The pieces will not necessarily touch.
Brush with half of melted butter.
Place remaining pieces in a layer on top of first layer.
Brush with remaining melted butter.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Turn out of pan and tap bottom crust.
If it sounds hollow, it's done.
If not, return to oven a few more minutes. Cool on rack.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: dessert salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Add cherries and nuts and mix together.
Sprinkle dry jello over mixture, toss well and chill.
Serve.

title: eleanor's sausage strata
directions: Butter a 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Place bread to fit on bottom.
Next, combine sausage with remaining ingredients; place on bread crumbs and top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Great as an appetizer or as part of a luncheon.

title: ground beef hoover style
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 20 minutes.

title: mustard dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in a jar.
Cover and shake well to blend. Shake again just before serving.
Makes 3/4 cup dressing.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream first four ingredients in medium-sized bowl.
Blend the milk, pudding and Cool Whip in large bowl.
After all is blended, add cheese mixture and blend well.
Put lid from Cool Whip in bottom of 8 or 9-inch new plastic flowerpot (or one kept specifically for this recipe).
Layer in crushed cookies-pudding mixture, finishing off with cookies on top.
Garnish with 6-inch bouquet of plastic flowers (3 to 4 sprigs).
Chill 6 hours or overnight.
Use a garden trowel as a serving spoon.
(I use half this recipe.)

title: 3 hour bread
directions: Put margarine, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
Pour scalding water or milk over this and add 1 cup flour.
When slightly cooled, add yeast dissolved in water.
Add 3 cups flour, eggs and powdered milk.
Mix well.
Add 2 1/2 to 3 cups flour and mix well.
Turn out on floured cloth and let rest 10 minutes.
Knead for 10 minutes. Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise 30 minutes.
Turn over in bowl and let rise 30 more minutes.
Shape into loaves and let rise 20 minutes.
Bake for 25 minutes at 425°.

title: blueberry crumble
directions: Put blueberries in 8-inch shallow dish and sprinkle with lemon juice and granulated sugar.
Combine rest of ingredients in bowl and mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: moldy mice
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place butter and sugar in a medium size bowl and mix until blended.
Stir in vanilla.
In a second bowl, mix nuts and flour.
Add flour mixture to butter mixture and mix until well blended.
Shape a rounded teaspoonful into small "mice" about thumb size.
Place about one-inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes until cookies are lightly browned. Remove from oven and cool slightly.
While cookies are still warm, roll in confectioners sugar to coat thoroughly and place on a wire cake rack to cool completely.
Store in an airtight container. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: cream of chicken meat loaf
directions: Combine in a large bowl ground beef, eggs, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Finely chop green pepper and onion.
Add to ground beef mixture.
Add 1/2 can of cream of chicken soup.
Mix well.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Place all ingredients into bowl; beat until well blended. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: syrian bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Keep adding flour until dough is no longer sticky.
Roll dough into thin sheets.
Place in cookie pan.
Dot with knife.
Bake at 450° until brown.
Watch closely.
Remove from oven and rub entire sheet with butter. Sprinkle on garlic powder or salt.
Cut into squares.
(This is good with soup or stew.)

title: bacon sausage quiche(easy)
directions: Cook sausage (cut up) and steam broccoli.
Cut up broccoli. Line uncooked pie crust with sausage and broccoli.
Mix together half and half, sour cream and eggs.
Pour over sausage and broccoli in pie shell.
Sprinkle grated onion and grated cheese over top of quiche.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375°.
Easy.

title: quick sausage stroganoff
directions: Brown sausage, onion and green pepper in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Pour off any fat.
Lower temperature.
Combine tomatoes, sour cream, water and seasonings; stir into meat mixture.
Gently stir in noodles. Cover pan and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes or until noodles are tender, stirring occasionally.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: rice custard pudding
directions: Mix raisins and rice and place in 8-inch buttered baking dish. Mix together the remaining ingredients and pour over the rice and raisins.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Set baking dish in pan of water and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven or until firm.

title: potetsuppe(potato soup, in case you hadn't guessed!)
directions: Grandma lived long before "fat-free" but she didn't like fat in her soups!

title: pie filling(basic)
directions: Mix sugar, flour, egg yolks and milk. Cook over low heat until mixture starts to bubble.
Cook until thick; remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell. Top with meringue (made from egg whites) and brown lightly.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; rinse well with cold water.
Add pepper, onion and celery.
Toss
well.
Add
cheese.
Mix
oil, sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise well.
Pour over macaroni and refrigerate.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Make white sauce with margarine, flour, milk and seasonings. Stir in mayonnaise to mix smooth.
Add spaghetti, turkey, peas (if desired) and 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese.
Mix lightly and pour into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/3 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broiled fish
directions: Place fish in skillet.
Sprinkle with seafood seasoning to taste.
Add Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, water and peppers. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer on low for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: the best carrot cake
directions: Grate carrots in a food processor; use fine grate.
Set aside. Mix together the eggs (well beaten), sugar, gradually and stir in salad oil.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to first mixture; mix well.
Add 2 teaspoons of vanilla; stir in carrots.
Bake in well-greased and floured glass pan (9 x 13-inch) for 1 hour at 350°.

title: auntie joe's cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce.
When partially set, stir and add other ingredients.
Chill.
Serve. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: potato ratatouille
directions: Fry bacon; remove, crumble and set aside.
Add oil to the pan and heat.
Add onion slices and garlic and saute until soft.
Next, add the potatoes, green beans, zucchini and tomatoes.
Sprinkle the crumbled bacon, salt, pepper, basil and parsley over the vegetables and stir a few times.
Cover and simmer 35 to 45 minutes, stirring gently occasionally until all vegetables are tender.
You will need a very large frying pan for this or an electric skillet or divide the recipe and cook in two smaller frying pans.
This will serve 6 to 8 people.
It is also delicious when baked.

title: russell stover turtles
directions: Melt caramels in double boiler.
Add milk and pecans.
Drop on buttered cookie sheet.
Chill 3 hours or overnight.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip with toothpick into chocolate mixture.

title: chili sauce
directions: Cook for 4 or 5 hours until thick.

title: rice hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger, season with salt and onion salt. Cook rice until almost done. Put rice in casserole and add corn, hamburger and soup. Dot with butter and bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart baking dish.
Combine flour, sugar and milk.
Pour in dish with butter.
Pour the peeled peach slices over batter; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour, oatmeal, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Press 1/2 of this crumb mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pie filling on top. Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: won ton soup
directions: Combine pork or chicken, green onions, ginger, salt, soy sauce and sesame oil; mix well.
Place 1 tablespoon of mixture in middle of wrapper.
Wet the outer edges of wrapper with water and close edges together.
Boil 5 cups of water and add broth, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Boil water in another pan and add won tons. When won tons come up to the surface, scoop them with a strainer and put them in a soup bowl.
Pour broth over them to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and curry.
Squeeze lemon over broccoli in casserole dish.
Place mixture over top of broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let sauce bubble.
Top with cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: In a large saucepan, heat the pumpkin puree, milk, butter and honey.
Combine the light brown sugar, salt, marjoram, cinnamon, mace and pepper.
Stir them into the pumpkin-milk mixture.
Heat slowly, stirring to the simmering point.
Do not boil.
Add orange juice, a little at a time, stirring constantly.
Serve hot.
Yields 32 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, milk, sugar and baking powder to make batter.
Pour in a baking dish and stir butter and batter slightly.
Pour fruit in middle of batter and bake at 350° until golden brown.
Serve with nondairy topping or ice cream.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: Lightly spoon flour into a measuring cup; level off.
Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl, blend at low speed until fine crumbs form.
Stir in pecans.
Press 2 3/4 cups mixture into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Sift together in a 9-inch square pan the flour, sugar, cocoa and salt.
Into 3 holes made in the dry ingredients, add the oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour the water over everything.
Mix well with fork.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread into small pieces.
Add onion, green peppers, butter, eggs, turkey meat and salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Moisten with stock or water.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: 24 hour lettuce salad
directions: Shred lettuce in a large flat serving dish or bowl.
Sprinkle over top next 3 ingredients in layers.
Break peas apart and sprinkle over while frozen.
Spread mayo like frosting over the top.
Sprinkle on sugar and enough grated cheese to completely cover the top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, top with bacon, tomatoes, eggs and parsley.
Serves 12.

title: best company pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and leave whole. Pour boiling water over them and let stand overnight.

title: teriyaki chicken(low-fat)
directions: Combine liquids and stir in brown sugar until dissolved. Marinate chicken in sauce for 1 to 3 hours.
Broil or grill, turning at least once until done.

title: klinke's banana-bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, bran, soda, raisins, nuts and cinnamon.
In another bowl, beat eggs.
Add applesauce, banana, milk, honey and vanilla.
Mix wet and dry ingredients together; hand mix until just blended.
Spoon into muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Yields 18 jumbo muffins or 24 regular size.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon (keep dry).

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Rinse peas and add 1 quart of water.
Heat to boiling and let stand 2 hours.
Put ham hock in 1 quart of water and simmer 1 hour.
Add ham hock in cooking liquid with onion, salt and Tabasco to peas.
Cover.
Cook 2 hours until tender.
Remove meat from bone.
Return to peas.
Yields 8 servings.
Has 250 calories.

title: shirley's cherry jello
directions: Bring water and cherry pie filling to a boil.
Add jello, pineapple and pop.
Chill.

title: apricot bars
directions: You
may
cream butter, sugar, egg; add dry ingredients in usual
manner
or
mix
with
pastry blender as you do pie crust. (I	cut the sugar into the oleo with a fork and knife, then add the other ingredients, except preserves; it's best if you
don't get the mixture creamy, just crumbly.) Reserve 3/4 cup
mix
for topping.
Grease
and
flour
x 13-inch pan. Spread
or	pat mix into pan.
Spread with apricot preserves. Crumble
or
spread 3/4 cup reserved mix on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° (do not overbake).

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix together butter, brown sugar and flour as for pie crust. Take out one cup for top of cake.
To rest of mixture, add egg, vanilla, sour milk, baking soda and salt.
Use spoon or fork to mix.
Don't overmix.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle cup of reserved crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Cool.
Drizzle with powdered sugar frosting, if desired.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Hollow out one loaf for serving dip and cube second loaf for dipping.

title: honey milk balls
directions: Mix peanut butter with your choice of honey syrup, molasses or jelly.
Add dry milk a little at a time.
Mix well after each addition.
Form into small balls, about 3/4 across, using your hands.
Roll the balls in crushed flakes.
Chill until firm. Makes small balls.

title: taco casserole
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef.
When done, add beans, taco sauce, tomato sauce and garlic salt; heat.
Coarsely crush chips in casserole dish.
Layer meat on top, then layer sour cream on top of meat, then onions, tomatoes and cheese.

title: pita crisps(makes 48)
directions: Cut around edge of pita bread to make 2 halves.
Spread butter on inside of both halves.
Sprinkle each half with garlic powder. Separate halves into 3 groups.
Top the first group with desired amount oregano, the second with tarragon and the third with dill. Sprinkle each pita with Romano cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: everyone's favorite hot cakes
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls into ungreased frying pan over medium-high heat.
Turn when bubbly on top.
Serve with your favorite syrup.
Absolutely delicious.

title: frosty spiced tea
directions: In a small saucepan combine the 3/4 cup water with sugar, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Strain to remove spices.

title: chop suey noodle casserole
directions: Cook meat, onions, green pepper and celery in pan for a little while.
Add chicken and mushroom soups.
Simmer slowly for approximately 30 minutes.
Add can of whole corn.
(I also like to add about one cup frozen peas for color.)
Cook noodles and add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: tropical cream punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except club soda; mix well.
Slowly add club soda.
Serve over ice.

title: english apple pie
directions: In medium size bowl, beat butter and brown sugar with wooden spoon or electric mixer until pale and fluffy.
Stir in flour, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and the water until smooth and thick.
Stir in pecans.
Mound apples in 9-inch pie plate.
Mix granulated sugar with remaining cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Spoon pecan topping over apples and dollops.
Bake on lowest rack of preheated 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes until apples are tender when pierced with a skewer.
Serve in bowls with the cream or ice cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ice cream and oreos
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or Pyrex dish with all but 1 cup of crushed cookies combined with melted butter.
Slice softened ice cream and smooth over cookie crust.
Top with whipped topping. Swirl chocolate syrup on top, then sprinkle with reserved cup of cookie crumbs.

title: frosted liver pate
directions: Combine liver sausage, 1 package cream cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce and 1 teaspoon mustard.
Mix until smooth. Pack mixture into a small bowl lined with Saran Wrap or aluminum foil and chill throughout.
Shape into a ball and remove film or foil; place in center of a serving dish.
Mix 2 packages cream cheese and remaining mustard into a smooth paste; spread evenly over liver sausage and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and nuts.

title: lemon squares #2
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients, saving 1 cup for top.
Mix remaining ingredients well; set aside.
Line cake pan with cake mixture.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.
Put next mixture over top of cake.
Sprinkle reserved 1 cup cake mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot sour cream-pecan spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk.
Tear beef into small pieces and combine with pepper, onion flakes and seasonings.
Add to cream cheese mixture; mix well.
Fold in sour cream.
Spoon into 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Brown pecans in butter and salt; sprinkle over sour cream mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve hot with Triscuits.
Serves 25.

title: upside-down cake batter
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over your favorite fruit in a square pan.
Dot the top with butter and brown sugar. Bake at 350° about 20 minutes. Cool and turn onto plate.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs until
light
and
fluffy
(may
add a little milk). Soak both sides
of
bread
very
well in egg mixture. Fry in butter on both sides until golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar
and/or cinnamon.
Serve with syrup or favorite fruit (if desired).

title: quick mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix well and spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 450 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Combine boiling water and oats; let stand 20 minutes.
In separate bowl beat butter until creamy.
Add sugars; beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla, eggs and oats mixture; mix well.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture and blend well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Do not remove from pan; while still warm, frost.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter. Place bread in bottom of dish. Cover with a layer of sausage and a layer of cheese. Beat eggs, milk and salt together and pour over cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Next day, uncover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: eggs newport
directions: In a blender mix first three ingredients.
Slice and saute mushrooms in butter.
Fry bacon until crisp.
In baking dish layer eggs, mushrooms, sauce, chives and bacon.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve on toasted English muffins.

title: glenda's cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
While hot, stick with a toothpick and pour mixture of jello dissolved in 2 cups boiling water.
Let cool.
Cover cake with strawberries, then cover with vanilla pudding, then cover with Cool Whip and decorate with strawberries.

title: spicy chuck wagon soup
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the flour, paprika, 1 tsp. chili powder, salt and garlic powder. Add beef, a few pieces at a time, and shake to coat. In a large soup kettle, brown beef in oil in batches. Stir in the onions, tomatoes, broth, bay leaf, cayenne pepper and remaining chili powder. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add potatoes and carrots. Cover and simmer 35-40 minutes longer or until meat and vegetables are tender. Add corn and heat through. Discard the bay leaf before serving. Yield: 10 servings (4 quarts).

title: cornbread muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Grease large muffin tins.
Pour about 3/4 full of batter and bake in oven at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lemon dill chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pound chicken breasts until flattened. Place each on a sheet of foil.
Season with salt and pepper. Blend dill, parsley and garlic.
Sprinkle over breasts.
Place 3 lemon slices on each breast.
Dot with butter.
Seal chicken in foil.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spiced zucchini bread
directions: Combine first six ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs lightly; add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients and stir only until moistened.
Pour into two well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa well.
Add milk.
Place on stove on medium heat and add butter or margarine.
Cook until soft ball stage. Remove from heat and beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour into buttered dish.
Let cool and then cut.

title: caramels
directions: Cook to form ball at 250°.
Add vanilla.
Add nuts.
Pour into buttered pan.
Let stand until firm.
Cut into squares and wrap in wax paper individually.

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Layer peaches with syrup, dry cake mix, butter, coconut and pecans in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake until topping is golden brown, 55 to 60 minutes at 325°.
Serve warm or cold with sweetened whipped cream or ice cream.
Yellow cake mix may be used instead of butter brickle.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: best broccoli
directions: Place cooked chicken in a baking dish.
Cook broccoli according to directions.
Place on top of chicken.
Blend mayonnaise, soups, mushrooms and broth.
Pour over chicken. Cover with shredded cheese.
Add bread crumbs.
Dot with butter or oleo.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onion and pepper lightly.
Set aside.
Add rice and brown, stirring often.
Reduce heat; add remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, for 30 to 35 minutes or until most of liquid is gone and rice is tender.

title: vegetable pizza appetizer
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles. Place rectangles crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Press over bottom and 1-inch up sides to form crust.
Seal perforations.
Bake at 375° for 14 to 19 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: granny kelso's dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Be sure and add enough broth to make extra moist.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Don't brown too much.

title: bread and butter sweet pickles
directions: Sprinkle ice over cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Sprinkle salt over ice.
Set for 3 to 4 hours.
Drain.
Boil vinegar, sugar and seasonings.
Let simmer 15 minutes with cucumbers.
Put into jars and seal.

title: key lime cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water, lime juice and oil. Stir and mix to blend, then beat well. Pour batter into a greased 13 x 9 baking pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes. Let cake cool, then drizzle on glaze.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar and sugar together.
Blend in egg, peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oats. Spread mixture in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with chips.
Let stand 5 minutes and spread evenly.
Before cutting, drizzle topping over bars.

title: honey-lime dip for fruit
directions: In a small bowl combine yogurt, honey, lime juice and rind; mix well.
Cover.
Chill overnight.
Makes 6 servings.
Spoon dip.

title: fudge pudding
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa together. Mix the melted shortening with milk and add to dry ingredients. Put in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Combine 1/4 cup cocoa with the brown sugar and sprinkle over the batter. Pour the boiling water over the top, holding a tablespoon under the stream of water so that it spreads evenly and stays on top. Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 45 minutes. Turn out upside down, letting the sauce pour over the pudding. Makes 4 servings.

title: corn muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cornmeal and baking powder together. Combine egg whites, milk and oil.
Pour into dry ingredients. Stir to blend.
Pour batter into lightly oiled muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 22 minutes or until golden brown.

title: buttery caramel corn
directions: Put popcorn in large paper grocery bag. Combine in 2 qt bowl butter, salt, brown sugar, corn syrup. Microwave 2 minutes and stir. Microwave 3 minutes more, stirring after each minute. Add vanilla and soda. Stir and pour over popcorn and peanuts, if desired, in bag. Microwave 1 minute, shake well and repeat. Pour onto cookie sheet and let cool. Store in air tight container.

title: grecian salad
directions: Mix liquids, salt and sugar until creamy.
Pour over vegetables and let set overnight.
Stir well before serving.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Cut tips from chicken wings.
Dip wings in egg and then in cornstarch to which the garlic salt has been added.
Pour cooking oil into electric fry pan and turn to 350°.
Brown wings.
Make a sauce of the next 7 ingredients.
Place the meat in 10 x 10-inch pan.
Cover with sauce and bake 40 minutes at 375°.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: oven fried mayonnaise chicken
directions: Spray large baking pan with Pam. Wash and pat dry chicken pieces. Put mayonnaise in small bowl; dip and thoroughly cover chicken pieces with mayonnaise. Dip in crushed corn flakes. Arrange in pan without touching. Bake 1 1/2
to 2 hours at 350°, uncovered.

title: baked chicken strips with parmesan cheese
directions: Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese; set aside. Wash and prepare chicken that can be sliced into strips or purchase chicken already in strips. Combine oil and garlic. Dip chicken into oil and garlic mixture. Roll chicken into the bread crumb mixture. Place on baking dish/sheet that has been sprayed lightly with oil. Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 15 minutes. Serve sprinkled with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: pumpkin-pecan pie
directions: Combine the first 11 ingredients and beat until smooth (2 to 3 minutes). Don't overbeat. Set aside.

title: cream cheese delight
directions: Mix flour, walnuts and butter.
Press on bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 8-inch square pan or an 8-inch iron skillet in a 350° oven.
Coat pan with margarine.
Mix other ingredients until blended.
Pour remaining melted margarine into batter and mix well.
Pour batter into hot pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crunchy cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with the boiling water; stir to dissolve.
Add rest of the ingredients; stir together.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch bowl.
Chill overnight.
Can add more pecans, if desired.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Simmer celery, pepper and onions and add to beef.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, bay leaves, basil and oregano and garlic cloves.
Bring to a boil and add salt and pepper to taste.
May use garlic, onion and celery salt, if desired.
Add a little red pepper and cook slowly for about 6 hours.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add milk.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: glazed lemon squares
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cut in butter.
Press into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: grandma brown's coffee cake
directions: Mix butter and peanut butter with sugar. Sift salt, cinnamon and 1 cup sifted flour and add together.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to box. Slice or dice vegies, then steam in a steamer or microwave to soften. Preheat oven to 375°. Grease casserole dish with cooking spray. Place a layer of sauce on bottom of dish, followed by a layer of noodles. Next, spread a layer of vegetables. Sprinkle with spices, then sauce, then Mozzarella. Repeat layering of noodles, vegies, sauce and cheese until used up. Top layers should be noodles, sauce and mixture of Cheddar, Mozzarella and spices. Bake approximately 35 minutes or until cheese is fully melted.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Add peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Chill until set.
Store in an airtight container in a cool place.
Can be refrigerated, if desired.

title: chocolate pudding pie
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts well and place in bottom of 9 X 13 baking dish.
Bake at 350 for 15 minutes.
Mix powdered sugar, 1/2 large Cool Whip, cream cheese.
Mix well and spread on crust.
Beat instant puddings with 4 cups milk and spread on cream cheese mixture.
Spread remaining cool whip on top and chill.

title: oven baked spareribs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Use cooking bag and shake flour in bag. Add all other ingredients to flour in bag.
Add ribs or chops to cooking bag.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Punch small holes in bag to keep from bursting and add a little water in pan while cooking.
This helps keep meat moist.
Cover lightly with foil.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Press raw ground beef into 8-inch square pan.
Place onion rings on the meat.
Salt if desired.
Mix milk, soup and beans; pour over meat and onion.
Top with frozen Tater Tots.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage,
onion
and bell pepper. Fold in 1 cup sugar. Set
aside.
Mix
remaining ingredients and bring to a slow boil.
Cool
slightly,
then
toss with cabbage mixture. Refrigerate for 24 hours and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Chill and make into a ball.
Roll in pecans.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Dissolve yeast in warm water, add salt, butter and pudding mix.
Add flour, knead dough 12 times. Roll out long and about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with soft butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle with raisins, if desired. Roll up dough, starting on long side and cut rolls about 1-inch thick.
Let raise.
(Usually 1 1/2 hours or until double.)
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Make glaze of powdered sugar and milk.

title: blackeye pea dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: pork chops in mushroom gravy
directions: Brown chops in small amount of fat.
Place chops in a casserole and pour soup over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma atchley's scalloped oysters
directions: Place crushed crackers in greased baking dish.
Cover with milk and let set for hours to soak up the milk.
Add more milk if necessary.
Add ground pepper, Old Bay seasoning, salt and onion salt to taste.
Add oysters and enough milk to make sloppy.
Cut up butter for top before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until browned and set, uncovered.
Can be started the night before.

title: all meat stew
directions: Cut elephant into small, bite-sized pieces.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire about 4 weeks at 465°. This will serve 3,800 people.

title: began bharta(north indian eggplant dish)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Rinse eggplant dry; slice in half lengthwise.
Place halves on foil covered oven rack.
Roast for 40 to 50 minutes.
When the eggplant is done the outside skin will appear charred.
Set aside to cool, then scoop out the flesh from the charred shell.

title: coconut puffs
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add salt and cream of tartar. Beat until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Beat until stiff and glossy.
Fold in extracts and coconut.
Drop from teaspoon to lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Chop 4 potatoes and onion in food processor.
Dice other potatoes into small pieces.
Place in a 4-quart pan with water. Add salt and pepper. Simmer until thick, about 20 minutes.
Melt butter in 2-quart saucepan.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add milk and half and half.
Cook over low heat until thickened and smooth, for about 20 minutes.
Stir Velveeta into milk mixture until melted and add parsley.
Combine with the potato mixture. Yield: 3 quarts.

title: ham and mushroom pate
directions: Melt butter in a skillet and saute mushrooms over medium heat. Combine ham, cream cheese and thyme; blend well.
Stir in sauteed mushrooms.
Cover and chill overnight.
Serve on party bread slices.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until creamy.
Then cool.

While dough is cooling, melt chocolate chips and wax together either in double boiler or microwave (watch carefully; do not scald chocolate). Keep chocolate in pan of hot water so it remains a liquid.
Form dough in small balls (large marble size).
With a toothpick, dip 1/2 dough ball into chocolate mix and place on wax paper to cool. Refrigerate.

title: potato-pepperoni supper
directions: Over medium heat, in skillet, melt margarine and remove from heat.
Add potatoes and onion on bottom and slightly up side of skillet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover skillet.
Over medium-low heat, cook until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes. Sprinkle potatoes with cheese; top with 1/2 tomato sauce. Arrange pepperoni and tomatoes over sauce; top with remaining sauce.

title: zucchini preserves
directions: Bring the zucchini slowly to a boil; boil for 12 to 15 minutes.
Add the lemon juice, pineapple and sugar.
Boil for 10 minutes; take off heat.
Add the jello and gelatine; mix real well.
Pour into jars and seal, or cover with paraffin or keep in freezer.

title: spaghetti ala carbonara
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling water until tender.
Meanwhile, beat eggs, half and half and pepper in a bowl.
Dice the bacon and fry until crisp.
Drain the spaghetti and add to the bacon.
Pour in the egg mixture, stirring, and toss over a gentle heat until the eggs begin to set.
Serve immediately sprinkled with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Combine all ingredients except chocolate chips in large bowl and mix for 2 minutes.
Add chips. Mix and pour into greased and floured Bundt pan and bake for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool cake for 15 minutes before removing from pan. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: eggless, milkless, butterless cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, salt and cocoa.
Make 3 holes.
In first hole, put vanilla.
In second hole, vinegar.
In third hole, the shortening.
Add water and mix all together.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Makes a small cake.

title: quick croissants
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Add milk, salt, sugar, egg and 1 cup flour.
Beat until smooth.
Blend in melted butter; set aside. In a large bowl, cut the butter into 4 cups of flour until the size of dried kidney beans.
Pour yeast batter over the top and carefully turn mixture over with spatula to blend, just until flour is moistened.
Cover with plastic and refrigerate 4 hours to 4 days.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Work peanut butter, oil and sugar.
Add enough flour to make mixture the consistency of play dough.
Delightful for small children to roll on table and tasty, too.

title: zucchini and sausage soup
directions: In large saucepan, brown the sausage. Remove with a slotted spoon to paper towel to drain, reserving 1 tablespoon of drippings.

Saute celery and onion in drippings for 5 minutes. Add sausage and remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes or until veggies are tender. Add water to make thinner, if necessary. Serves 9.

title: herbed chicken breasts
directions: In a pie pan, mix bread crumbs, salt, thyme, rosemary and black pepper.
Dip each chicken breast in egg and then coat with bread crumb mixture.
In a medium skillet, heat oil until hot.
Saute chicken until lightly browned on each side, about 5 minutes.
Add wine and bring to a boil; reduce.
Serves 2.

title: spinach noodle casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions. Drain well. Combine with 1/2 the sour cream, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain, add margarine and onion and blend with spinach mixture.
In a 2-quart baking dish, layer spinach, then noodles, then cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Top with remaining sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: roast beef salad
directions: Arrange ingredients on a platter or 4 individual plates in the order listed.
Drizzle on dressing when ready to serve.

title: super chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a large bowl with an electric mixer on high speed, cream sugars and margarine until light.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
On low speed add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Fold in nuts and chocolate morsels.

title: party beef casserole
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine flour, salt and pepper; add beef cubes and shake to coat. In a skillet over medium heat, brown beef in oil. Place beef and drippings in a greased, shallow 2 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg and enough milk to moisten ingredients thoroughly.
Drop by spoon into deep fat (400°) and cook until golden brown.

title: breakfast frittata
directions: Mix together potatoes, broccoli, onion, green pepper and butter in skillet.
Cook spuds in butter until tender.
Add onions and peppers; cook until onions are tender.
Add broccoli; cover and cook on low for 5 minutes.
Add to mixture eggs, Parmesan cheese, basil, salt, pepper and water.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 15 minutes (until edges are set).
Sprinkle 1/4 cup Monterey Jack cheese on top (optional).
Take off heat; cover and let set for 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: steamed carrots cashew
directions: Cut carrots into 2-inch pieces.
Place cut julienne slice. Heat margarine in heavy saucepan with lid.
Add carrots, sugar, salt and water.
Cover and steam 10 minutes.
Be careful not to burn carrots.
Add peas and steam another 2 minutes.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Mix and put in glass jar.
Cover loosely and let stand 24 hours at room temperature.
Put in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days, then feed.
Add 1 cup warm water, 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons instant potatoes.
Mix well and add to mixture.
Let stand out of refrigerator 8 to 12 hours.
Will not rise, only bubble.
Remove 1 cup to make bread.
Return remainder to refrigerator . Keep in fridge 3 to 5 days, then feed again.
Always take out 1 cup to use or give away or throw away.
(I sometimes let stay in fridge for a week before feeding again.)

title: peanut butter tandy cake
directions: Beat together the sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add the flour, salt, baking powder and milk.
Beat well.
Spread into a greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Put the peanut butter on the hot cake in 6 small mounds to soften.
Spread across the cake.
Refrigerate.
Melt the Hershey bar with the shortening in a double boiler.
Spread it on the cold cake.
Cut in squares.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon and set aside to drain.
Pour off bacon fat.
Add onions to pan and saute until translucent.
Add potatoes and water or clam juice.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add milk, clams with juice, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes (do not boil).
Add butter just prior to serving. Garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: surprise meringues
directions: In large bowl beat to soft peaks 2 egg whites, 1/8 tsp. cream of tartar, 1/8 tsp. of salt and 1 tsp of vanilla.
Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold in 6 oz. package of semi-sweet chocolate bits and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Drop by tsp. on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes at 300 degrees.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine the first 8 ingredients in a mixing bowl until a dough forms.
Shape dough into balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from oven. Push a chocolate kiss into center of each while warm, so cookie cracks around the edge.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: hillary's cheese scalloped potatoes
directions: Bring potatoes to a boil in a saucepan; immediately drain and transfer to a greased 2-quart baking dish.
While potatoes boil, make white sauce:
Melt butter in saucepan; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat; slowly add milk, while stirring.
Bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly. Add cheese and stir over medium heat until melted.
Pour cheese sauce over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until bubbly.

title: salsa
directions: Squeeze the juice of the limes. Cut up the celery. Do not put the celery in the blender. Blend all other ingredients in the blender. Mix with celery. Yum!

title: holly clusters
directions: Spread pieces of wax paper, about 1 foot long, on a table. Measure cinnamon candies and set them on table.
Measure corn flakes and put them in a pile on another piece of wax paper.
Put butter or margarine in saucepan; turn burner to low.
When butter starts to melt, add the marshmallows.
Stir until the butter and marshmallows are completely melted.
Remove from heat.
Add food coloring and stir until mixture is evenly colored.
Pour in corn flakes and stir until just coated.
Drop from tablespoon onto wax paper.
Press several cinnamon candies on each.
Let dry 1 hour. Makes about 36.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add onions and green peppers; cook until tender.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add beans last hour.
Remove bay leaves before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and syrup.
Add salt, vanilla and oleo.
Mix well.
Sprinkle 1 cup of pecans in pie shell.
Pour mixture over nuts.
Bake at 325° until firm.

title: sour cream meatballs
directions: Form into small balls the beef, crumbs, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Brown in some grease in large pot, a few at a time.
When all are browned, add the water.
Simmer for 1/2 hour, covered. Remove from the pan. Add the 2 cans of soup and the milk to pan. Scrape browned remains in pan.
Stir until smooth.
Now, add balls back to pan and simmer 2 hours.
Add the sour cream before serving.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: russian tea cakes(or mexican wedding cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly oleo, sugar and vanilla. Work flour, salt and nuts in until dough holds together.
Shape into 1-inch balls and bake on ungreased baking sheet 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while warm.
Cool, roll again.

title: spinach potato dish
directions: Mix.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: light 'n' lean meat loaf
directions: Coat a large nonstick frying pan with vegetable cooking spray. Add the carrots, onions and pepper.
Saute for 5 to 10 minutes. Crumble the ground beef and turkey into a large bowl.
Lightly toss with the cooked vegetables, oats and rice.
In a small bowl, combine the tomato juice, eggs, oregano, thyme, pepper sauce and black pepper.
Add to the meat mix.

title: no-peek beef stew
directions: Do not brown meat and do not add salt.
Put ingredients in casserole dish, starting with meat.
Cover and bake at 300°
for 3 hours.
Don't peek.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.
Serve with rice.

title: cream of rice and mushroom soup
directions: Saute butter, onion, celery, and mushrooms until the vegetables are tender.
Add 2 Tbsp. flour.
Bring to boil.
Add broth, rice, salt, and pepper.
Boil until somewhat thickened. Add 1/2 c. whipping cream and let boil for 1 minute.
Add thyme and marjoram.
Serve warm.

title: chicken salad in pineapple boats
directions: Wash pineapples; trim any bad leaves around edge and cut in half.
Hollow out, leaving at least a half inch of the pineapple meat.
Mix chicken, scallions, almonds, pineapple meat and grapes. Add mayonnaise (just enough to hold the ingredients together). Fill pineapple shells.
To serve, line platter with red lettuce leaves and lay pineapple with leaves out.
Top salad with a little fresh chopped parsley and a half a grape turned upside down.

title: corn 'n frank chowder
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan saute cubed franks, onions and peppers in margarine until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Stir in seasoning and pour in small dish lined with chips.
Pour tomatoes over meat mixture and top with grated cheese.
Heat for 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve like tacos.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Arrange alternating layers in casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: michael, natalie and mark's favorite macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare package of elbow macaroni per instructions.
When pasta is prepared and rinsed, grease the bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish with 1 tablespoon of butter or margarine.
Place approximately 1 1/2 cups of elbow macaroni in casserole dish and dot top with 1 tablespoon butter or margarine and 1 cup shredded Velveeta.
Repeat this layering 2 more times.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour approximately 1/2 cup of milk over mixture.

title: tomato soup
directions: Run the tomatoes through food press after cooking. Blend onions and celery seed with a little juice.
Dissolve the cornstarch in some juice.
Pour all ingredients into a huge pot. Add the sugar, pepper, salt and margarine.
Cook until thick. Stir well.
Process in hot water bath for 20 minutes.
Yields 12 to 14 pints.

title: creamy mushroom and noodles
directions: In large dkillet melt margarine over medium heat.
Add onions and mushrooms;
saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Add red bell pepper;
cook 1 minute.
Stir half-and-half, corn starch, salt and pepper until smooth;
stir into skillet.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Toss with egg noodles.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Mix. Use directions on package.
Set aside.
In large bowl, chop lettuce, onion and tomato.
Add kidney beans, Cheddar cheese, ground beef mixture and crushed Doritos.
Mix together well and add dressing; add sour cream, if you like.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain well.
Add refried beans and taco sauce; mix well.
In casserole dish, layer meat mixture, chips and cheese until full, ending with cheese.
Put in oven until hot and the cheese has melted.

title: marshmallow pops-on-a-stick
directions: You will need 40 wooden popsicle sticks.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Saute onion until clear.
Mix together all ingredients except chips.
Pour in casserole dish and layer with cheese and chips (crushed).
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine the gelatin, sugar, egg yolks, lime juice and water in a saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat; let chill.

title: quick-n-easy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Choose any cake mix and add eggs and oil.
Mix well.
Drop teaspoonfuls of dough onto an ungreased cookie sheet, spacing about 2 inches apart.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool completely before serving.
Feel free to add nuts, chocolate chips or raisins.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: quick yeast muffins
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Combine butter, sugar and egg in a large bowl; beat well.
Stir in yeast mixture. Gradually add flour, stirring well.
Cover and store in refrigerator for 2 days in airtight container.

title: 2 flavored fudge
directions: Combine in saucepan, brown sugar, sugar, milk and butter. Bring to a full boil over moderate heat, stirring frequently. Boil for 15 minutes over moderate heat.

title: coffee klutch sweet treat
directions: Stir raisins, brown sugar and nuts together in bowl; set aside.
Stretch or press biscuits into 4-inch circles on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Butter biscuits generously and press raisin mixture over top.
Bake 8 minutes at 450°.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Heat marshmallows and milk until marshmallows melt.
Add to the other ingredients.
Place mixture into a tube pan or loaf pan that is lined with waxed paper.
Cover with waxed paper.
Chill a day or more before cutting.

title: tipsy mud pie
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and butter; place mixture firmly into a 10-inch pie plate.
Combine banana slices and lemon juice.
Arrange in a single layer on chocolate crust.
Freeze.

title: baked eggplant parmigiana
directions: Pare eggplants and cut into thin slices.
