Dip into beaten egg, then bread crumbs and place in single layer on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes or until browned on both sides.

title: sunday salad
directions: Drain fruit well; combine.
Add grapes which have been halved and seeds removed.
Mix lightly with fruit.
Empty topping and pudding mixes into bowl; add milk.
Beat to consistency of whipped cream.
Fold into fruits.
Can be made a day ahead.
Serves 10.

title: german sweet chocolate dessert
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients over boiling water in a double boiler until chocolate is melted and the mixture is slightly thickened. Remove from heat.
Add 4 egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Cool.
(When separating, keep a yolk in each half shell.)
Add 4 egg whites, which have been beaten stiff.

title: lobster casserole
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise and sherry.
Stir in milk; combine with remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Turn into 3-quart baking dish; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (40 minutes if it has not been refrigerated).

title: mom's meatballs
directions: Combine above ingredients and form into meatballs.
Fry on both sides until brown.
Place meatballs into a baking dish.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Mix both crumbs, sugar and butter and put in a 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Cool. Mix pudding and milk. Beat in ice cream. Pour into cooled crust. Refrigerate to harden. Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed candy bars. Chill several hours.

title: easy steak and gravy
directions: Batter and fry steak enough to brown on both sides.
Drain. Place meat in casserole dish and cover with soup and onion slices (about 1/2 cup water will make gravy thinner). Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: breakfast cake
directions: Mix above ingredients together for 8 minutes.

title: cranberry crunch bars
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 8-inch square pan.
Sift flour, salt and cinnamon into bowl.
Stir in brown sugar and oats. Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Add nuts.
Press 1/2 of mixture evenly over bottom of pan.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and relish in saucepan. Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils 3 minutes.
Pour mixture over oats in square pan and top evenly with remaining oats.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tomato pie
directions: Mix biscuit mix, 1/4 cup water and butter with fork and press into 9-inch pie pan.
Layer tomato slices on crust.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on tomatoes.
Mix and spread over cheese: mayonnaise, green onions (sliced) and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in lower half of oven.
Serve immediately.

title: 7 minute white icing
directions: Mix and heat over boiling water.
Beat with mixer constantly until fluffy.

title: easy ham glaze
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 5 minutes. Brush frequently on ham during last 30 minutes of baking.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: didie's dirt cake delight
directions: Crush (in food processor) Oreo cookies until very fine; set aside.
Cream together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar in mixer or food processor.
In one bowl blend milk and pudding.
Mix well, then fold in Cool Whip.
In an 8-inch flowerpot (plug hole in bottom with foil) begin layers, starting with cookie crumbs, then cream cheese mixture.
Continue layering and end off with cookie crumbs.
Chill overnight.
Top with silk flower and serve with garden spade.
Add gummy worms (optional).

title: no-crust broccoli quiche
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of boiling salted water until barely tender.
Drain well and in a small bowl, combine with onion, green pepper and cheese.
Butter a 10-inch pie or quiche pan and place broccoli mixture on bottom.

title: orange julianne
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and whirl a few minutes.

title: grandma's brownies
directions: Cream sugar and butter, then add rest of ingredients. Grease 8 x 16-inch pan. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: marinade for meat
directions: Combine
vinegar, oil, onion, garlic and Worcestershire sauce in a
large
glass
bowl.
Mix
well; add meat and stir. Let stand in
refrigerator
overnight, turning the meat occasionally. Yields about 8 servings.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine sugar and syrup; bring to boil. Remove from heat and stir in the peanut butter.
Pour this mixture over the corn flakes and coconut.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream the butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs, beating well.
Combine flour, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture, beating well. Stir in pecans. Drop by level tablespoonful, 2-inches apart, onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool slightly on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire racks.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: waterloo farm bean soup
directions: *Such as large and small limas, split peas, kidney beans, barley, lentils, navy beans, black-eyed peas and small red beans.

title: chocolate sin
directions: Mix together flour, pecans and butter or oleo.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 325° for 15 minutes. (Cool.)

title: italian roast beef
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour over meat and roast in oven at 350° until done. Meat should pull apart when completely cooked. Add a little more water if needed. I let the meat sit overnight in the refrigerator and then slice down. Then put it back in the broth and reheat.

title: little spice cakes
directions: Combine egg, molasses and melted butter.
Sift remaining ingredients and add.
Mix well and chill until firm enough to shape (maybe 1 hour).
Roll into balls 3/4-inch in diameter.
Roll in sugar.
Bake about 12 minutes at 375°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: ham and cheese delight
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach salad
directions: In a blender, combine oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, celery leaves, mustard and onion.
Blend well.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix and let stand overnight.
Just before serving, add 2 small cans chow mein noodles.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fill container to line with milk.

title: whole wheat beef 'n' pepper pizza
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Spray
a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam; set aside.	In bowl, combine flour, eggs, oregano and 1/2 teaspoon salt, beat until smooth.
Pour into pan and sprinkle with	beef, vegetables,
pepper and the remaining salt.
Bake for
20 minutes, then top pizza with tomato sauce and cheese. Bake	10
to 15 minutes longer.	Serves 4.
Exchange per serving:
protein, 1
bread,
1/4 vegetables, 10 optional calories.

title: 5-layer dessert
directions: Mix and pat into dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and margarine well, then add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: california onion dip
directions: Mix milk and bouillon cubes in blender until bouillon dissolves.
Add remaining ingredients, except onion, and blend at high speed until smooth.
Stir in onion.
Use as a dip for raw vegetables. Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: oven-fried potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in two (doubled) resealable bags. Add oil. Combine parmesan cheese and seasonings. Add to potatoes and shake to coat.Place into a baking pan. Bake uncovered at 375° for 40-50 minutes or until tender.

title: hanky panky(appetizer)
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Under low heat, add cheese and mix until all melted and blended.
Place tablespoons of meat and cheese mixture on slices of bread and place on cookie sheet. Place under broiler until mixture bubbles and bread is crisp (usually 5 to 7 minutes).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute onion and celery.
Mix together and add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer.
Then blend in other ingredients and mix well.
Turn into greased 9-inch deep dish pie pan (or two shallow 8-inch pans).
Bake 30 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
This pie makes its own crust.
Pie is better made a day ahead.

title: fudge nut bars
directions: Melt chips and shortening in microwave.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
In another bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in melted chips and shortening.
Add nuts and blend thoroughly.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned sugar cream pie
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and salt and add 2 cups cream and vanilla, beating thoroughly; pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, reduce heat to 325° and bake 45 to 50 minutes longer.
Filling should boil in little heat bubbles over entire pie and is done when a golden brown and still shaky but not runny.

title: squash casserole
directions: Spread a layer of bread crumbs in a greased casserole.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over bread crumbs.
Add another layer of bread crumbs on top. Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german rolladen
directions: Pound 4 slices of beef until thin.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
On each slice of beef, spread 1 slice chopped bacon and about 1/4 onion, chopped, along center of meat (lengthwise).
Pickle spear may be added.
Roll up and secure with wooden toothpicks or white thread.
Heart a little olive oil in pan.
Brown the 4 meat rolls on all sides.
Add approximately 3/4 cup water.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour or until done.
Remove rolladen from pan and add approximately 3/4 cup water mixed with about 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and add 2 tablespoons sour dream.
Mix thoroughly.
Serve the rolladen with gravy accompanied with spaetzle or potatoes.

title: hot tomato salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Remove from heat and immediately pack hot tomato mixture into hot jars, filling to 1/2-inch from top.
Carefully run a nonmetallic spatula around inside of jars to remove air bubbles.
Wipe jar rims.
Cover at once with metal canning lids and screw on bands. Process in boiling water bath 15 minutes.
Yield:
4 pints.

title: penne with broccoli(makes 8 cups)
directions: Cook the penne according to package directions.
Three minutes before pasta is done, add broccoli to the pasta.
Drain and return to saucepot.

title: georgia dish
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream; set aside.
Fry onion and ground beef; drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Add tomato sauce.
Cook 15 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cover bottom of greased casserole with potato slices. Sprinkle with half the flour, salt and pepper.
Repeat layers. Pour milk over potatoes.
Drizzle evenly with melted butter. Cover and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Uncover; cook for 30 minutes longer until potatoes are tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cool and debone.
In medium bowl, mix soup (can be any kind of cream soup, do not dilute), sour cream and cheese with drained Veg-All mixed vegetables.
Melt butter and mix with crackers.
Put chicken in casserole dish, then put soup mixture on top of chicken.
Top with crackers and butter mixture. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 45 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and shortening; take out 1 cup for topping.
Add remaining ingredients to the larger portion of the dry mixture and beat together well.
Pour batter into 2 (9-inch) round pans or 1 (13 x 9-inch) pan.
Sprinkle reserved 1 cup of topping over batter in pan(s).
Bake cake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
It may take less time to bake the cakes in the 9-inch pans, so keep an eye on the 9-inch cakes while you are baking them.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, condensed milk and lemon juice; beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Stir in pecans and fruit. Pour into pie shells and refrigerate for several hours.
Yields 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Mix ingredients all together, then roll into 1-inch balls. Roll balls in granulated sugar to coat. Space on ungreased cookie sheet. Press balls down using an unwrapped Kiss. Bake cookies at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: souper tuna loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, tuna, bread crumbs, eggs, parsley and lemon juice.
Spread evenly in well-greased loaf pan, 8 x 4 x 3-inch.
Bake 40 minutes at 400°.
Loosen edges; unmold.
Combine rest of soup, water and basil.
Heat.
Pour over loaf.

title: jeff's baby back ribs
directions: Remove back membrane.
Bake ribs in covered cake pan with 1/2 cup water for 1 1/4 hours at 325°.
(If ribs are fatty, boil first for 20 minutes, then bake, covered, for 45 minutes.)
Drain and chill.
Make sauce with rest of the ingredients.
Place ribs on covered outdoor grill on low fire.
Heat both sides 5 minutes, then add sauce.
Cook 10 minutes on each side, until slightly browned and crispy.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together until light and fluffy. Mix vanilla and flour together and add to sugar mixture.
Add the nuts and potato chips by hand.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar when cooled.

title: mint candy
directions: Mix well. Shape into small balls.
Place between layers of waxed paper.
Press with a glass until thin.
Chill and dip in chocolate.

title: creamed rice
directions: Bring water to boil.
Stir in rice and bring back to boil. Boil 5 minutes.
Drain off water.
Add milk, butter and salt. Cover and turn heat down to simmer.
Cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
This is especially good with "Pumpkin Blossoms", sliced tomatoes on the side with a sprig of parsley for color.

title: easy pot roast
directions: In large heavy pan, brown meat on all sides.
Pour off fat. Stir in soup.
Cover.
Cook over low heat for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Remove meat.
To thicken gravy, gradually blend 1/2 cup water into two to four tablespoons of flour.
Slowly stir into soup.
Cook, stirring until thickened.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Make a paste and alternate with dry ingredients. Add chocolate chips and zucchini.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in greased and floured 10 x 14-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
If using a Bundt pan, bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: pecan pie #2
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs, corn syrup, sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Stir well.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.

title: chili bake
directions: Saute meat and onions in butter until browned.
Add tomatoes, beans, celery, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add chili powder and simmer 30 minutes more.

title: sister reida's dolollie
directions: Boil macaroni until done; drain.
Fry sausage and onion; drain.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Add stewed tomatoes and salt.
Mix together.
Garnish with fresh tomatoes (thinly sliced) and a touch of butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers.

title: punch
directions: Mix cranberry juice and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add pineapple juice; chill.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale. Yields 32 cups.
Will keep frozen for several months.
Very good frozen and served at slush stage.

title: popcorn
directions: Read directions on each bag and ignore them.
Press 5, 0, 0 on your microwave and watch your popcorn pop.
When it gets to not popping constantly, take it out.
Open away from face and pour into large bowl.
Put your 2 shakes salt on the popcorn.
Eat.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 stick oleo and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Pour in 9-inch pie shell.
Top with meringue made from 4 stiffly beaten egg whites, 8 tablespoons sugar, 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: mom's goulash
directions: Coat beef with flour and brown in
hot oil. Add all ingredients and simmer about 2 hours.
Stir often so it does not stick to bottom of pan.
You may have to add a little more liquid. There should be about 2 cups of thick, dark sauce.
Serve over noodles.

title: raspberry swirl
directions: Combine thoroughly the crumbs, melted butter and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Lightly press mixture into well-greased 7 x 11 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Bake in moderate (375°) oven about 8 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add cream cheese, sugar and salt; beat until smooth and light.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Whip cream until stiff and thoroughly fold with egg whites into cheese mixture.
In a mixer or blender, crush raspberries to a pulp.
Gently swirl half of fruit pulp through cheese filling and spread mixture into crust.
Spoon remaining puree over top; swirl with a knife.
Freeze, then cover and return to freezer.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: green beans viennese
directions: Cook beans according to package. Meanwhile, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add broth, parsley, vinegar and dillweed.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in sour cream.
Add to drained beans.
Heat mixture through, do not boil.
Turn into serving bowl.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cinnamon pinwheels
directions: Cut margarine into flour with pastry blender.
Stir in sour cream.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Mix 3 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon.
Divide dough into halves.
Roll 1 half into rectangle, 20 x 7-inches, on sugared, well floured cloth covered board.
Sprinkle with half of the sugar-cinnamon mixture. Roll up tightly, beginning at 7-inch side.
Roll out other half. Sprinkle with cinnamon/sugar.
Join loose end of first roll with 7-inch end of second piece and pinch to seal.
Continue to roll up.
Wrap and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix the first six ingredients well and then add the last five ingredients.
Roll in 1-inch balls and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 20 to 22 dozen.

title: onion surprise casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray Pam in casserole dish.

title: okra stew(liberian dish)
directions: Boil beef for 20 to 25 minutes.
Combine okra and chopped onion and fry for 8 minutes.
Add 3/4 cup warm water, seasoned salt and tomato paste.
Add cooked beef to the sauce and allow to cook on medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on cooked rice.
Makes 5 servings.

title: delicious dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Best after refrigerated a day. Serve with chips, crackers or veggies.

title: easy surprise cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured, pour one package of miniature marshmallows.
Mix up any cake mix of your choice according to directions on box and pour over the marshmallows.
Do not stir.
Now, drop by spoon any canned prepared fruit pie filling all over the cake mixture.
Again do not stir. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
The surprise comes when you take it out of the oven.
Hint, you won't need any frosting.
Example:
If you use a chocolate cake mix, you may want to use a cherry pie filling. For vanilla, you may want to use blueberry; white cake mix, perhaps you would want to use strawberry.
Get the picture?

title: chicken casserole
directions: *May substitute cream of asparagus soup.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine the sugar, cornstarch, flour, milk, water and egg yolks; mix well. Cook over low heat until thick, to a pudding-like consistency. Stir in vanilla and butter.
In a medium size mixing bowl, blend powdered sugar and peanut butter until it resembles cornmeal. Sprinkle 3/4 of the mixture into bottom of baked pie shell; reserve the remaining 1/4.
Add the filling and top with meringue.
Sprinkle meringue with reserved crumb mixture and bake in a 300° oven until brown.
Let sit 1 hour before serving.
Store in refrigerator.

title: berry berry cool pie
directions: Stir together Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice until well combined.
Mix in berries.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon mixture into crust.
Freeze 5 hours or until set.
Let stand 30-40 minutes before serving.
Garnish as desired.

title: ground meat casserole
directions: Cut up onion and pepper and cook in frying pan with meat and taco mix until done.
Add tomatoes and put in casserole.
Top with corn bread mix.
Bake until bread is done.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar until fluffy, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Alternately add milk and flour to margarine.
Add 5 flavors and blend well.
Pour batter into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: ginger krinkles
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Mix in egg, then molasses.
Add flour mixture with spices, soda and salt.
Form ball of dough the size of a walnut, roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cookies will look too soft but they cool to be just right.
Cool on pan for 1 to 2 minutes, then move to a rack.

title: baked chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken and pepper in water-soaked (remove skin from chicken) simmer; mix well.
Place chicken breast over top of mixture.
Sprinkle with pepper; cover with water-soaked lid.
Microwave for 15 minutes, soaked lid. Microwave for 15 minutes on High.
Rearrange chicken.
Microwave for 28 to 30 minutes on simmer or until rice and chicken are done. Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
Serves about 6. Cook in 2-quart dish.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Let set a few hours.
Keeps well for a week (covered) in refrigerator.

title: chicken ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into ball.
Roll in grated pecans (1/2 cup).
Freezes well.
Serve with crackers.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: On lightly floured surface, roll pastry to 12-inch circle. Place in 9-inch pie plate (you may buy a frozen pie crust already prepared).
Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended. Blend in egg.
Spread onto bottom of pastry shell.
Combine all remaining ingredients, except syrup and pecans; mix well. Carefully pour over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes.
Cool.
Brush with syrup; top with pecans.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and add 1 1/4 cups of the sugar so they will hold their air.
Now cream the butter and the rest of the sugar.
Add the egg yolks.
Sift the flour, salt and soda and add alternately with the sour cream.
Add the vanilla.
Fold in the egg whites last.
Turn into a greased and floured tube pan or two loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until it is done. Turn out on cake rack to cool.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Gently stir in chicken. Pour mixture in Pam sprayed casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 generously.

title: wild rice supreme
directions: Cook rice as directed.
While cooking, melt oleo in pan.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually add chicken broth, milk, pimento, parsley, almonds and chicken breasts.
Place in a 2-quart greased casserole and bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal tube cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes. Cream butter and sugar; beat in vanilla and eggs.
Add oat mixture; mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; add to butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Turn into a greased and floured 6 cup tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Plunge raisins in hot water for a minute and drain.
Cream lard and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add sifted flour, soda, salt and baking powder, then rolled oats.
Stir well. Add raisins and drop by spoonfuls on greased pans.
Bake.

title: artichokes from bari(carciofi di bari)
directions: Cut
off
stems
and
tips of artichokes.
Remove tough outer leaves and soak in flour, lemon and water for 5 minutes. Place rinsed
artichokes in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients into and around leaves of the artichokes.
Cook on medium low heat for 45
minutes or until tender to fork.
Serve with melted butter, if desired.

title: new zealand scones
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add sugar and rub in butter.
Add dates or raisins and mix to a soft dough with milk.
Knead on a lightly floured board; roll out.
Cut and bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Serve with fruit jam, whipped cream and hot, hot tea.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Combine the popped corn,
candy
and peanuts in a large pan. Melt the margarine, oil and marshmallows together.	Pour this mixture over the popped corn mixture.
Mix	well
with
a heavy spoon.
Press mixture into a
greased
tube
pan
very lightly. Put pan in the refrigerator until
the cake is cool. Turn cake onto a plate.
If the cake	doesn't
let
go easily, let the pan set in hot water for a few minutes.

title: reese's peanut butter cup brownies
directions: Mix brownies and bake as directions state.
Ten minutes before brownies are finished, take brownies out of oven and break peanut butter cups on top.
Put back in the oven for last 10 minutes.

title: chip dip
directions: Mix sour cream and salad dressing together.
Add parsley, dill weed and seasoned salt.
Add garlic salt and bacon bits, if desired.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch dish, melt the margarine.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with chocolate morsels, coconut and nuts.
Press down gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: creamed cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Beat eggs, sour cream, oil and corn; blend in corn meal, baking powder and salt. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 8 x 8 pan.

title: love letters
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until smooth.
Spread mixture on bottom of large, wide bowl.
Sift flour and sugar onto mixture. Gently knead until blended by hand.
Minimal handling of dough is necessary.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Flatten one onto a sheet of waxed paper about 16-inches long.
(Dough should be extremely soft but not sticky.
If sticky, dust with flour before placing dough on waxed paper.)
Cover with another sheet of waxed paper.
With rolling pin, spread dough out almost to edges forming rectangle about 10 x 13-inches.
Trim edges.
Transfer dough and papers to baking sheet and chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Remove top paper, turn dough upside down onto baking sheet.
Remove other paper.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch squares.
Put tiny dab of jam on each square and fold in the corners to form an envelope.
If dough becomes too soft while working with it, return it briefly to refrigerator.
Seal the top flap with a red cinnamon heart.
Repeat for other half of dough. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until edges just begin to color.
Transfer to rack to cool.
Makes 20 love letters.

title: banana-yogurt ice milk
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in a saucepan.
Let stand 1 minute.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until gelatin dissolves. Remove from heat.
Combine banana, milk, yogurt and honey.
Stir into gelatin mixture.
Place in an 8-inch square pan.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes to soften.
Break into chunks.
Place in food processor; add banana mixture.
Process until smooth.
Return mixture to pan and freeze until firm.
When served, top with fresh fruit.
Contains 98 calories per 1/2 cup serving and 0.7 fat.

title: banana oatmeal bread
directions: Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl combine bananas, oats and milk; set aside.
In large bowl cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with banana mixture to creamed mixture.
Bake 1 hour.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Mix everything together, except Mozzarella cheese and buns or muffins.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.
Spread on buns or muffins.
Top with cheese.
Heat at 450° until cheese melts, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in lukewarm water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out.
Cut desired number of biscuits and refrigerate remaining dough for later use.
Bake at 450°. Dough can be rolled out and allowed to rise for a few hours before baking.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix well and freeze.
This tastes like strawberry ice cream.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil, then pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with water.
Add raisins and nuts. Bake in loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ada's nacho casual
directions: Crumble beef and sausage into skillet with onion; saute until red color disappears.
Drain off fat and season with salt to taste.
Spread refried beans on greased 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet or jelly roll pan with sides.
Top with meat mixture.
Cover with chilies and sprinkle with cheese.
Drizzle taco sauce over all. This may be covered and refrigerated at this point.

title: homemade ice cream(low carb)
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into ice cream maker/freezer. Follow manufacturers instructions.

title: lime-ginger salmon
directions: Preheat broiler. Line broiler pan with foil.
Spray pan with nonfat butter spray.
In blender, combine ginger, sugar, lime juice and soy sauce until smooth.
Place salmon fillets on broiler pan; brush fillets with glaze.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 5 minutes.
Turn fillets over and brush with remaining glaze; broil 5 minutes longer, until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: dietetic cranberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and Sweet 'N Low in hot water.
Add lemon juice, pineapple juice and water.
Let set.
Stir in fruits and celery and pour into mold.
One-eighth of mold equals 1 fruit.

title: puppy chow for kids
directions: Melt the peanut butter, chocolate chips and oleo or butter. Pour over cereal in a large bowl.
Stir until cereal is well coated.
Let cool.
Stir in the 10x sugar until coated.
Best if refrigerated!

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients; spread in pie plate and cook for 30 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Serve with wheat crackers.

title: stuffed cabbage leaves(petit choux farcie)
directions: Remove 6 large outer leaves from cabbage and blanch in boiling water until tender, about 3-6 minutes.
Place in cold water to stop cooking.
With a sharp paring knife, slice off the thickest part of the stems of the leaves.
Reserve.
Cook rice uncovered in a good amount of water until tender.
Drain and reserve.
Heat 1 1/2 Tbsp. of the butter in a saute pan.
Add the chopped onion and cook covered until tender but not browned.
Add the spinach, season with salt and cook covered until wilted.
For the stuffing:
In a large bowl, combine the rice, cream and the bread crumbs.
Mix in the spinach mixture.
Let cool.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and salad oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened (do not beat).
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Spoon into three 9-inch well-greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool completely.
Frost each layer with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: mom's applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar, egg or yolks and shortening; add and blend flour, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, soda, applesauce, raisins and walnuts.
Bake in a greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Best if baked in tube pan.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into balls the size of a hickory nut. Dip in sugar. Place on a nonstick cookie sheet. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 12 to 15 minutes. Watch closely because they can burn easily.

title: speedy meatball skillet
directions: Partly cook carrots; add meatballs, (brown meatballs if desired), lima beans, soup and water to skillet.
Stir lightly to combine.
Cook slowly for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Mixed vegetables may be used instead of carrots and limas.

title: dressing for endive or lettuce
directions: Cut several slices of bacon into small pieces and fry.
Then add the rest of the ingredients and bring to a boil and cook about 2 minutes or until it thickens.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix together.
Add ice when ready to serve.

title: noodles and meat
directions: Cook onion and bell pepper.
Brown hamburger meat.
Mix together.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Cook egg noodles.
Drain.
Mix with other ingredients.
Cook in microwave for 10 minutes.
Serve with corn bread.

title: pork chops and mushrooms
directions: Put flour in bowl.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover pork chops. Fry until done.
Remove chops and place in baking pan.
Pour cream of mushroom soup and cream of celery soup over cooked pork chops. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 325°.
Cover chops while baking.

title: perfect corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Sift flour, corn meal, sugar, salt and baking powder together.
Stir in milk, egg and melted shortening. Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: praline squares
directions: Arrange crackers one layer deep in an ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Place butter and sugar in a saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts; mix well.
Spread mixture over the graham crackers.
Bake for 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove from oven and let set 2 minutes. While still warm, cut into 48 squares.
Store in coffee can.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix peanut butter and marshmallow cream together.
Cook sugar and milk to a soft ball stage.
Pour hot mixture over peanut butter mix.
Beat and pour into buttered pans.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain corn.
Melt margarine and combine with cream cheese until creamy.
Stir in garlic salt and sugar.
Add drained corn. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Pour into baking dish; top with 1 stack Ritz crackers (crushed).
Drizzle 1 stick melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham primavera
directions: In a large skillet, saute mushrooms and onion in oil until tender. Stir in flour, Italian seasoning, bouillon, salt and pepper until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil; boil and stir for 2 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti, ham and peas; heat through. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Yield: 4 servings.

title: corn oysters
directions: Cut corn off cob; 2/3 the depth of kernel.
Add yolks; blend together.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Stir into corn and egg mixture; blend well.
Gently fold in egg whites. Drop by spoonful on hot greased griddle.
Fry until brown; turn and brown other side.

title: "suck-up" stew
directions: 1. Brown beef cubes in hot oil in a large kettle; drain well. Add remaining ingredients, stir well. 2. Add boiling water until mixture is covered.
Continue heating with kettle covered until meat and potatoes are tender.
Add additional seasonings as desired.
Serve to your boss.

title: chili soup
directions: Fry hamburger meat, onions and garlic.
Add spices and tomato juice and simmer 30 minutes.
Then add cooked beans and water to desired consistency.

title: purple cow (salad)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Drain fruit for 1 cup cold liquid and add to Jell-O mixture.
Add drained fruit when Jell-O has become slightly thickened.
Gently fold in whipped cream and nuts.

title: cherry nut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Freeze.
Take out of freezer 1 hour before serving.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to 275° on candy thermometer. Meanwhile, in large bowl on high speed, beat egg whites with salt until it peaks.
Add hot syrup mixture slowly to beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to swirl off a spoon onto wax paper.
Let stand until hard.

title: baked apple
directions: Core apple, leaving approximately a 1-inch hole 3/4 the way through the apple.
Pack hole tight with brown sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Wrap apple with aluminum foil.
Use approximately a 12-inch square piece.
Twist excess foil at top of apple, leaving a tear drop shape.
Curl top of foil like a hook.
Place apple into coals for approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Use hook on top to remove with a stick, open and enjoy!
This is a great dessert after a foil meal!

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve the orange Jell-O in 2 cups hot water and add frozen orange juice.
Let cool.
Add crushed pineapple and Mandarin orange segments (drained).
Pour into a flat dish.
Let set.

title: pretzels(spicy)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add pretzel pieces.
Stir well until pretzels are coated.
Microwave for 6 minutes; stir every two minutes.

title: barbecued flank steak
directions: Combine soy sauce, garlic, ginger, brown sugar, lemon juice, oil, onion and pepper.
Place flank steak in container.
Pour mixture over top and prick meat with fork.
Cover and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Turn steak over several times.
(The Tupperware marinade pan works great; just flip.)

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with 1/4 package of saltine crackers which have been crushed.
Dot with butter on top and bake in a 10-inch Pyrex dish for 30 minutes.

title: caramel fondue
directions: Melt caramels and cream cheese together in double boiler, stirring frequently.
Pour into heated fondue pot.
Serve with fresh fruit wedges.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add beaten egg.
Sift in flour and baking powder.
Add mashed bananas.
Bake in loaf pan for about 50 minutes at 350°.
Makes 1 loaf.
Check for doneness by inserting toothpick.
Enjoy!

title: frozen salad
directions: Blend together sour cream, Cool Whip, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla.
After it is all mixed together, add the fruit and nuts. Place in a 4 1/2 cup ring mold and freeze several hours or overnight.
Take out of freezer 45 minutes before serving.
Can be tripled for a 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: quick apple danish
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients as for pie crust.
Sift flour, sugar and salt together into bowl.
Cut in shortening, using pastry blender or 2 knives.
Using fork, beat egg yolk in cup; add enough milk to make 2/3 cup in all.
Mix lightly with dry ingredients.
Divide in half.
Roll out to fit onto a cookie sheet.
Cover this pastry with 1 cup crushed corn flakes, then a thick layer of thinly sliced apples.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Thoroughly mix 1/2 dozen children with 1 to 2 dogs (puppies if available); pour on large grassy field.
Cover with blue sky. When nicely browned, remove from heat and cool in warm bath.
When dry, serve with milk and fresh baked cookies.

title: mounds bars
directions: Crust: Mix and pat crumbs, butter and powdered sugar in a 9 or 10-inch pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 325°.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins with the margarine in about 3 cups of water until tender.
Mix cornstarch in 1/4 cup cold water; add to raisins to thicken them.
If this is not enough to thicken, add a little more.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Let mixture cool.
Pour into bottom crust.
Top with remaining crust.
Slash crust and brush with margarine.
Cook until crust is brown at 375°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, eggs, pumpkin, water and dry ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch pans.
Bake in moderate oven for 1 hour.

title: raisin energy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. In a large bowl, combine butter, egg and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Add the oats and flour, stirring until well mixed.
Stir in the raisins, almonds, dates and chocolate chips.
Spread butter evenly in the prepared pan and sprinkle with bran.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan before cutting into squares.

title: gandhi's nappa salad
directions: Brown noodles and almonds in butter (takes about 10 minutes). Combine noodles, almonds, cabbage (chopped), and onions (chopped) in bowl and refrigerate.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Fry rice with 1/2 stick of butter.
Bring to boil soup, broth and bouillon cube.
Brown pork chops.
In a large casserole dish, put in rice; layer pork chops, then pour soup mixture over it. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour in a medium saucepan.
Add vinegar and water.
Cook until thick and add butter.
Add 2 cups sliced or julienned cooked beets to prepared sauce and heat.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: porcupine meat balls(club member: jason harvey)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except catsup and water. Mix well and shape into small balls. Place in baking dish and cover with catsup and water mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover last 15 minutes.

title: straw and hay
directions: Combine milk, cottage cheese and cornstarch in container of food processor or electric blender.
Top with cover and process until smooth.
Transfer milk mixture to a medium nonstick skillet. Place over medium heat.
Add 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and nutmeg, stirring well until cheese melts; set aside.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add ham and garlic; saute 2 minutes.
Stir in peas and saute 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in reserved milk mixture; set aside.
Cook fettucine and spinach fettucine according to package directions, omitting salt and fat.
Drain.
Place in a large bowl; pour ham mixture over pasta, tossing until well combined.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately.
Yields 12 servings.
Contains 118 calories per 1/2-cup serving.

title: delicious banana pudding
directions: Layer sliced bananas and vanilla wafers in serving bowl. Break eggs in boiler; add salt and sugar.
Heat milk and pour in with dry ingredients and eggs.
Heat over medium heat and stir until thick.
While still hot, pour over bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: cream of broccoli soup(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart microwaveproof bowl, combine all ingredients, except broccoli.
Stir until cornstarch is dissolved.
Add broccoli.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on 70 for 13 to 14 minutes, or until broccoli is fork-tender.
Stir once during cooking time.
Let stand 3 minutes before serving.
Garnish with small raw broccoli florets.

title: pineapple nut pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice together.
Mix together pineapple, milk, and lemon juice.
Add pecans and Cool Whip.
Mix all together.
Pour into the 2 crusts.
Put plastic cover over each and freeze until ready to use.

title: cordon bleu
directions: Make sure veal cutlet is a light pink in color, the color of pork is what your looking for.
Prepare a batter with flour and eggs.
Don't season with salt, since the ham is salty, may use a little pepper.
Place the cheese and ham of top of the cutlet. Coat lightly with the batter, place in breadcrumbs,
press both sides firmly into crumbs.
Sauces should be mixed together and kept hot (double boil is safer).
You can prepare cutlets 2-3 hours before serving.
In a thick bottomed skillet over moderate heat saute cutlet in olive oil browning both sides.
If one side is taking more than 3 minutes, increase the heat a little.
Serve with hot sauce under the veal and a sprig of parsley on top.

title: barbecue ham
directions: In medium size pot, brown the onion in the oleo.
Add the ketchup, water and brown sugar.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add chipped ham.
Stir until well mixed.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lemon ice cream
directions: Mix lemonade, sugar, Eagle Brand milk and enough milk to fill can.
Pour into freezer.
Can substitute juice of 9 lemons for can of frozen lemonade.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain the pears, peaches and pineapple. Put fruit mixture into a large bowl. Add strawberries and juice. Sprinkle with dry pudding mix. Let set several hours before serving. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: "roll your own" manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix Ricotta, Mozzarella, bread crumbs, salt, parsley and egg.
Boil lasagna as directed (on box).
Cut cooked lasagna strips in half.
Spoon portion of cheese mix onto each strip and roll macaroni.
Pour 1/2 meat sauce in a 9 x 13-inch pan and arrange manicotti in single layer over sauce.
Top manicotti with remaining sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix and bring to a boil.
Add drained squash and bring again to a boil.
Pack in hot jars.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese and combine ingredients.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: smothered cabbage wedges
directions: In a Dutch oven cook cabbage wedges in a small amount of salted water until tender (about 12 minutes).
Drain and place wedges in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In a saucepan, cook green pepper and onion in butter until tender but not brown.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Pour over cabbage and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Mix mayonnaise, chili sauce and cheese. Spoon over wedges and bake 5 more minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crab swiss bites
directions: Combine all ingredients except biscuits and mix well. Separate biscuits into 3 layers and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spoon crab mixture and press down lightly with a fork to near edge of biscuit.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Serves 36 appetizers.

title: fruit pops
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Pour into 5 ounce paper cups and place a popsicle stick in middle and freeze.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash tender-crisp; drain.
Add next 5 ingredients; stir gently to combine.
Melt butter; toss with stuffing mix.
Reserve 1/2 cup.
Press 1 1/2 cups mix on bottom of 2-quart casserole. Pour squash mixture over and sprinkle the reserved crumbs over. Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven until browned on top.
